title: rocky road cake
directions: Mix cake as per package directions.
Add rest of ingredients and stir until combined.
Pour into buttered tube or Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: picante paella
directions: Cut sausage into 1/2-inch pieces.
Discard casing.
Cook sausage, onion and garlic in oil in skillet until meat is no longer pink.
Add broth, picante sauce, rice and saffron.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in chicken.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in shrimp and peas.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 to 10 minutes, until liquid is absorbed.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into mixture of flour, sugar and salt until crumbly.
Beat water, vinegar and egg together.
Stir into flour mixture.
Divide into 4 portions.
Shape into patties and wrap in waxed paper.
Chill for 30 minutes or up to 3 days.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil and continue boiling for 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from stove and add chocolate chips, chocolate squares, marshmallows and nuts. Stir until melted.
Beat rapidly for 1 minute.
Pour into greased pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck; mix together onions, soup and peas and add to ground chuck.
Pour into baking dish and place Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: horehound candy
directions: Add horehound to hot water and cook about 20 minutes; strain. Add sugar and cook until syrup forms a hard ball when dropped in cold water.
Pour into greased pan.
When cool, form into small balls or cut into squares.

title: cream of chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix soup, chiles, sour cream and cheese, stirring over medium heat.
Cook tortillas and dip into mixture.
Put 1 1/2 tablespoons chicken into each tortilla and roll each one.
Pour rest of mixture over enchiladas.
Sprinkle the cheese over top and put in oven 15 minutes at 350°.
Serves 2 to 6.

title: dream cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in 9 x 13 dish. Put in freezer until serving time. Top with pecans before serving.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes; mix all ingredients except corn flakes.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 1 hour at 375°.
During last 5 minutes of baking, add corn flakes to top.

title: chicken couch
directions: Cook and bone chicken in salted water.
Place broccoli in bottom of casserole.
Lay chicken on top of broccoli.
Combine other ingredients and pour over top.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked french fries(low fat recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Cut potatoes lengthwise into 1/4 inch thick slices, then cut into fry shaped strips. Pour oil into bowl and toss to coat. Spread on baking sheet and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Bake 20 minutes and then turn potatoes and bake until crisp, about 15 minutes.

title: cheese straws
directions: Grate cheese; add flour.
Cream the butter.
Cook at 400° about 10 minutes until golden brown.

title: strawberry fig jam
directions: Combine figs, sugar and jello.
Cook until thick and transparent (about 35 to 40 minutes).
Makes 4 pints.
Wash jars in hot, soapy water.
Rinse well.
Place jars and lids in pot of boiling water.
Boil at least 10 minutes.
Remove jars from hot water.
Place on clean dishcloth.
Fill jars with jam.
Place lids on jars and seal tightly.

title: egg drop soup
directions: *Lipton noodle soup mix with real chicken broth.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Soak first 4 ingredients overnight; next morning, rinse twice, then add to remaining ingredients.
Bring all ingredients to a rolling boil.
Use in potato salad, macaroni salad, etc.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix pecans and coconut.
Drain pineapple; add lemon juice and mix with condensed milk.
Fold in 1/2 of Cool Whip and mix.
Pour in pie crust.
Put in refrigerator and top with Cool Whip.

title: gazpacho
directions: Beat oil and lemon juice. Stir in all other ingredients. Chill thoroughly. Serves 8 to 10.

title: asian chicken salad
directions: In a small bowl, whisk oil, vinegar, sugar, pepper and contents of noodle seasoning packet; set aside.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine Marshmallow Creme and softened cream cheese;
mix until well blended. Makes 2 cups.

title: ham and cheese strata
directions: Remove crusts from bread and cut into cubes.
Alternate layers of bread and cheese in an 8 x 12-inch or 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk and salt.
Pour over bread and cheese.
Place cubed ham and mushrooms on top.
Pour melted butter over all.
Refrigerate overnight.
Following day, bake at 350° for about an hour or until firm and golden brown.
Cut into squares and serve warm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine pie filling mix, milk, sugar and egg in saucepan. Blend well.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and 1 cup coconut. Cool about 5 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Pour into pie shell. Cover with waxed paper.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Cover with whipped cream and sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: shortbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat sugar, oil, eggs, and vanilla. Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add cocoa.
Add nuts and zucchini.
Mix well and spread on a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until mixture tests done.
Frost with the following:

title: caesar salad
directions: Rub wooden bowl with 1 cut garlic clove; crush the rest. Allow some garlic in the bowl.
Mix in 1 cup anchovies, oil, salt, dry mustard and pepper.
Chop lettuce.
Add mixture to lettuce; squeeze lemon over salad and toss.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and croutons.

title: creamy pasta primavera
directions: Cook carrots and broccoli in boiling water 3 to 4 minutes or until tender; drain.
Pour warm water over snow peas to thaw; drain.
In large skillet, warm Ranch dressing over moderate heat until almost simmering.
Do not boil.
Add noodles and veggies; toss to coat.
Remove from heat; sprinkle with cheese and parsley. (Use diet Ranch to cut calories.)

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix every thing except vanilla and peanut butter in a boiler and cook to a soft ball stage.
Stir in vanilla and peanut butter and stir until stiff.
Put into a buttered pan and pat down with the back of the spoon.

title: spanish pork chops
directions: Slowly brown pork chops in a large skillet (electric skillet is fine) until they are nicely browned.
Remove chops and set aside.
Keep some of the drippings in the skillet and brown the contents of the box of beef Rice-A-Roni until light golden in color.
Add stewed tomatoes and water to the Rice-A-Roni in the skillet.
Add the browned pork chops to the mixture and cover the skillet with a lid.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes (with the lid on).
Serves 4 to 6.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Chop nuts, dates and orange slices into small pieces and add coconut.
Melt butter and pour over mixture.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk, cook, stirring until thickened.
Add small portion into eggs; blend well.
Pour egg mixture into hot mixture.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and butter.
Pour into baked pie shell. Top with meringue or whipped topping.

title: reuben chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in greased baking dish.
Drain sauerkraut and spread over all.
You may not need all of it.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon.
In medium bowl, mix salmon, egg and onion. Stir in flour.
Form into patties and fry until golden brown.

title: crock-pot meatballs
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Make into balls and put on cookie sheets; close together.
Put in 350° oven for 15 minutes. Bump the pan and bake for 5 more minutes.
Refrigerate until ready to heat in crock-pot.
Add cream sauce (3 cans of cream of mushroom soup and 2 tablespoons dill weed).
Heat until warmed.
Great for parties.
Makes a big batch.

title: party potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender; drain.
Beat softened cream cheese and sour cream at medium speed until well blended.
Add hot potatoes gradually, beating constantly until light and fluffy. Season to taste with salt.
Spoon mixture into 2-quart greased casserole dish.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Mix up and bake in 4 layers.

title: turketti
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spinach with oil
directions: Rinse and drain spinach or defrost frozen spinach.
Brown onions and garlic in hot oil until golden brown.
Remove onions and garlic with slotted spoon; set aside for garnishing.
Add spinach to oil; cover and cook for 10 minutes on low heat. Garnish with oil and garlic.
Serve with lemon wedges.
Serves 4.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips with peanut butter.
Pour over the Crispix in a large bowl.
Dump powdered sugar in a large plastic bag.
Add the chocolate covered Crispix and shake well.
This make a lot.
Will keep about 10 days in a tightly covered container.

title: seafood linguini casserole
directions: In saute pan, cook mushrooms and onions in butter for about 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove mushrooms and onions.
In butter remaining in pan add tomato paste, tarragon, salt and pepper and wine.
Boil hard for 10 minutes or reduced to 1/2 cup.
Beat egg yolks to blend and add cream.
Add this mixture to wine mixture.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Stir in shrimp, mushrooms, onions and water chestnuts.
Heat through and toss with cooked linguini.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: sausage in pastry
directions: Combine cream cheese and margarine, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended.
Add flour and mix well. Shape into ball. Chill. Divide pastry in half on lightly floured surface. Roll each pastry half to 15 x 12-inch rectangle.
Cut into 3-inch squares.
Place sausage piece in center of each pastry square.
Bring edge together, pressing to seal.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serve with saucework hot mustard sauce.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine carrots, eggs, sugar and oil.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour into greased pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: no-friller-cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix baking mix, milk and cheese until a soft dough forms; beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, until golden brown.
Mix butter and garlic powder; brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 biscuits, each with 169 calories, 10 g fat and 15 mg cholesterol.

title: almond pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortenings well.
Add eggs and salt; mix well. Add remaining ingredients; the longer the batter is mixed, the better the cake.
Pour into very lightly greased 12-cup Bundt pan. Put into cold oven; set temperature at 320°.
Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes and remove from pan.
Keeps very well several days.

title: quick applesauce cake
directions: Blend sugar and cinnamon.
Grease a 10-inch Bundt or tube pan and dust with 1 tablespoon sugar-cinnamon mixture, reserving remainder for cake.
Blend margarine, eggs, applesauce and cake mix until moistened.
Pour 1/2 of batter into pan.
Sprinkle remaining mixture of sugar and cinnamon on batter in pan.
Add remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all
ingredients well.
Form into 2 loaves and wrap in foil.
Refrigerate
hours.
Poke
4 holes in bottom and sides of loaf.
Place on rack over cake pan to catch drippings and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: hamburg stroganoff
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef with bacon.
Add onion; cook until tender, but not brown.
Drain off the excess fat.
Add seasonings to meat mixture.
Stir in soup; cook slowly, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Stirring frequently, stir in sour cream and heat through; do not boil.
Serve over hot noodles.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: nut cookies
directions: Cream softened oleo and add sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Put spices in flour and add to oleo and sugar mixture.
Pour into cookie pan and brush the top with egg white and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake for 30 minutes at 300° to 325°.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order given into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Seal with mayonnaise, spread completely over top of vegetables.
Cover dish completely with Saran Wrap or foil and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Toss before serving.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Mix cornstarch and water until there are no lumps.
Add to mixture in saucepan; stir constantly until it boils.
Boil for 1 minute, then simmer for 5 minutes.

title: fluffy chicken and dumplings
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening or oil with a pastry blender.
Stir in milk until blended.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cooked chicken pieces in broth.
Cook 10 minutes uncovered and 10 minutes covered.

title: apricot bread
directions: Cover apricots with warm water and soak 30 minutes.
Drain and cut into 1/4-inch pieces.
Blend sugar, butter and egg.
Add water and orange juice.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to liquids.
Beat until smooth.
Add apricots and nuts.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour into greased loaf pan which has been lined with wax paper.
Let mixture stand for 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes.
Cool and remove from pan.
This recipe doubles easily to make 2 loaves.

title: sausage cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients by hand, then add boiling water and buttermilk with soda, dissolved in 2 cups flour.
Mix well.
Mix dried fruit, black walnuts, 1 cup flour and raisins.
Add fruit mixture to batter.
Bake in greased tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Cover with heavy foil.
Can be refrigerated for up to 1 week or can be frozen.

title: quiche vickay
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium mixing bowl, combine Cheddar and Swiss; sprinkle half of mixture into pie shell.
Sprinkle in bacon bits, then cover with remaining cheese mixture.
In small mixing bowl, combine eggs, milk, onion powder and black pepper; beat thoroughly.
Pour over cheese; sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes until firm and toothpick (when inserted) comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes, then cut into pie shaped slices.

title: orange julius
directions: Pour all ingredients in blender and mix until smooth.

title: blueberry tea cake
directions: Stir shortening to soften.
Add flour sifted with baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add milk and beat for two minutes.
Add eggs, beat one minute.
Stir in blueberries.
Pour in sheet cake pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: southwest frankfurters
directions: In saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients except frankfurters.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish (10 x 6 x 2-inch); top with frankfurters. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mexican hot chocolate
directions: Sift the powdered sugar.
Mix all ingredients well.
Let sit 24 hours before using.

title: tahitian supper
directions: In
saucepan,
combine	1/2
cup
packed
brown
sugar, cornstarch,
pineapple
juice, water and vinegar.
Cook, stirring until clear and thick, then stir in the Treet or Spam cut in 1-inch
cubes
and	bell pepper strips.
Keep cooking until hot (about
10 minutes).
Serve over hot, cooked rice.	Serves 4.

title: rock cornish hen-apple roast
directions: Wash thawed Rock Cornish hens and pat dry.
Rub inside and out with salt and nutmeg.
Stuff lightly with Brown-Apple Stuffing (if dressing is desired) and truss.

title: garlic lover's vinegar
directions: Separate and peel all the cloves of garlic.
Put them in the vinegar and allow to steep for two weeks.
Strain the vinegar and discard the garlic.
Only a few drops are needed in most dishes.

title: onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter until limp and tender.
Add broth, water and seasoning.
Simmer for 1 hour.
(You really don't have to, but I like to let the flavors blend.)
Ladle soup into ovenproof bowls; top with a slice of bread and cheese.
Broil until cheese bubbles.

title: confetti caramel corn
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Place cereal in a jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Mix brown sugar, margarine and corn syrup in a 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Heat mixture over medium heat about 3 minutes, stirring occasionally, until margarine is melted and mixture begins to boil.
Cook, without stirring, 4 minutes longer. (Mixture will boil and turn golden brown.)
Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla and baking soda until mixture is foamy.
Pour over cereal; stir to coat evenly.
Bake 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Loosen right away from sides and bottom.
Cool. Makes 7 cups.

title: drop doughnut balls
directions: Mix sugar, milk and egg and add melted shortening.
Add sifted flour, salt, baking powder and nutmeg to the liquid mixture. Combine the 2 mixtures lightly.
Drop from a teaspoon into deep cooking oil heated to 365° (or until an inch cube of bread browns in 60 seconds).
Fry doughnut balls until brown and cooked in the center (about 4 minutes).
Drain on absorbent paper, roll in powdered sugar, if desired.

title: ham-linguine florentine
directions: In a large saucepan, cook mushrooms and onion in margarine and oil until onion is tender but not brown.
Stir in flour and thyme; mix well.
Add the beef broth and milk all at once.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 minute more.
Stir in ham, parsley and mustard, using a wooden spoon to thoroughly combine.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place rice in bottom of greased baking dish.
Arrange chicken, skin side up.
Place on top of rice.
Combine milk, soup and water; pour over rice and chicken.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cinnamon sticks
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Separate breadsticks into strips.
Twist each strip and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Brush with combined margarine and honey. Sprinkle with combined sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes until browned.
Makes 8 cinnamon sticks.

title: cauliflower with mustard sauce and dill
directions: Pour stock into a 10-inch skillet and add dill seeds and bay leaves.
Cover and bring to a simmer.
Add cauliflower, cover and continue to simmer until cauliflower is tender, about 7 to 8 minutes.
Uncover the skillet and place it in the refrigerator. Let cauliflower chill in its stock for about 30 minutes.
Drain cauliflower, reserving stock and place it in a serving dish. Strain stock and combine 1/4 cup of it with mustard.
Drizzle sauce over cauliflower, sprinkle with minced dill and serve.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in skins, peel and chunk.
Saute onion in butter.
Add cheese and soup, chunky potatoes.
Mix together.

title: slow and easy chuck roast
directions: Cut away as much fat as possible from roast.
Sprinkle roast with next 3 ingredients and place in crock-pot.
Add water and cook
on low for 8 to 10 hours.
Thicken gravy with flour or cornstarch.
Serves 6.

title: sherry sauce
directions: Beat butter until smooth and creamy.
Add
powdered sugar gradually.
Add the sherry slowly and beat until smooth.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Saute onion in small amount of butter in microwave until tender.
Cook bacon until almost done.
Let cool and cut into small pieces.
Add potatoes, cheese, onion, bacon and mayonnaise in bowl.
Stir well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into a buttered 2-quart casserole and bake at 350° until cheese melts (usually 30 to 40 minutes) or microwave.

title: crunchy nut cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar and white sugar with oleo.
Add eggs.
Mix again.
Add flour, soda, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Drop by spoon and press down with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together the pretzels, melted butter and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Mix the cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Dissolve the jello in the hot water.
Put in the frozen raspberries (put in frozen).
Stir and dissolve.
Let set up until syrupy.
Spread over top of Cool Whip mixture.

title: grilled steamed hamburgers
directions: Note:
Need aluminum foil and 1 grill.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water. Add pineapple and blueberry pie filling. Chill. Top with mixture of cream cheese, sugar and vanilla. Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.

title: chocolate creamy fudge
directions: Lightly grease 9 x 9 x 2 pan. Set aside. Heat sugar, butter, milk and marshmallow cream in heavy 3 qt. sauce pan, over medium heat until mixture boils, stirring constantly. Boil and stir, 5 minutes. Add chocolate chips and vanilla. Beat till chips are melted. Stir in walnuts. Immediately spread into greased pan. Refrigerate over night, cut into 1 inch squares. Store in air tight container in refrigerator. For creamer fudge, set out 1 hour before serving.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix thoroughly. Keep in airtight container.
Use 1 rounded teaspoonful per cup hot water.

title: chicken soup
directions: Place chicken in large stewing pot; add water.
Bring to boil; lower burner.
Simmer gently, uncovered, for 3 hours.
Add other ingredients just before lowering burner.
Allow pot to cool.
Chill soup.
Remove fat and strain soup.
Reserve small amount fat and return to soup as you reheat for serving.
Cut chicken into small pieces.
Serves 8.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar; continue beating 2 minutes.
Add vanilla, pecans and crushed Ritz crackers.
Stir. Press into pie pan.
Cook on 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Best if baked in loaf pans.

title: squash casserole
directions: Dice squash and onion and cook until done.
Pour off excess water.
Add to squash and onion, one can of cream of chicken soup. Mix well.
Pour into a casserole dish; top with grated Cheddar cheese and crumbled Ritz crackers.
Bake at 325° for approximately 15 to 20 minutes (or until bubbly).

title: 3-bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and bacon.
Add in all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine ingredients and bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Season chicken breasts with celery, salt and onion flakes. Both kinds of chicken breasts can be found at Sams.
Wrap in foil and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cut chicken into bite-size pieces, reserving the liquid in the foil.
Add soups, sour cream, reserved liquid, onion and jalapeno to chicken and mix.
Tear tortillas into quarters.
Layer tortillas, chicken and cheeses twice, ending with the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves about 6.

title: lasagna
directions: Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, 1/2 teaspoon salt, oregano and basil leaves to first 4 ingredients and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocklit chip cookies
directions: Put chocklit chips into the dough.
Add 1 cup shugar and 2 scoopes of flour.
Stir and put them in the oven for 100 degrees for 3 minutes.
Take it out and eat.

title: linda's crunchy chicken cheese bake
directions: In 3-quart oblong baking dish, place chicken. Top with cheese. Stir soup and spread over cheese; top with tomato. Combine margarine and stuffing; sprinkle over tomato. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: tart beet salad
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in 1 cup boiling water, then add 1 cup beet juice or cold water.
Add beets, celery, onion, horseradish and mustard; stir.
Pour into individual molds or 8 x 8-inch dish. Delicious with bland meat dishes or cheese strata.
Serves 8.

title: haystacks
directions: Combine and bring to a boil for one minute the sugar, milk, cocoa and butter.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop on wax paper by spoonfuls and let dry.

title: swiss chicken casserole
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish. Top with cheese slices. Combine milk and soup. Stir well. Spoon over chicken. Sprinkle with stuffing mix. Drizzle butter over crumbs. Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: english toffee
directions: Butter a square pan.
Sprinkle almonds on bottom of pan to cover.
Melt butter in saucepan and add brown sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 7 minutes continuously.
Carefully pour hot sugar mixture over almonds.
Break up chocolate bar into small pieces and immediately put on top of hot mixture.
Chocolate will melt. Gently spread chocolate over entire surface, being careful not to mix up layers.
Cool completely before removing from pan.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Drain pineapple (reserve syrup).
Halve pineapple slices.
Melt butter in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Add brown sugar and 1 tablespoon of juice.
Arrange pineapple in bottom of pan.
Place cherry half in center of each pineapple.
Cream together shortening and sugar until light.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add water to pineapple juice to make 1/2 cup.
Put all together and beat.
Spread over pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pina colada fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into a foil lined 9 x 13-inch square dish or pan.
Let stand in refrigerator until firm. Peel off foil and cut into squares.

title: delicious chess squares
directions: Mix and press cake mix, margarine and 1 egg in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix well the cream cheese, powdered sugar and 2 eggs and pour over bottom layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: double crispy chicken
directions: Measure crushed Kellogg's corn flakes cereal into shallow dish or pan.
Set aside.

title: ellie may's pound cake
directions: Have butter and eggs at room temperature.
Sift together cake flour, salt and soda.
Beat butter gently until fluffy; add sugar slowly and mix until creamy and light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add sour cream and flour mixture alternately.
Blend in flavorings.
Pour into large tube pan sprayed with Pam (this makes a larger cake).
Bake at 330° for 1 hour and 10 minutes (or until tester comes out clean).
Serves 15 to 20.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix together and bake in casserole dish for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Soften gelatin in 3 tablespoons cold water.
Heat gelatin, soup and salt in deep pan; while warm, add remaining ingredients. Stir well.
Put in mold and chill.
Great with crackers.

title: brownie pie
directions: Sift together sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add 4 beaten eggs; stir in margarine and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked shallow pie shells and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Important:
Do not overcook.

title: tennessee barbecue sauce(u.t. prof. cole)
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Heat, but do not boil. Baste chicken frequently over medium fire, turning occasionally, until done (1 1/2 hours).

title: apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer in saucepan until thick.
Pour in unbaked crust and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Mix cheese
and
jello	together
and
set aside.
Melt marshmallows and 7-Up
and	pour over jello mixture while hot. Blend in pineapple;
stir
and set until it starts to thicken. Add mayonnaise and fold in whipping cream.
Set until firm.

title: good plain cake
directions: Cream the sugar, butter and eggs together. Gradually add flour. Stir in vanilla.
Mix well. Pour into a greased and floured pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: yum-yum cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread the coconut and nuts in bottom
of pan.
Mix the German chocolate cake mix per directions on the
box and pour over the nuts and coconut. Soften the margarine
and cream cheese and cream together with the powdered sugar.
Spoon
over
top
of
cake batter.
Swirl with fork.
Caution:
do
not
touch bottom or sides of pan or cake will run over.
Bake
for 50 to 60 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.

title: dale's apricot chess pie
directions: Cover bottom of 10-inch unbaked pie shell (should have high sides) with the apricots.
Mix the other ingredients (except nutmeg) and pour carefully over the apricots.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven to 325° and bake for about 30 minutes.

title: chicken with dressing
directions: Place bite size pieces of chicken at bottom of 9 x 12-inch dish.
Mix soups and milk and heat; pour this over chicken.
Melt oleo in 1 1/2 cups chicken broth, then mix stuffing mix with this; spread over chicken and soup.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: cheesy red onions
directions: In a large pot, place onions in water to cover.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Remove.
With one fork, secure onion; pull out 1/2 inch onion center with another fork.
Fill with cheese.
Place in a greased baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, until tender. Serves 6.

title: sausage balls
directions: Blend ingredients and make into balls about the size of large marbles.
Bake
for
15 minutes.	These can be baked ahead and frozen.
Makes about 90.

title: meat balls
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Shape into 12 balls.
Brown in skillet.
Combine catsup, water and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Pour over meat balls.
Simmer over low heat 20 minutes, stirring frequently. Makes 4 servings.
Pour over cooked spaghetti or cooked rice.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, combine flour, meal, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In medium bowl, beat egg, milk and margarine.
Add egg mixture and sour cream to flour. Stir until blended.
Pour into baking pan and bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: easiest ever peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt chocolate and peanut butter in top of a double boiler. Remove from heat and stir in milk.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan lined with wax paper.
Chill.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: exotic turkey salad
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients. Toss with mayonnaise. Refrigerate before serving. Serves 8.

title: crescent turkey rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cream cheese and margarine, then add next 6 ingredients and to mix.
Separate crescent rolls into 4 rectangles, seal them.
Spoon of mixture into center of rectangle, pull 4 corners of dough to the center and seal edges.
Brush top with margarine and sprinkle with crouton crumbs.
If used without croutons and margarine, it is still very good.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: baked barbecue chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat preserves, dressing and soup mix until smooth (preserves will melt).
Pour over chicken and bake for 1 hour, covered with foil.
Remove foil and bake an additional hour.

title: easy graham cracker cookies
directions: Spread graham crackers out on large cookie sheet.
Bring oleo and brown sugar to a boil.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly. Add pecans.
Spread mixture over graham crackers.
Do this quickly.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let crackers cool on wax paper.
Break graham crackers into quarters.

title: romaine lettuce soup
directions: Cook lettuce and water in pressure cooker for 5 minutes.
Heat onion in melted butter until soft over low heat.
Add to lettuce and water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Put croutons on top.
Makes 6 servings.

title: green bean request
directions: Put alternate layers of beans and onions in casserole dish. Mix soup, mushrooms and almonds with liquid.
Pour over beans. Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry breeze
directions: Beat cream cheese with mixer until light and fluffy.
Add Eagle Brand and blend thoroughly.
Stir in lemon juice and Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Top with chilled pie filling before serving.

title: holiday fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and crushed pineapple thoroughly. Mix with bananas and cherries. Blend softened cream cheese and mayonnaise and mix with fruits, taking care that everything is well mixed.

title: egg custard
directions: Scald milk (do not boil).
Separate 3 of the eggs and use 3 whole eggs.
Beat eggs slightly.
Slowly add sugar while beating egg mixture.
Add a little of the hot milk to egg mixture (add hot milk slowly at first and then add remaining milk).
Add cornstarch.
Cook in top of double boiler or on slow heat on top of stove.
Stir constantly until mixture is slightly thick.
Do not boil or custard will curdle.
Add vanilla and cool.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add milk, sweet potatoes, vanilla, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Mix well. Pour into pie shell and bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 35 to 40 minutes longer or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.
Store in refrigerator. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: club salads
directions: Divide salad greens among four salad plates and top with tomatoes and chicken.
Spoon dressing over top.
Sprinkle with bacon and garnish with toast.

title: cream of cauliflower soup
directions: Break up the cauliflower into small pieces and put on to boil in water.
While it is boiling, chop the green onions finely and saute very slowly in butter over low heat.

When the cauliflower is barely tender, remove from heat and add the milk to it. Combine the flour with the onions and mix well; cook for about 3 minutes, stirring all the while, and then turn the heat off for a moment.
Slowly pour the cauliflower mixture into the flour mixture, stirring continuously, until it is well mixed.
Now add the salt and black pepper; turn the heat back on and let it come to a simmer (do not boil) and cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from the heat and stir in the chopped parsley.
Serve over croutons, if desired.
Serves 6 people.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and chop or cut up carrots, cut up celery and chop up onions.
Cover these with water and cook for about 1 hour to 1 1/2 hours.
Cut up potatoes, cook until tender on medium heat.
When almost done, add margarine and cook until melted.
Mix cornstarch and skim milk and thicken to suit.
Add salt and pepper to taste. When done, you can sprinkle parsley flakes on top.

title: coconut knots(cookies)
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and coconut flavoring.
Add egg and beat with a spoon.
Then add Bisquick mix and instant potatoes.
Cover bowl with a clean towel and chill 1 hour.
Then I shape my dough into 2 rolls.
Each roll I cut into 4 long strips and cut off pieces the size of the end of your thumb.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and lightly press each down.
Bake at 300° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Take out and remove with spatula from baking sheet and put on a clean towel to cool.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions. Drain well. Pour into greased casserole dish. Add butter and cheese; mix well. Mix eggs, milk, tomatoes, salt and pepper in another bowl. Combine with pasta and cheese. Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Let sit 5 to 10 minutes, then serve.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour spring-form baking pan; set aside.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
With electric mixer on medium, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes.
Reduce speed to low and add egg and vanilla.
Alternately add flour mixture and milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Fold in berries.

title: traditional rocky road fudge
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, combine sugar, butter and evaporated milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until mixture comes to a full boil (7 to 10 minutes).
Boil, stirring constantly, until candy thermometer reaches 228° or small amount of mixture dropped into ice water forms a 2-inch soft thread (5 to 6 minutes).
Remove from heat, gradually stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Stir in marshmallows and peanuts, leaving a marbled effect.
Spread in lightly buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover; refrigerate until completely cooled.
Cut into 1-inch squares. Store covered in refrigerator.
Yields 9 to 10 dozen candies.

title: nuant(nut candy)
directions: Have a cookie sheet or jelly roll pan ready.
Put the honey and lemon juice in a large saucepan; bring to a boil over medium high heat, stirring occasionally.
Add nuts; stir over medium heat for 10 to 12 minutes, until mixture is thick and a rich brown. Remove from heat.
Moisten cookie sheet with water.
Pour nut mixture onto sheet and spread with back of a wet wooden spoon or spatula.
Let cool and harden.
Break into bite size pieces. Store airtight with waxed paper in between layers.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: pumpkin-beef stew
directions: Preheat broiler.
Place meat on rack in pan 4 inches from heat.
Broil 10 minutes, turning once.
Set aside.
In large pot, over medium heat, heat oil and saute onions 5 minutes until tender.
Add broth, meat and pepper.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes partially covered until meat is tender.
Add pumpkin, beans and salt; cook 10 minutes longer, until pumpkin is tender.
Toast peanuts in nonstick skillet, shaking pan 2 minutes. Pour stew into serving bowl; sprinkle with peanuts and coriander.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Bake in pie shell for 1 hour at 325°.

title: fruit pizza
directions: *Or you can use any fruit you like.

title: lefse
directions: Heat water with margarine and Crisco.
Add sugar, salt and flour and mix well.
Roll out on lightly floured board until thin. Bake on griddle, dabbing on milk as it bakes.
Cook on both sides.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix thoroughly flour, butter and confectioners sugar.
Press evenly in bottom of ungreased square pan, either 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inch.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: gold water beans
directions: Add all ingredients to cooked beans.
Cook 1/2 hour, until the flavors blend.
Serve over rice with picante sauce.

title: mango bread
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together; form
a
well
in the center.
Add the remaining ingredients;
mix.
Pour
into pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: never-fail pie crust
directions: Blend shortening or lard with flour, sugar and salt.
Beat slightly the egg in a measuring cup and fill the cup with water. Mix with dry mixture.
This will make several crusts.

title: frozen pops
directions: Dissolve Jell-O, Kool-Aid and sugar in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Pour into ice cube trays, small paper cups or frozen pop molds.
Insert wooden sticks or paper spoons diagonally in each ice cube section or at an angle in molds or cups for handles.
(If desired, pops may be partially frozen before handles are inserted.) Freeze until firm, 2 to 3 hours.
Makes 20 to 24 pops.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Brown potatoes in butter. Combine cheese, soup, sour cream, onion, 1/4 cup butter, salt and pepper.
Mix, then fold in potatoes.
Pour into baking dish.
Toss cornflakes in butter and sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: hamburger noodles
directions: Melt butter in large frying pan.
Brown meat; add garlic, salt, pepper, sugar and tomato sauce.
Simmer for 20 minutes (cover).
Cook noodles (drain).
Cut green onions into pieces. Place in blender with sour cream and cream cheese.
Blend until smooth.
Place 1/3 of noodles in 2-quart casserole dish, then 1/3 of cheese mixture and 1/3 of meat, layering, ending with meat. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: Cook over hot water and beat to right consistency.

title: peanut butter cookie chips
directions: Combine peanut butter, shortening, sugar, vanilla, and water, in that order, beating on medium speed of mixer. Stir in biscuit mix. Drop by small teaspoons on lightly greased cookie sheet. Flatten with bottom of a glass dipped in milk. (Especially attractive if bottom of glass has a design on it.) Bake at 400° for 8 minutes. Yield: about 6 dozen.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and half of onion rings, mixing well.
Spoon half of pea mixture into a lightly greased 2-quart baking dish.
Top with half of cheese.
Spoon remaining pea mixture over cheese and top with remaining cheese.
Sprinkle remaining onion rings over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: three cheers for chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken and place in a large 11 x 14-inch Pyrex.
Melt margarine and add onion, bell pepper, pimentos, rice, soups, water and water chestnuts.
Pour over chicken breasts. Cook at 350° for 15 minutes, then turn oven down to 300° and cook for 1 hour more.
Add cheese 5 minutes before dish is done and return to oven for the last 5 minutes.

title: mexican supper pie
directions: Brown meat and onion, add other ingredients and pour into large dish.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Cook at 375° in large greased pan until golden brown.
Will be moist when done.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix instant pudding and milk.
Beat for 1 minute only.
Add whipped topping; mix well.
Layer whole (not crushed) graham crackers in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread 1/2 pudding mixture on top; repeat.
Add one more layer graham crackers.
Gently spread frosting on top of crackers.
Refrigerate 10 to 12 hours.

title: crisp toffee bars
directions: Thoroughly cream together butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour; mix well.
Stir in chocolate and walnuts.
Press mixture into a 13 x 9-inch ungreased cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes just until lightly browned.
While warm, cut in squares, then cool before removing from pan.
Makes about 5 dozen.
They can be cut very small because they are quite rich.

title: prune cake
directions: Combine ingredients (dry ingredients, then milk and vanilla). Bake in greased cake pan at 300° about 45 minutes.

title: lemon pecan cake
directions: Dredge pecans and cherries in a cup of flour.
In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add remaining flour and lemon extract, beating until smooth.
Fold in cherries and nuts.
Pour into a well-greased and floured tube pan and bake at 250° for one hour. Test to see if done.

title: chicken pizza
directions: Halve, bone, skin and cut breasts in 1-inch pieces.
Unroll crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Press dough into lightly oiled 12-inch pizza pan, sealing perforations well.
Heat oil in skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken, onion, green pepper, mushrooms and olives and cook, stirring, 15 to 20 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender and almost all liquid is absorbed.
Spread pizza sauce over dough.
With slotted spoon (to drain off any excess drippings), spoon chicken mixture evenly over sauce.
Sprinkle garlic salt, oregano and Parmesan cheese over all.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 20 minutes or until crust is done.
Cut into wedges to serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: old fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: In a saucepan, cook raisins in water until plump, about 15 minutes.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Add enough water to liquid to measure 1/2 cup.
In a mixing bowl, cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in raisin liquid.
Blend in dry ingredients. Stir in raisins and oats.
Add nuts if desired.
Drop by teaspoon about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown.
Yield: 5 dozen.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients and mix well. Add to boiling water and cook until thick and clear, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Arrange berries in a cooled, baked pie shell.
Pour cooled mixture over the berries and chill.
May top with whipped cream.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and cream cheese.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, stirring just until blended.
Stir in flavorings.

title: luscious strawberry jello
directions: Pour boiling water over jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Add frozen berries; stir gently.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add pineapple and nuts.

title: poached pears in red wine sauce(great for holidays!)
directions: Combine half of wine, orange juice, sugar, lemon juice and cinnamon sticks in each of 2 heavy large saucepans.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat.
Peel pears, leaving stems intact.
Cut small slice off bottom of each pear so that pear will stand upright.
Arrange 4 pears on their sides in each saucepan.
Cover and simmer until pears are tender but still hold their shape, turning once, about 15 minutes per side.
Using slotted spoon, transfer pears to upright position in glass baking dish.
Boil cooking liquid in each pan until reduced to 1/2 c., about 9 minutes.
Strain into small bowl.
Cover and chill sauce and pears separately until cold, at least 2 hours or up to 1 day.
Beat cream in large bowl until soft peaks form.
Add Cognac and sugar and beat until stiff peaks form.
Spoon whipped cream into pastry bag fitted with medium star tip.
Transfer pears to upright position on plates. Spoon red wine sauce over.
Pipe whipped cream around pears.

title: cracker salad
directions: Crush crackers.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Chill for about 1 hour.

title: roast beef and gravy
directions: Wash roast real good.
Place in baking bag.
Add cream of mushroom soup and onion soup.
Fasten top of bag with the fastener.
Place in an oblong 2-inch deep pan.
Bake at 350° for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.
Place in deep baking dish.
Slice roast; let sit in gravy and serve.
Wonderful with mashed potatoes.

title: crabmeat mold
directions: Lightly heat mushroom soup and cream cheese until cheese melts.
Add drained crabmeat, mayonnaise, celery, onion and gelatin (dissolved in 1/4 cup boiling water).
Mix together well and pour into 1-quart mold.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: "healthy" chocolate chip cookies
directions: Stir flour, baking soda and salt in a bowl.
In a large mixing bowl, cream butters with sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Mix in oatmeal and chocolate chips.
(Add sunflower seeds or nuts if desired.) Blend in dry ingredients.
Drop by tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken-broccoli bake
directions: Boil chicken breasts for 20 minutes.
Let cool and remove meat from bones.
Place broccoli in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken over top.
Place cheese slices all over top of chicken in a single layer.
Mix together the soup and mayonnaise.
Spread over the top of the cheese. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle onion rings on top and return to oven for 5 minutes.
May be wrapped in aluminum foil and frozen.

title: shrimp mosca
directions: Saute shrimp with herbs and spices in olive oil, stirring regularly, until shrimp are almost done.
Add wine or stock and simmer over very low heat for about 5 minutes, until liquid is about half cooked down.
Serve in shells with lots of paper towels or dampened napkins.
Serves 4 as an appetizer or 2 as a main course.

title: hot stuff
directions: Cook onion in a large skillet until almost tender or transparent.
Add green pepper (both chopped).
Add the meat.
Add salt and crushed pepper; keep stirring so it will not stick. Makes its own juice.
Takes about 1/2 hour.
Serve as a side dish or over buns.

title: cheese-garlic biscuits
directions: Mix baking mix, milk and cheese until soft dough forms.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or golden brown.
Mix butter and garlic powder; brush over warm biscuits.
Serve warm.
Bake at 450°.

title: seven minute brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Line bottom of 8 x 8-inch square glass pan with wax paper.
Bake in a 425° oven for approximately 7 minutes.

title: waffles
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Add eggs, shortening and milk. Beat well.
Stir until smooth.
Heat waffle baker.
Bake batter according to the manufacturer's directions.
Makes 3 large or 6 (7-inch) waffles.
Be sure baker is hot before putting in some batter.
Remove when browned.
Serve with syrup or preserves.
Add some bacon on the side.

title: pink salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix dry jello and cottage cheese.
Add pineapple, then add Cool Whip.
Chill 3 or 4 hours.

title: pineapple surprise
directions: Layer pineapple, cherry pie filling, yellow cake mix and butter.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Put nuts on top about 15 to 20 minutes before removing from oven.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: ranch dip
directions: Combine the 2 ingredients and refrigerate.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Place brown sugar, sugar and milk in a heavy metal pan.
On high, bring to a boil you cannot stir down.
Boil on high for 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir slowly.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter, vanilla and butter or margarine.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: mom's chocolate chip cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, cream margarine and sugars.
Add pudding mix, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour and soda.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Fold in chocolate chips and drop by teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields 4 dozen cookies.

title: glazed peanuts
directions: In a deep pot, dissolve sugar in water.
Add peanuts.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently until all sugar and water has coated peanuts. Put in a flat pan and place in 300° oven for 30 minutes.
Stir every 5 minutes.

title: frozen strawberry preserves
directions: Mix strawberries and sugar in bowl.
Boil Sure-Jell and water for 1 minute in saucepan.
Pour over strawberries.
Stir for 3 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace; add lids.
Let stand at room temperature for 24 hours.
Freeze until firm.
May substitute peaches, blueberries or other fruit for strawberries.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Remove paper from tamales and break tamales into small pieces into saucepan.
Add chili, Velveeta and Worcestershire.
Heat over low heat until cheese is melted, stirring frequently.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add food color.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt together 3 times. Alternate, adding with milk.
Add vanilla.
Dissolve baking soda in vinegar and fold into batter.
Do not beat after adding soda!!! Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes in a Bundt pan.

title: potato latkes(israel)
directions: Grate potatoes and onions.
Add beaten eggs.
Add flour and salt.
Mix well.
Fry in deep fat in frying pan, dropping from tablespoon.
Turn only once.
Drain on paper toweling.
Makes about 3 dozen pancakes.
Tastes great with applesauce or sour cream.

title: galotobouriko
directions: Scald milk.
Add farina slowly, stirring constantly.
Beat eggs and add sugar to them.
Beat thoroughly.
Add to milk mixture slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook until custard begins to thicken.
Add butter, vanilla and salt and stir until butter is melted.
Cool, stirring occasionally, to prevent the custard from forming a crust.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender, but firm.
While cooking, cut up vegetables.
When cooked spaghetti is done, drain and then run under cold water for several minutes so spaghetti is cold.
Drain again.
Place in large bowl.
Add vegetables and dressing after mixing well and add Salad Supreme.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill.
Thin with milk, if necessary. Serve with sliced fresh fruit.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown the meat in a skillet and add to the sauce.
Salt and pepper to taste, if not already done as you prepared the sauce. The sauce must be very liquid, as much of it will be required to soften the noodles.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Brown the pork chops; drain off the fat.
Add onion soup mix, mushroom soup and water; simmer.
Cook noodles; drain and rinse. Put into dish by layers;
first, noodles, then sauerkraut, then meat from gravy.
Pour gravy over all.
Bake at
350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp and broccoli
directions: Preheat wok at medium-high heat for 1 minute.
Pour oil around the top of the wok so as to coat all sides.
Add onion and stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add bell pepper, water chestnuts and mushrooms; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add broccoli, shrimp, wine, sugar and soy sauce.
Stir-fry 3 minutes or until shrimp turn pink.
Now, push shrimp mixture up the sides of the wok and form a well in the center of the wok.
Pour egg whites into the well and stir-fry until egg is set.
Stir shrimp mixture into egg whites.
Add rice and stir-fry 2 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Sweet and sour sauce goes well with this dish.
Serves 4 to 6, depending on how hungry you are!

title: lemon-glazed poppy seed cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add to liquid.
Grease a 13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour half the batter across the bottom.
Sprinkle 1/2 topping over batter.
Spoon cherry pie filling over batter.
Pour remaining batter over filling and sprinkle rest of sugar mixture on top. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add water and oil. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flavoring and poppy seed.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar, egg and molasses.
Sift together the flour, baking soda, salt, cloves, cinnamon and ginger.
Stir into molasses mixture.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Dip tops in granulated sugar.
Place 3 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine, butter, brown sugar, eggs, vanilla and milk and blend well.
Add flour, baking soda, oatmeal and salt and blend.
Raisins, dates or walnuts may be added.
Chill dough two hours or overnight.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Put cooked rice, cooked and drained broccoli, onion, celery and sauteed green pepper in large casserole dish with mushroom soup and cheese soup.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pam's cheese ball
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with rest of ingredients (except pecans).
Shape into a ball and roll in chopped pecans.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all of the ingredients except cornbread stuffing mix. Pour into casserole dish.
Then sprinkle top with stuffing mix. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: ham appetillas
directions: Combine cream cheese, mayo, onions and olives.
Spread thin layer on tortillas.
Arrange 4 slices of ham over cheese mixture. Tightly roll up tortilla.
Wrap individually in plastic wrap. Place in fridge at least 3 hours or overnight.
To serve, cut into 3/4-inch slices.
Makes about 64.

title: champagne salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Blend cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Dip bananas in pineapple juice and then drain.
Mix together strawberries, bananas and pineapple. Add to cream cheese mixture.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze. Defrost in refrigerator 24 hours before serving.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown meat and onion slightly.
Add vegetables and water; bring to a boil.
Add spices and rice.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve topped with sharp grated Cheddar cheese, if desired.

title: chunky chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken well done; let cool.
Take it off the bone and cut in chunks.
Dice celery, onion, grapes and peanuts.
Add to cooled chicken; mix well.
Add mayonnaise and relish.
Mix after each food addition.
Add chopped eggs; mix.
Put in large bowl. Slice 2 eggs; place on top.
Dust with paprika.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Put eggs, sugar, milk, margarine, Bisquick and vanilla in blender; blend 5 minutes.
Add coconut and blend 1 minute.
Pour in buttered 8 to 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cool and refrigerate.
Easy and delicious! Makes its own crust.

title: forgotten chicken
directions: Heat the soup and water.
Spray or grease pan.
Spread rice in bottom of pan.
Place chicken pieces on rice.
Sprinkle dry onion soup mix over all. Pour heated mixture over chicken.
Cover and seal with foil; do not open until cooked.
Bake 2 hours and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate dreams
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine cake mix, water, buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix until well blended.
Add 2 eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition until well blended and smooth. Spoon mixture into greased or paper lined muffin tins, filling each cup 1/2 full.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to boil.
Add peanut butter.
Add Rice Krispies.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: potatoes, peppers and kielbasa casserole
directions: Put all ingredients into large bowl and stir until all coated. Transfer into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Cover with lid or aluminum foil. Bake at 400° for 55 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Blend margarine and eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk to which baking soda has been added.
After completely mixed add 1 c. hot black coffee and 1 tsp.
vanilla. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: bean dip
directions: For Crock-Pot:
Put beans and bacon on to cook overnight. Mash beans and add all the ingredients.
Cook on low 2 or 3 hours. Start on high, end on low.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Coat crackers with chocolate icing. Mix the rest of the ingredients together.
In pan, put a layer of crackers, then pudding mix and end with crackers on top, then top with nuts or crumbs.
Let cool overnight.

title: icebox pie
directions: Melt
in
double
boiler the Hershey bars, marshmallows and milk.
Pour
into crust and top with Cool Whip.
Place in refrigerator and let set well.

title: mimi's blueberry coffee cake(serves 16)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Reduce speed to low.
Add flour, baking powder, lemon peel, salt and eggs.
Beat just until blended, scraping bowl often.
Increase speed and beat until smooth.

title: chocolate chip cheese ball
directions: In a mixing bowl beat the cream cheese, butter and vanilla until fluffy.
Gradually add sugars and beat just until combined. Stir in chocolate chips, cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Put mixture in Saran Wrap and shape into a ball.
Refrigerate for 1 hour and then roll in pecans.
Serve with chocolate graham crackers.

title: white salad
directions: Mix Cool
Whip,
sour cream, Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice. Add other ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Take chunks or strips of chicken and lay in the bottom of casserole dish.
Cook soup, water and butter; put in a pan.
Cook until it melts the butter, then pour over chicken.
Take chunks of bread and add enough chicken broth to flavor your crumbs.
Put this over your chicken mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Wash limas.
Put in pot and cover with water.
Bring to a boil, adding water as needed as it cooks down.
Cook beans approximately 1 hour until completely soft.
Put beans in baking dish (do not strain).
Add ingredients to the pan and stir until brown sugar is dissolved.
Bake 2 hours at 325° to 350°, uncovered, stirring every 1/2 hour.

title: easy microwave fries
directions: Place a sheet of microwave-safe plastic wrap on a micro-safe plate; set aside.

title: butter icing
directions: Bring sugar
and
water
to
soft ball stage.
Pour over flour and
butter, beat until it begins to thicken, then put on cake while it is warm.

title: butter chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl except chips.
Beat all other ingredients
until moist. Stir in chocolate chips to mixture. Shape into small drops. Bake on greased cookie sheet for 25 minutes in oven at 300°. Very easy.

title: christmas gelatin
directions: Combine both packages of Jell-O with boiling water and dissolve.
Add pineapple juice.
Cool.
Add cranberries, apple, crushed pineapple, sugar and nuts.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. (I spray it with Pam.)
Put Cool Whip on top if desired.

title: layered tossed salad
directions: Layer in a large bowl beginning with lettuce.
Spread layer of mayo on very top, sealing edges.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Toss just before serving.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill 2 hours or more.

title: mom's pumpkin pie
directions: Bake at 425° for 45 minutes.
Watch; if browned too fast, turn oven down.
Bake until set.
Makes 2 (8-inch) foil pans.

title: rainbow delight
directions: Prepare all jello separately (except lemon), using 1 cup hot water and 1/2 cup cold water.
Pour each flavor into an 8-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Combine pineapple juice and sugar; heat until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat and stir in lemon jello.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Chill until syrupy or until consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Mix vanilla wafer crumbs and butter.
Press 1 cup of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve 1/2 cup crumbs for the top.
Pour lemon/pineapple mixture into Cool Whip.
Cut jello into 1/2-inch cubes.
Fold the cubes very gently into the Cool Whip mixture.
Carefully pour into pan; sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Chill overnight.

title: veggie rolls
directions: In a small bowl, blend together cream cheese, garlic salt with parsley and lemon pepper. On each tortilla, spread a layer of cream cheese mixture. Layer spinach leaves, Cheddar cheese and carrots over cream cheese; roll up tortillas. Slice each tortilla into 1/2-inch pieces. Serve with salsa. Makes 3 dozen.

title: snapper terra nova
directions: Place fish fillets in glass baking dish.
Pour on lemon juice. Marinate 1 hour.
Combine vinegar, oil, sugar, chilies, jalapeno peppers and garlic in a small bowl.
Set aside.
Combine flour, salt and pepper in medium bowl.
Lightly dredge fillets in flour mixture.
Melt 4 tablespoons butter in large heavy skillet over medium heat.
Add fillets and saute until golden brown and cooked through, 3 minutes per side.
Transfer to platter and keep warm. Add remaining 4 tablespoons butter to same skillet.
Add tomatoes, onions and bell peppers and cook until tender, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes.
Spoon vegetable mixture over fillets and garnish with lemon wedges.
Serve, passing chili mixture separately.

title: mock chicken salad
directions: Cut eggs in half. Grind together all ingredients (except mayonnaise) in food chopper.
Use the fine chopper blade.
Add mayonnaise to make mixture spreading consistency. Good for sandwiches, on crackers or with potato chips as a dip.

title: corn fritter
directions: Mix ingredients and make like pancakes.
Served at the Kutztown Folk Festival.
This can be frozen until you need it. Serve with butter or syrup or both.
Makes about 4 gallons.

title: penuche frosting
directions: Put oleo, brown sugar, white sugar and milk in saucepan and bring to boil.
Boil for 1 minute only.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Beat and let set.
Beat every few minutes, letting it rest a little between beatings.
It will continue to thicken to consistency to spread on cake.

title: marinated vegetable snack
directions: Advance preparation:
In saucepan, simmer carrots, covered, in small amount of water for 2 minutes.
Add broccoli and cauliflower; bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer 3 minutes more.
Drain.
Combine all vegetables.
Combine cooking oil, vinegar, oregano, salt and pepper; pour over vegetables.
Cover. Chill at least 8 hours; stir occasionally.
Makes 4 cups.

title: mom's soft raisin cookies
directions: Combine raisins and water in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cook for 3 minutes; remove from heat and cool (do not drain).
In a mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes at 350°.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: picante corn bread
directions: Combine all and pour into a well greased 8-inch square pan. Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.

title: toffee squares
directions: Place soda crackers on cookie sheet with edge or 10 1/2 x 15 1/2 jelly roll pan. The last row may need to be cut to fill pan. Melt butter and sugar. Bring to boil. Boil 3 minutes, stirring occasionally. Pour over crackers. Cover in all crackers. Bake 5 minutes in 350° oven. Turn off oven. Spread chocolate chips on top of crackers by using a spatula. Cover with chopped nuts. Return to oven until chocolate is melted. Cool. Place cookie sheet in refrigerator until cold. Chocolate should be charred. Cut in squares. Makes 40 to 48 squares. Keeps well in tin in refrigerator.

title: spinach dip
directions: Boil spinach and drain, then add onion and chives while hot! Add mayo; chill and, most of all, enjoy!

title: cinnamon swirl loaf
directions: In large bowl, combine 3 1/2 cups of flour and yeast.
In saucepan heat milk, 1/2 cup sugar, shortening, and salt just until warm, stirring constantly to melt shortening.
Add to dry mixture in mixing bowl.
Add eggs and beat at low speed with electric mixer for 1/2 minute, scraping sides of bowl constantly.
Beat three minutes at high speed.
By hand, stir in enough of the remaining flour to make a moderately soft dough.
Turn out on lightly floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic.
Shape into a ball. Place in lightly greased bowl, turning once to grease surface. Cover; let rise in warm place until double.
Punch dough down and turn out on lightly floured surface.
Divide in half.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes.
Roll each half into a 15 x 7-inch rectangle. Brush entire surface with water.
Combine the 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Spread each rectangle with half the sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Roll dough up as for jelly roll, beginning with narrow side.
Seal long edge and ends.
Place sealed edge down in two greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Cover and let rise in warm place until almost double.
Bake at 375° until done.
Drizzle with icing.

title: jerry's artichoke dip
directions: Start with enough mayonnaise to equal the desired quantity of dip.
Add ingredients to taste.
Mix and refrigerate for several hours before serving for best flavor.
Serve with hot or cold cooked artichokes.

title: lucky if you get a piece
directions: Mix 1st layer together and put in oblong pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: easy homemade ice cream with oreo cookies
directions: In large bowl, beat egg yolks; stir in Eagle Brand, water and vanilla.
Fold in cookies and whipped cream.
Pour into aluminum foil-lined 9 x 5-inch loaf pan or other 2-quart container.
Cover. Freeze 6 hours or until firm.
Scoop ice cream from pan or peel off foil and slice.
Return leftovers to freezer.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Put half of the mixture in a 9 x 12-inch cake pan to set. When firm, spread one small carton sour cream over top.
Put remaining half of gelatin mixture on top.
When set, serve by cutting into squares.

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
If too dry, add more ketchup.
If too moist, add more oats.
Put in pan; spread ketchup on top. Bake at 425° for about 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: chili
directions: Put 1 quart cold water in pot with hamburger meat.
Mash with potato masher until fine.
Cook on low heat for 1 hour, stirring often.
Add seasonings, salt, pepper and sauce.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Good for hot dogs and hamburgers.

title: polish apple pancakes
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, sugar and salt.
In another bowl, lightly beat egg; add milk and oil.
Add to dry ingredients and stir until smooth.
Fold in apples.
Pour batter by 1/2 cupfuls onto a lightly greased hot griddle and spread to form a 5-inch circle.
Turn when bubbles form.
Cook the second side until golden brown and apples are tender.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Makes 14 to 16 pancakes.

title: frosted creams
directions: Grease and flour 10 x 15-inch pan.
Add salt to shortening and mix.
Add sugar gradually and cream it.
Mix in egg and molasses. Sift together flour, baking soda and spices.
Add to first mixture alternating with hot water.
Bake in floured pan for 30 minutes. Let cool and frost with buttercream frosting.

title: orange pecan muffins
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine first 4 ingredients.
Set aside.
Remove the peel from two of the oranges.
Cut all the oranges into eighths and remove seeds; puree in blender or food processor.
If necessary, add enough water to puree to equal 2 cups.
Stir oranges, eggs, oil, cereal and pecans into the dry ingredients.
Blend only until mixed.
Fill greased muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 18 muffins.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour 5 (1 pound) coffee cans.
In a large bowl, beat the eggs.
Add the sugar and beat well.
Add the oil and pumpkin and mix well.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix well. Fill the cans equally with the batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 or 60 minutes.
Turn out onto a cooling rack.
Makes 5 loaves. This bread freezes well.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Make crust using graham cracker crumbs mixed with granulated sugar and melted margarine.
Form crust in an oblong Pyrex dish and bake for 8 to 10 minutes (375°).

title: chicken bake
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam.
Slice onion rings and put in bottom of casserole dish with a couple pats of butter.
Lay chicken in dish.
Mix soups and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not cover.

title: chicken fruit salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together.
Season individual portions into lettuce cups.
Makes approximately 12 servings.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Cook ingredients until it comes to a boil.
Cook 1 minute longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and beat for 1 minute.
Spread on cooled cake layers.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour and baking soda; set aside.
Cream together, in a separate bowl from flour, shortening and peanut butter.
Gradually add sugar and brown sugar.
Cream well.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Roll into teaspoon size balls.
Roll in sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 5 to 8 minutes.
Place chocolate kiss in the middle of each ball and push down lightly until edges crack.
Bake for another 2 to 5 minutes longer.

title: lemon lush
directions: Follow steps like layers:
(1) Melt butter; mix with flour, 1 tablespoon sugar and pecans.
Make into crust.
Butter pan or casserole lightly before spreading with mixture.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Let cool.
(2) Mix and layer cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
(3) Beat until stiff pudding and milk and layer the lemon pudding.
Cover with rest of Cool Whip.

title: lima bean chowder
directions: In Dutch oven, brown meat. Add all other ingredients.
Cover and cook 30 minutes on simmer. Remove cover and cook 15 minutes more. Garnish with parsley and serve.

title: horseradish mayonnaise
directions: Combine egg yolks and seasonings.
Add very small amount of oil and vinegar alternately, beating vigorously until mixture thickens.
Chill.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: molasses cake
directions: Cream lard and sugar together, then add eggs and blend thoroughly.
Add molasses and soda and mix well.
Add flour until stiff enough to roll.
Refrigerate if making them in hot weather in order to handle easier.
Roll out on lightly floured board. Cut out and place on lightly greased and floured sheets.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chili con queso
directions: Brown onions and green peppers until transparent.
Add chilies and jalapenos.
Melt cheeses in the onion mixture.

title: lanelle's sugar cookies
directions: If doubling recipe use 1/2 c. shortening and 1/2 c. butter.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown onion and meat.
Simmer and drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer on low for 20 minutes.
Serve on rolls.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening, peanut butter, sugar, brown sugar and egg well.
Stir and blend in flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt; chill dough.
Roll into walnut-size balls.
Place 3-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork, criss-cross and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: sugar-free banana pudding
directions: Pour milk in large bowl. Add the pudding mixes and beat with mixer about 2 minutes. Gently fold into pudding 2 or 3 large dollops of Cool Whip. Layer cookies, bananas and pudding twice. Top with cookies. Refrigerate.

title: chicken delight
directions: Place chicken in a casserole dish.
Add onion, salt and pepper.
Over this, pour catsup.
Pour Coke over entire casserole (only Coke will work).
Bake in oven 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.
Cover with lid to keep chicken moist.
The Coke and catsup make a barbecue sauce.

title: sherbet pie
directions: Crumble cookies.
Mix the cookies with half of whipped topping.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 12-inch dish.
Spread sherbet, which has been slightly softened, over mixture.
Mix the pecans with remaining half of topping.
Spread over sherbet.
Freeze overnight.
Garnish with lime, lemon, pineapple or orange slices.

title: chicken baked in sherry-cream
directions: Place chicken in shallow dish so that it doesn't overlap. Combine soup, sherry and sour cream; mix well.
Pour over chicken. Shake paprika over it.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: favorite bread and butter pickles
directions: Put pickling spices and celery seed in a spice bag. Combine everything except cucumbers. Bring to boil. Add cucumbers and boil 2 minutes. Remove spice bag. Fill jars and seal. Process in hot water bath 10 minutes. Keep 2 to 3 months before serving.

title: italian baked eggplant
directions: Pare and slice eggplant.
Layer in a shallow baking dish. Layer with onion and green pepper rings.
In small bowl, make sauce with all other ingredients.
Pour over vegetables.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve at lunch or dinner.

title: hot pineapple salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Drain pineapple; reserve 6 tablespoons of juice. Combine sugar, flour and reserved juice. Add pineapple and cheese. Mix well. Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole dish. Combine butter and cracker crumbs; mix well. Sprinkle over prepared mixture. Bake 30 minutes and serve warm or cold.

title: beef stew
directions: Place meat, vegetables, salt
and
pepper
in
pressure cooker or saucepan; cover with water.
Pressure cook for 20 to 30 minutes or
boil
until
tender.
Mix flour and water in a bowl.
Bring meat
mixture
back to a boil.
Slowly add flour mixture (using a strainer) until desired consistency.

title: crusty broiled tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes in half.
Spread cut side with mustard; sprinkle with salt, pepper and cayenne pepper to taste.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix pudding, milk and vanilla.
Cream margarine, cream cheese and sugar; add to pudding mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Crumble cookies real fine.
Put in a clay flowerpot without holes.
First put layer of cookies, then a layer of mixture.
Continue with cookies on top.
Put silk flowers down in pot.
Serve with shovel. Makes a beautiful table piece.

title: canned sweet potatoes
directions: Heat juice from potatoes, brown sugar, salt and margarine. Mix cornstarch with cold water until dissolved (not too thin). Thicken juice mixture with cornstarch.
Put potatoes in a casserole dish.
Pour thickened mixture over the potatoes.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes 15 servings.
For smaller amount, cut recipe in half.

title: jello mold dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Combine all ingredients together.
Pour into mold pan.
Place in refrigerator overnight. Serve.

title: methodist party mix
directions: Mix in a large bowl and enjoy.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Mix milk and water, blend in pudding. Chill for 5 minutes. Fold in cool whip, saving some for top. Layer cookies, then pudding, then strawberries. Spread on rest of cool whip and garnish with a few strawberries.

title: chili verde
directions: Cut meat in bite size pieces.
Brown in oil with chopped onion.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer until meat is done, about 1 1/2 hours. Best done in heavy skillet.
Serve with fry bread.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: In blender, add vinegar, sugar, dry mustard, salt and grated onion.
Blend 5 minutes.
Divide in half and mix with bottom mixture (one-half at a time) the Wesson oil and poppy seed.
Blend 5 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook and drain green beans.
Mix all other ingredients, except stuffing mix.
Pour in a
9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish. Top with stuffing mix and bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: quick easy salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: broccoli chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice in chicken broth.
Saute onion, celery, bell pepper and broccoli.
Mix all together and cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake on greased pan 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown at 350°.

title: nut goody bars
directions: Microwave chocolate chips and peanut butter in 2-quart bowl on Medium 2 to 3 minutes or until melted, stirring after each minute. Fold in marshmallows and raisins.
Pour into foil-lined 8-inch square pan; chill until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Boil spaghetti in salt water until done.
Drain.
Mix in bowl the eggs, cheese, parsley, salt, pepper and margarine.
Mix it in drained spaghetti.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cut up chicken and place in large kettle; cook until tender. Remove meat from bones.
Add water to make 2 quarts.
Combine all ingredients and cook over low heat, about 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.

title: marti's barbecue ribs
directions: Marinate overnight (in refrigerator) in pineapple juice and basil mixture.
Bake in roaster pan at 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours. Then put on grill and coat with barbecue sauce for 15 minutes or so.
Ribs are already done so this just gives them that "grilled" taste and texture.	May put back in oven on "warm" with extra barbecue sauce until ready to serve.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Mix salt, pepper and meal (or use self-rising meal).
Put about 1/4-inch of cooking oil in cast iron skillet.
Heat until sizzling.
Dip tomato slices (both sides) in meal a few at a time. Fry one side at a time until golden brown; drain well on paper towels. Serve hot.

title: chili
