directions: Brown ground beef.
Saute the celery and onion with the ground beef; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and let simmer for 1/2 to 1 hour.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients except baking powder in bowl of electric mixer.
Start mixer on low speed and beat until all ingredients are well blended.
Sprinkle baking powder over batter and beat at medium speed 10 minutes, scraping bowl frequently.
Bake in 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans or a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Put in cold oven, set oven at 350° and bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.
(The top of the cake will crack.)

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Add salt to ground beef; brown and drain off grease.
Add garlic, green pepper and onion.
Cook until golden brown.
Add tomato paste, tomatoes, mushrooms and seasonings.
Stir in Romano cheese.
Cook slowly for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Stir occasionally. Can also put in slow cooker for the day on low heat.
Cook spaghetti noodles when ready to serve.

title: prawns a la cognac
directions: Cut prawns along the back from end to just before the tail, leaving the shell and tail on.
Remove the vein; rinse in cold water and dry with paper towels.
Place 4 tablespoons of the cognac in a bowl and add the prawns.
Mix together until all of the prawns are coated with the cognac.
Marinate 2 hours covered in the refrigerator.
Heat wok on medium-high to high and add the remaining 2 tablespoons of cognac.
With a spatula, coat the wok sides with the cognac.
(See warning at the end.)
With a match, ignite the cognac.
Add the prawns and marinade to the wok and stir-fry until prawns are pink, about 4 to 6 minutes.
Serve on heated platter; pour sauce on small dishes for dipping.

title: mormon split pea soup
directions: Wash split peas in cold water.
Use a 5-quart kettle and combine peas, carrots, 1/2 diced onion and celery and 8 cups water.
Over high heat, bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally. In a 12-inch skillet, over medium heat, cook the remaining celery and onion until tender, stirring occasionally.
With a slotted spoon, remove vegetables and place in a large bowl. Add ground pork, bread crumbs, sage, 2 tablespoons water and 1 teaspoon salt.
Mix well.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Cook meatballs in the drippings over medium heat until browned.
Drain on paper towels. To the split pea mix, add potatoes, pepper and 2 1/2 teaspoons salt.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add meatballs. Cover and continue cooking 15 minutes. Stir occasionally.

title: popeyes
directions: Thaw spinach; remove moisture.
Add all ingredients to spinach, except tortillas.
Spread spinach mixture over flour tortillas.
Roll tortillas up like a jelly roll.
Cut into 1 inch pieces.

title: dijon 'n honey cream sauce
directions: In a medium bowl, combine Grey Poupon, cream, ginger and honey. Beat until stiff.
Fold in pecans.
Serve on sliced fruit.
Makes about 1 1/4 cups.

title: kentucky fry biscuits
directions: Melt the butter in pan while mixing ingredients.
Double ingredients if you want over a dozen biscuits.
Roll out and cut into rounds. Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: coconut spice cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and beat well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour and next 4 ingredients. Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and chopped pecans. Pour batter into 2 greased 9-inch round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool cake layers in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove and frost.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Saute the onion in butter.
Add soup and chicken; bring to a boil.
Add sour cream and stir until well blended.
Dip tortillas in boiling water or chicken broth.
Fill tortillas with one tablespoon of the chicken mixture and a little cheese.
Then roll up.
Pour remaining filling over all and sprinkle with the remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: devine seafood dip
directions: Combine catsup and horseradish (whole jar).
This is the cocktail sauce.
Combine 2/3 of catsup and horseradish combination with softened cream cheese.
Use the mixer to remove lumps.
Put rest of cocktail sauce aside.
Drain one bag of defrosted shrimp. (Remove as much excess water as possible.)
Place mixture into serving dish.
Layer drained crab meat on top.
Place second bag of drained shrimp on top and chill.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: chicken kabobs hawaiian
directions: In a medium nonmetallic bowl, combine all marinade ingredients.
Mix well.
Set aside. Alternate chicken, green pepper, pineapple, onion and tomatoes on 6 (10-inch) skewers. Place kabobs on grill about 8-inches from medium-hot coals.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink, turning and brushing frequently with marinade.
Serve over a bed of rice. Makes 6 servings.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese and potato chips, in casserole.
Add to top the shredded cheese and crushed potato chips.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes in 400° oven.
(I always double recipe.)

title: sweet pepper relish
directions: Note:
Need jars with lid that seal.

title: molasses cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add molasses and beaten eggs. Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with 1 1/2 cups sour milk. Mix soda in the remaining flour.
Floured raisins and currants are added last.

title: quick chocolate peanut butter cookie pops
directions: You will need 10 wooden sticks.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat egg, sugar, shortening and bananas.
Add flour, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Fold in oatmeal, raisins and nuts.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for approximately 12 minutes.
Yield: 4 to 5 dozen.
A delicious, healthy, soft cookie.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cut bread into small squares.
In casserole dish layer bread. Brown and drain sausage; layer sausage after bread.
Mix other ingredients and pour on top.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Next morning bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: In large skillet, fry bacon until crisp; remove and set aside. Cook chopped onion in the bacon drippings until tender. Stir in flour and blend until smooth.
Add vinegar and water; cook until slightly thick.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Crumble in bacon and the sliced, cooked potatoes.
Heat through, stirring lightly, to coat all the potatoes.
Serve warm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fruit strata salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, place half of the lettuce.
Layer fruits atop lettuce.
Top with remaining lettuce.
Spread yogurt over top.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Cover and chill 2 to 3 hours.
Toss gently to serve.
Makes 12 servings.

title: creamed peas(microwave)
directions: In 1-quart glass casserole, melt butter (High) 30 to 45 seconds.
Blend with flour, cream substitute, salt and pepper. Add undrained peas.
Microwave (High) 5 to 6 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes until hot and slightly thickened.
Boiled onions are very good in this sauce!

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat in butter.
Remove meat from skillet and saute chopped onion, mushrooms and garlic.
Brown lightly.
Stir in beef broth, cover and simmer 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Stir occasionally.
When done, gradually stir in sour cream and cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: microwave peanut clusters
directions: Combine chocolate, butterscotch and peanut butter morsels in a 2-quart casserole.
Heat on Full power for 2 minutes or until melted.
Stir halfway through heating time; stir in peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let set until firm.
Store in refrigerator.
If mixture hardens before dropped onto wax paper, return to microwave and heat 1 to 2 minutes or until soft.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice according to directions.
Saute onions and celery in butter.
Mix in rest of ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered.

title: stuffed chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts on bottom of buttered casserole dish. Place a piece of Swiss cheese on top of each piece of chicken. Add white wine to chicken soup; stir until mixed and pour over chicken and cheese.
Spread stuffing crumbs over top of soup; before you spread crumbs, roll over them with a rolling pin to make pieces smaller.
Drizzle melted butter over top of crumbs. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add pumpkin, egg and vanilla. Add dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Ice with favorite icing.

title: corn dogs
directions: Combine flour, cornmeal, sugar, mustard, baking powder and salt.
Add milk, egg and butter.
Mix until smooth.
Put wieners on skewers.
Dip wieners one at a time in cornmeal batter.
Fry until golden brown in vegetable oil.
Drain on paper towels.

title: low calorie chocolate fruit dip(low-fat)
directions: In small mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Blend in powdered sugar, cocoa, milk and extract.
Beat on medium speed of electric mixer until smooth.
Cover; refrigerate several hours or overnight for flavors to blend.
Just before serving, wash and dry fruit; cut into serving size pieces, if necessary (brush bananas with lemon juice to prevent browning).
Serve dip well chilled; refrigerate leftovers.

title: tallareni
directions: Using a big pot, cook the beef, garlic, onions and bell peppers
in a small amount of olive oil for 10 minutes.
(Beef will create additional fat.)
Add the chili powder, tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Add the corn, olives and the boiled egg noodles. Toss ingredients together well.
Pour into 2 flat baking dishes (9 x 13-inch).
Top with the grated cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven until cheese is slightly brown on top (about 35 to 40 minutes).
Serves 14 to 15.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast and lukewarm water together.
Mix butter or margarine, flour, Crisco, egg and sugar together.
Mix all ingredients together and spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake for 20 minutes at 425°.
Will keep in the refrigerator for a week or two.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and put spinach in a sieve.
Press to remove water thoroughly.
Mix rest; fold in spinach.
Cover; refrigerate for 24 hours.
Makes 3 cups, 35 calories per tablespoon.

title: caramel corn
directions: *Corn popped in air popper works very well.

title: debbie's aunt's cake
directions: Position a rack in the center of the oven and preheat to 350°. Lightly butter and flour a 12-cup fluted tube pan.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all together and cook until done.

title: corn pone pie
directions: Brown chopped onion in skillet.
Add meat and brown this also and Ranch Style beans and canned tomatoes.
Simmer for about 15 minutes.
Pour into 9 x 11-inch casserole or larger.
Pour cornbread batter over this mixture and bake about 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan (or sheet pan).
Bake 40 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: spicy meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into balls, any size. Small for cocktail meatballs, larger for entrees.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Mix last 3 ingredients together; pour over chicken.
Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Works best in a glass dish in which the chicken just fits.

title: green beans oriental
directions: Drain beans.
Saute onion in butter until soft.
Add flour and blend.
Slowly add milk and cheese; cook until smooth and thick, stirring constantly.
Add seasonings.
Stir in cooked or canned beans, mushrooms and chestnuts.
Sprinkle almonds over top and bake, uncovered, at 375° until bubbly.
Makes 8 to 10 servings. This can be made the day before, but don't put almonds on until you put it into the oven.

title: impossible pie
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender until well mixed.
Use 1/8 cup of butter to coat a 10-inch pie pan.
Flour well.
Pour in blended ingredients and bake at 350° for about 50 minutes or until an inserted knife blade comes out clean.

title: nacho dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat.
Use for tortilla chips or pretzels.
Best way to cook and serve is in a slow cooker or crock-pot.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Brown meat with onions and spices.
Drain.
Add soup and beans.
Line bottom and sides of a 9 x 13-inch pan with tortillas, having them extend slightly above the sides.
Pour half of the meat mixture into dish, cover with a layer of cheese, then remaining meat mixture.
Use cheese and olives to decorate top of casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until cheese on top melts.
(Slices of jalapeno pepper can also be used to decorate top.)

title: glazed fruit
directions: Pour 2 cups of juice from canned fruits over pudding mix and cook until thick, stirring often.
Let cool.
Fold in canned fruit and refrigerate.
Add fresh fruits before serving.

title: cream of broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Cook altogether until broccoli is tender.
Add 1 1/2 cups shredded Cheddar cheese to soup and boil, stirring constantly. Thicken to desired consistency with water and flour.

title: sweet and sour meatball appetizers
directions: Form meat mixture into 40 meatballs using a rounded teaspoonful for each.
Brown meatballs lightly in 1 tablespoon vegetable oil. Cover and cook over low heat for 5 minutes. Drain excess fat.
Combine the chili sauce and jelly.
Pour over meatballs.
Heat, stirring until jelly is melted. Simmer 10 to 12 minutes until sauce thickens; baste occasionally.
Makes 40 appetizer meatballs.

title: raisin oatmeal molasses drop cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar. Add molasses and egg.
Blend. Add dry ingredients.
Add oats and raisins.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
This makes a moist, tangy chewy cookie.

title: frank's gourmet low-fat oven crispy chicken and chops
directions: The first thing you do is take the chicken breasts or the pork chops and remove all traces of excess fat.
Take your time and trim it all away with a sharp paring knife.

title: jumbles(make with m&m's mini baking bits)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, beat butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add egg.
Combine flour and baking soda; blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in M&M's mini baking bits, raisins and nuts.

title: crusty fried chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
Soak in buttermilk overnight.
Next day, place flour, salt and pepper in a paper bag.
Put in chicken pieces and shake until coated.
Fry in medium grease until brown and crisp.
You may substitute for the buttermilk 3 tablespoons vinegar added to regular milk.
Let sit 3 or 4 minutes until thick.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown ground meat; drain.
Put first 10 ingredients together. Cook until vegetables are tender, 30 to 45 minutes.
Add macaroni and cheese.
Cook 15 minutes more.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients, cutting in shortening until fine crumbs. Add milk and stir with a fork until dough leaves sides of bowl. Turn dough out onto lightly floured board.
Knead just until smooth.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with floured cutter.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until brown.
Makes a dozen biscuits.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut
beef
into
small cubes, potatoes into fourths and onions to desired size.
Tomatoes may be cut into small pieces also.
Put into
large
pot
and
cook over medium heat until potatoes are done.
Serve.

title: frozen brandy alexanders
directions: Mix all together and freeze.
When ready, scoop into glasses and enjoy.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Mix peanut butter, margarine, vanilla and 4 tablespoons powdered sugar and flour. Mix well, then add nuts. Bake and immediately roll each "cake" in more powdered sugar.

title: cowboy cornbread
directions: Mix cornbread mix and corn together.
In skillet, cook ground beef, celery, bell pepper and taco seasoning together.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan as follows:
1/2 cornbread mixture, ground beef mixture, shredded cheese and remaining cornbread mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: jerky
directions: Mix all ingredients and add meat.
Let soak overnight.
Place on wire oven racks with foil on lower rack to catch excess juice when cooking.
Let dry in oven on warm temperature for 5 to 7 hours or until desired consistency.

title: roast
directions: Wash roast.
Salt and pepper.
Batter in flour; put in roasting pan.
Add water (almost to top of roast).
Cover; cook in a 350° oven until tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Take from oven.
Add potatoes, cut lengthwise.
Add carrots.
Cover; put back in oven and cook until potatoes are tender, about 30 minutes.

title: german fudge wundebars
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch baking pan with foil.
Melt butter in a prepared pan.
Combine brown sugar, nuts, coconut and evaporated milk; spread over butter in pan.
In a large mixer bowl, blend cheese and egg.
Measure 1 2/3 cups frosting mix by lightly spooning into cup and leveling off.
Gradually add frosting mix to cheese mixture.
Mix until well blended.

title: southern corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain liquid off whole corn.
Melt butter in small pan.

title: shrimp-tomato aspic-salad
directions: Boil onion and tomato juice 3 minutes.
Strain and pour over jello.
Add hot water and vinegar.
Let cool to jello consistency. Add celery, olives and shrimp.
Pour in mold and chill.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and dry mushrooms. Remove stems. Lay caps upside down in well buttered baking dish.

title: irish bread
directions: Cream
butter and sugar; add eggs.
Beat until mixed, then add sour cream and stir well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to sour cream
mixture.
Beat or stir until well mixed.
Fold in raisins. Makes 2 loaves (fill pans about half full).
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Enjoy!

title: home cooked salad dressing
directions: Combine ingredients and cook until thick, then add 2 tablespoons mustard and cool.
Just before using, add 1/2 cup heavy cream.
Mayonnaise may be substituted for cream.
If an individual's diet precludes the use of mayonnaise, condensed milk may be substituted.
Basic dressing (before cream, mayonnaise, milk) may be stored in refrigerator for weeks.

title: grannies fruit cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Boil gently for 3 minutes, then cool in large mixing bowl.
Add mixed fruit and nuts.
Beat in eggs.
Sift in flour and
add cinnamon, nutmeg, baking powder, salt and soda.
Beat well after each addition.
Pour into tube pan and bake in very slow oven at 275° for 2 1/2 hours or until completely done.

title: hawaiian baked beans and franks
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Combine pineapple with remaining ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for an hour.

title: peter pans
directions: Put chips, butter and peanut butter into an 8 x 12-inch glass baking dish.
Microwave 2 to 3 minutes, until everything is melted.
Stir well.
Cool, then add marshmallows and peanuts. Refrigerate.
When firm, cut into squares.
Makes 48 pieces or more.

title: green pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in salad bowl.
Mix gently. Chill before serving.

title: ambrosia
directions: Place orange juice in mixing bowl.
Add water as directed on can.
Peel, core and coarsely grate apples and bananas.
Add to juice.
Add crushed pineapple, coconut and sugar.

title: scorpion
directions: Build in bucket glass with crushed ice.
Garnish with red cherry and orange slice.

title: swiss chicken bundles
directions: Cook lasagna noodles, rinse and drain.

title: special blueberry muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
In large bowl mix other ingredients except berries.
Add dry ingredients and mix just until all is moistened.
Add berries.
Fill greased muffin tins (1 dozen).
Sprinkle generously with granulated sugar.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and salt.
Drain.
Place beef and onion in a 2-quart dish.
Spread soup over it.
Place Tater Tots on top. Cover with cheese.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: garden pizza
directions: Roll out crescent rolls on a jelly roll pan to make a rectangle. Bake at 400° for 11 to 13 minutes. Cool. Mix mayonnaise, Ranch mix and cream cheese. Spread on crescent rolls and top with chopped veggies. Slice into squares.

title: josephine deceglie's lamb chop bake(michael deceglie's grandmother's recipe)
directions: Sprinkle bottom of large roast pan or baking dish lightly with oil.
Next, add half the crushed garlic, a little parsley, rosemary, salt, pepper and half the diced tomatoes.
Then place shoulder lamb chops on top.
Next, layer cubed potatoes, followed by drained mushrooms.
Sprinkle with another layer of crushed garlic, parsley, rosemary, salt, pepper and diced tomatoes.
Top off lightly with Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs; sprinkle with oil.
Add water until bottom of pan is covered with about 1/2 inch.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli until slightly tender; drain and place in a 9 x 13-inch glass casserole.
Set aside while making sauce.
In a saucepan, melt cream cheese and blend in milk, Parmesan cheese, salt and garlic salt.
Pour over broccoli and sprinkle with paprika and almonds.
Bake 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Cream egg yolks, sugar and flour, pineapple, butter and salt. Cook in double boiler.
Add coconut with other ingredients, if desired.
Use for pie or cake filling.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place thawed potatoes in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: french vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt; stir in milk.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly until slightly thickened.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes.
Stir a little hot milk into eggs, then stir into remaining hot milk.
Cook over hot (not boiling) water, stirring constantly for 5 minutes or until mixture coats the spoon.
Remove from hot water. Chill.
Add vanilla and cream. Freeze.
I put chopped fruit in just before I put it in the ice cream freezer.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute garlic, onion, green pepper and celery.
Cook until tender, about 10 minutes.
Add flour and sugar and stir.
Add stewed tomatoes, Tabasco sauce, wine, salt, chili powder, thyme and bay leaf.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add shrimp.
Serve over rice.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread pecans and coconut on bottom of pan.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions; pour over pecans and coconut.
Mix melted margarine, softened cream cheese and sugar together; pour over cake batter.
Bake for 1 hour, or until cake is brown.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Break cauliflower and broccoli into flowerets, using as much of stems as desired.
Chop or cut small onion.
Mix remaining ingredients well and toss with cauliflower and broccoli.
Will serve 8 or more.
For one person or a small number, halve recipe for dressing and add to vegetables as desired.

title: peanut butter crunch candy
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a rolling boil; remove from heat. Add peanut butter and flavoring; stir to blend.
Pour over corn flakes and peanut mixture.
Pack into a 9 x 13-inch pan while warm.
Cut into squares.

title: super bowl chili
directions: Brown onions, garlic and meat in large pot.
Dump everything else in and simmer about 5 hours.
Will serve 14 to 16 men. Freezes well.

title: mac-n-cheese puff
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water about 10 minutes; drain. In saucepan, combine egg yolks, milk, butter, mustard, onion, 1/4
teaspoon
salt and a dash of pepper.
Add cheese. Cook
and stir over medium heat about 10 minutes (until thickens
but
do not
boil).
Stir
in macaroni and bread crumbs. Fold
in egg whites.
Pour half the mixture into a 1 1/2-quart souffle dish. Reserve a few
slices of franks for top.
Place remaining franks in	casserole.
Pour
on
remaining
macaroni mixture.
Put remaining franks on
top.
Bake
at
350° for 45 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: calla lily sandwiches
directions: Combine almonds and food coloring in a jar; cover with lid and shake vigorously until almonds are evenly coated.
Roll each slice of bread to 1/8-inch thickness with a rolling pin; cut with a 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter.
Combine cream cheese and marmalade; spread about 1 teaspoon on each bread round.
Pinch the edges of one portion of the circle together to form a calla lily.
Press a tinted slivered almond into the pinched portion to represent the flower's stamen.
Yields 4 1/2 dozen.

title: california chili
directions: Cook all ingredients together except rice. Serve chili over cooked rice.

title: crab fritters
directions: Drain crabmeat.
Mix together all ingredients, except crabmeat and mayonnaise.
Add drained crabmeat; mix.
Add and blend in mayonnaise last.
Fry in melted margarine over medium heat.
Brown on both sides.
Serve at once.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Place sauerkraut in 1 1/2-quart glass casserole.
Top with corned beef and shredded cheese.

title: dumpit cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread applesauce in pan.
Dump in crushed pineapple (including juice).
Spread evenly.
Spread dry cake mix on top.
Pour melted margarine over cake mix.
Sprinkle chopped nuts.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with whipped cream, Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream.

title: chocolate-peanut clusters
directions: Combine peanut butter, butterscotch and chocolate morsels in a heavy saucepan.
Place over low heat and cook, stirring constantly, until melted.
Stir in peanuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto waxed paper.
Chill until firm, about 10 minutes.
Store in a covered container in refrigerator.
Yield:
about 4 dozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes and drain.
Mix soup, egg, mayonnaise, onion and cheese.
Place broccoli in greased casserole dish.
Pour mix over broccoli and place crushed crackers on top. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 cup Cheddar cheese, 3 tablespoons of onions and garlic.
Spread onto bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Mix picante and tomato; spread over cheese mixture.
Sprinkle remaining Cheddar cheese and onion. Serve with tortilla chips. Serves 8 to 10.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well and pour into large baking dish.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni noodles until tender; drain.
Melt margarine in noodles while hot.
Grate cheese; beat eggs in milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Layer noodles and cheese in baking dish.
Pour egg/milk mixture over noodles.
Bake 30 minutes in 400° oven.

title: cool carrots
directions: Slice carrots.
Cook in salted water for 5 minutes; drain. Combine all other ingredients and bring to boil.
Pour over carrots.
Can be eaten warm but are much better refrigerated until completely chilled.

title: banana bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour jelly roll pan.
Mix sugar, sour cream, butter and eggs on medium speed.
Beat in bananas and vanilla and then add in flour gradually.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; refrigerate and serve.

title: almond pound cake
directions: Beat first four ingredients on high for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until smooth. Pour in floured, greased tube pan. Put in a cold oven.
Turn heat on at 325° and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sweet 'n sour meatballs
directions: Brown meatballs.
Cook cornstarch, vinegar and sugar until clear.
Add rest of ingredients and heat.
Add meatballs.
Serves 16.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven at 400°.
Cook macaroni until done, drain and pour into an oblong baking dish.
Top with sliced Velveeta cheese. Sprinkle with sharp Cheddar cheese.
Mix egg and milk in glass and beat well.
Pour over cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Place ingredients in large glass bowl.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Chop cooked chicken and place in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish. Make sauce by heating the cream of chicken soup, margarine and milk. Stir to mix thoroughly and pour over chicken. Layer with eggs and onion. Cover with stuffing.
Pour 2 1/2 cups broth over top. Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries, sugar and pineapple.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Add marshmallows and apple.
Fold in Cool Whip and walnuts (if desired).

title: barbecue
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: date pinwheels
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together.
Add eggs; beat well. Mix the dry ingredients together.
Add to the creamed butter, sugar and eggs.
Divide the dough into 3 parts and wrap in wax paper.
Chill overnight.
(This makes it easier to spread the filling on the dough.)

title: mango jello salad
directions: Bring 1 cup of water to boil.
Add jello and cook one minute. In blender or food processor, put cream cheese and mangos, including juice.
Blend until very, very smooth.
Add to jello mixture.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and coat with egg and Bisquick. Fry at 400° until brown and place on paper towels in oven at 250°. Combine sugar, cornstarch and paprika in skillet.
Drain pineapple and add water to juice to make 2 cups.
Add pineapple, soy sauce and vinegar to sugar mixture.
Cook until it boils and let boil 1 minute.
Add green pepper and onions and cook 5 minutes.
Add pineapple, tomatoes and chicken.
Serve over hot white rice.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Beat egg yolks; gradually add sugar, salt, cornstarch and butter.
Add scalded milk.
Cook and stir over very low heat. Stir constantly until thickens.
Stir in coconut.
Cool and add vanilla.
Cool completely and pour into baked pie shell.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook carrots and onions first, then add squash for final 5 minutes.
Combine soup and sour cream.
In a separate dish, combine butter and stuffing mix.
Take 1/2 squash mixture and put in bottom of casserole, then add 1/2 stuffing mixture.
Alternate layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: chocolate clair cake
directions: Make pudding as directed.
Add Cool Whip.
Layer graham crackers or wafers on bottom of baking dish.
Put 1/2 pudding mixture over crackers.
Form another layer of crackers.
Pour remaining pudding mixture over crackers.
Form another layer of crackers.
Frost with chocolate frosting.
Refrigerate.

title: olive-cheese balls
directions: Mix cheese, margarine, flour and paprika.
Chill.
Mold about 1/2 teaspoon of mixture around dry olives.
Chill again.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: barney's chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and the cocoa together 3 times.
Cream the sugar and shortening until light and fluffy; add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add the dry ingredients alternately with the sour milk and vanilla; beat for another 4 minutes.
Turn into a 13 x 9-inch pan, which has been greased and floured.
Bake in a moderate oven at 325° until done (30 to 40 minutes).
Cool, frost and serve.
Makes 20 generous servings.

title: fiddlehead casserole
directions: Saute together the onion, chopped bacon and mushrooms.
Boil 1 quart of fiddleheads until tender (about 15 minutes).
Mix all ingredients together.
Top with 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and 1 cup bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake until brown in a 350° oven.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Drain pineapple and set aside.
Whip heavy cream until fluffy, then add pineapple, cherries and marshmallows.
Chill until cool and firm.

title: old fashioned pumpkin pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together with beater.
Pour mixture into lined 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 400° until tests done when silver knife comes out clean (45 to 55 minutes).
Center of pie will be soft, but will set as it cools.

title: ramen noodle oriental
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Saute onions, celery, mushrooms and soy sauce in butter.
Add salt and pepper.
Bring noodles to a boil. Boil 3 to 4 minutes; drain.
Serve by making a noodle bed.
Place beef mixture on top.
Serve hot.
Fast meal.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cover chicken with water; cook until done.
Remove chicken from bones.
Put in casserole dish.
Cover with can of celery soup (not diluted with water or milk).
Cover chicken and soup with dressing. Cover this with broth until all is moistened.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: apple raisin muffins
directions: Beat eggs; stir in remaining ingredients, mixing just to moisten.
Pour into 12 greased muffin cups until 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form into balls and store in freezer.
Thaw and roll out dough as needed.

title: slaw
directions: Grate cabbage and carrots.
Mix together all ingredients to taste.

title: peach pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place butter in a glass baking dish. Let melt while mixing flour, sugar and baking powder. Add milk, stirring to form a smooth paste.
Remove baking dish from the oven.
Spoon flour mixture over the butter, then pour juice and peaches over top of the mixture; do not stir.
Place in oven and bake 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: fudge
directions: Put sugar in heavy pot.
Mix in cocoa.
Add water and mix very well.
Cook on medium heat for 5 minutes.
Let mixture come to rolling boil.
Add condensed milk and butter.
Lower heat and stir continuously until mixture comes to soft ball stage (250°) on a candy thermometer.
Add vanilla.
Remove from heat.
Whip with hand mixer until smooth and creamy.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased 7 x 11-inch pan.
Allow to cool.
Cut in bite size pieces.

title: golden carrots
directions: Slice and cook carrots in water.
Add sugar and butter. Simmer until carrots are glazed.
Add a little cinnamon.

title: the beaver club banana bread(makes 2 loaves, 8 x 4 x 3-inch)
directions: Preheat oven to 275° and place the shelf in the middle.
Line the loaf pans with buttered parchment paper or grease and flour.

title: zucchini bread(makes 2 loaves.)
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Wrap well in foil; keeps in freezer a long time.

title: scotcharoos
directions: Combine white Karo and syrup and bring to a boil; remove from stove.
Add peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt chips and spread over top.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Dice broccoli; add chopped nuts, crumbled bacon and sliced onion.

title: light salad dressing("the jar")
directions: Soak cut up onion and garlic in vinegar for 20 minutes. Strain.
Add to all remaining ingredients.
Mix and shake well. Delicious with any green salad or pasta salad.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix and pour in pie shells.
Chill.

title: gingerbread
directions: Sift together flour, spices, soda and salt.
Cream together shortening and sugar.
Gradually add molasses to shortening and sugar mixture and stir in 1/2 cup of dry mixture.
Beat in egg. Add milk alternately with the remaining dry ingredients.
Pour batter into well-greased and lightly floured 8-inch pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in large bowl; stir until blended. Add ground beef and mix well.
Pack in 9 x 5-inch loaf pan and spread taco sauce on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour. Sprinkle cheese on top of meat loaf and bake an additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add frozen spinach and soup mix.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Beat baking mix, eggs, milk and salt until smooth.
Stir in broccoli and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Stir thawed berries, eggs and oil together.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and nuts.
Add berry mixture to dry ingredients and stir until blended.
Bake 1 hour or until done.

title: cool lime salad
directions: In a small saucepan, bring pineapple to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Cool to room temperature.
Stir in cottage cheese and whipped topping, chill until set.
Yields 1 serving.

title: traditional irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a baking sheet or line with parchment.
In a large bowl, stir the first 5 ingredients together.
In a separate bowl, beat the eggs, buttermilk and oil together.
Make a well in the center of the dry ingredients and pour in the buttermilk mixture.
Add the caraway seeds and raisins.
Stir until soft dough is formed.
Shape the dough into a large ball on a lightly floured board.
Flour hands for easier handling.
With a sharp knife, make a cross on the top.
Place on the prepared pan.
Brush the top with milk.
Bake in the center of the oven until golden brown, 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool before slicing.

title: cream pull candy
directions: Cook to 258° with candy thermometer. Pour onto buttered marble slab. When cool enough to handle, pull with hands, cold but dry. Shape into strips and cut into pieces.

title: easy apple butter(made in a crock-pot)
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on high 4 1/2 hours.
Remove cover and cook additional 4 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Pour into clean sterilized pint jars and seal.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll
into
small balls.	Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Roll
in powdered sugar while hot. Roll again when cool.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: pumpkin pie supreme(this is a different pumpkin pie recipe to try.)
directions: In a large bowl, mix well all ingredients, except nutmeg. Pour into an unbaked pie shell and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: fish roll dinner
directions: Cook asparagus and rice as directed on packages.
Place 4 to 6 asparagus spears on fillets and roll up, starting from narrow end. Place rolls, seam side down, in baking dish.
Brush with margarine. Sprinkle with lemon pepper.
Bake at 375° until fish flakes easily (about 18 to 20 minutes).

title: apple squash yam bake
directions: Spread a layer of potatoes, squash, and apples in the bottom of buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with some brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Pour a little melted butter over top.
Repeat 1 or 2 more layers of the same.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Top with mini marshmallows and bake 30 minutes longer, till veggies are done and marshmallows light golden brown.

title: broccoli chowder
directions: Pour chicken broth in kettle; add broccoli.
Slow boil until broccoli is just tender (10 to 15 minutes).
Remove broccoli and set aside.
To broth, add milk, ham, cream, Swiss cheese and butter.
Coarsely chop broccoli; add to chowder.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add salt and garlic to taste.
May add a little cornstarch mixed with broth to soup if a thicker base is desired. Feeds 6 (approximately).

title: country style ribs
directions: Note: This recipe requires cooking 1 day ahead of time.

title: glazed onions and carrots
directions: Place
carrots	in
large
saucepan with 1-inch boiling water. Cover and simmer 10 minutes. Add onions. Cover and cook 5
minutes longer
or until vegetables are just tender. Drain and
return to	saucepan.
Add	Shedd's Spread Country Crock, brown
sugar, ginger and salt, stirring frequently.
Cook over medium
heat
5 minutes or until vegetables are glazed.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: vegetable beef barley soup
directions: Using a 5
or
6-quart pot bring to a boil, then simmer bones, steak, onions and bay leaves in about 4 quarts of water for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
(While doing this, cook barley.) Remove steak and bones.
Add vegetables, celery, cabbage and tomatoes and simmer about 20 minutes.
Shred or dice the meat, then add meat and barley.
Add
bouillon
cubes
if stronger flavor is desired.
(I usually
make this soup the night before it's to be eaten.)

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine cream cheese and sugar; beat until smooth.
Add eggs and beat until well mixed; pour into crust.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: nut strudel
directions: Bring cream cheese and butter to room temperature, then beat with a mixer.
Add flour and mix well.
Shape into ball; cover and chill for 1 to 2 hours.
Meanwhile, cook sugar and milk over medium heat until milk boils and sugar dissolves, stirring occasionally.
Stir in nuts.
Cool until spreadable.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: You will also need wax paper and toothpicks.

title: pecan pie
directions: Prepare pie shell and arrange pecan halves in bottom.
Beat eggs in bowl and add butter or margarine, corn syrup and vanilla and stir until well blended.
Combine sugar and flour and blend with egg mixture.
Pour over nuts in pie shell.
Let stand until pecans rise to surface.
Nuts will glaze during baking.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 45 minutes.

title: carrot plum pudding #1
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Grind with medium grinder all raw vegetables including raisins.
Mix all together with hands.
Steam in tight covered steamer or other pan which can be used for 1 1/2 hours on top of stove.
Put in slow oven (preheated) for about 15 minutes to dry.
Serve piping hot with following dressing.

title: ozark pudding pie
directions: Beat egg until light.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in flour sifted with baking powder and salt.
Add vanilla, nuts and apples, stirring until just blended.
Bake in greased pie pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: pig cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in 3 pans according to cake directions.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Grease an 8-inch square pan.
In a saucepan bring sugar and milk to a boil; boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat, add peanut butter and marshmallow cream; mix well.
Quickly pour into the greased pan.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: orange juice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Put chopped nuts in bottom of the pan.
Mix all ingredients well and put in pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: papa's salsa
directions: Place onion, peppers and the juice from 3 cans of tomatoes into blender and liquify.
Add whole tomatoes into blender and run on low speed for a few seconds, leave tomatoes slightly chunky.
Pour into large mixing bowl.
Blend remaining tomatoes in same manner and add to mixture.
Add salt, and garlic powder and stir well. You can add salt, garlic, and pepper to taste.
Refrigerate in closed container.

title: ultimate nacho dip
directions: Spread bean dip in a greased 8-inch baking dish, top with onions.
Cook hamburger and drain, mix in taco seasoning and tomato sauce and spread over onion and bean dip.
Top with green chilies.
Bake at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Spread cheese over top and bake another 15 minutes.
Serve with Tostitos or your favorite chip.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix pineapple with marshmallows; set aside.
Blend together flour, vinegar, egg, sugar and juice.
Cook over medium heat until thickened; cool.
Core and chop apples; add to pineapple and marshmallows.
Add sauce and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip. Refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: quick pizza dip(preparation time: 5 minutes. cooking time: 20 minutes.)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat cream cheese and seasonings with electric mixer until well blended.
Spread on bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Top with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, pizza sauce, then remaining Mozzarella cheese and peppers.
Bake 20 minutes or until mixture is thoroughly heated and cheese is melted.
Serve with bread sticks.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: pear cake
directions: Mix pears, nuts and sugar.
Let stand 1 hour.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to pear mixture.
Stir in oil and well beaten eggs.
Add vanilla.
Mix with wooden spoon.
Pour in greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: creamy shrimp
directions: Shell and devein shrimp.
Cook and drain.
Melt butter and saute mushrooms until wilted, but still white.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Heat oil and mix with all ingredients.
Put crackers in airtight container with oil and shake.

title: chicken bombay
directions: Combine brown sugar, ginger, sherry and soy sauce.
Marinate chicken 1/2 to 1 hour in sauce.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cook in sauce, uncovered, until tender and brown, 1 hour at 350°.
Good Party dish.
Amount of chicken can be reduced to suit.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin until fluffy.
Stir flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and baking soda.
Add to pumpkin mixture and mix thoroughly.
Bake in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: nippy franks
directions: Combine all ingredients except cocktail wieners in crock-pot. Stir wieners into sauce mixture.
Cover and heat 1 hour; remove lid and heat an additional hour.

title: aunt mary's virginia corn bread(year 1900)
directions: Sift together the flour, corn meal, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Rub in the lard cold; add the eggs and then the milk. Mix into a moderately stiff batter; pour it into well-greased, shallow baking pans (pie tins are suitable).
Bake from 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hot fruit compote(excellent for brunch or with ham.)
directions: Layer all ingredients in order in a souffle dish.
Cook 1 1/2 hours at 350°, covered. Remove cover and cinnamon stick. Serve warm.

title: snowball cake
directions: Add gelatin slowly to the boiling water, stirring constantly until dissolved.
Add sugar, pineapple, salt and lemon juice. Tear cake into pieces and stir in with pineapple mixture, being sure to wet cake thoroughly.
Whip 2 packages Dream Whip, according to package directions, and pour into cake mixture. Stir.
Pour into large dish.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In a large skillet over medium high heat, cook meat and onion until meat is brown, stirring constantly.
Drain off fat.
Add tomatoes and remaining ingredients.
Simmer over medium-low heat for 30 minutes.
Spoon mixture in buns.
Serves 4.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat together.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot, greased skillet. Saute on one side until golden brown.
Turn and cook on other side.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve at once.
Great with maple syrup.

title: spinach salad
directions: You can use any ripe orange; navels have no seeds.

title: german potato pancakes
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain.
Coarsely shred potatoes.
Stir in egg, onions, salt, pepper and flour.
Put mixture in sieve, press with spoon for starch to drain.
Add crumbled bacon.
Form into patties.
Fry patties in hot grease 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown, turning once.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix together flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon, salt, baking powder and cocoa.
In another bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Stir zucchini mixture into flour mixture.
Grease well and lightly flour 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans; divide mixture evenly between the loaf pans. Bake for 1 hour or unitl wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes on a rack, then remove from pan. Cool completely before slicing.

title: pickle peaches
directions: Put spices in bag and mix, then mix everything and boil for 20 minutes.
Peel approximately 4 quarts peaches and put in boiling mixture slowly, then put into jars and seal.

title: vegetarian lasagna(diabetic)
directions: Rinse the spinach well.
Cook the spinach in a covered saucepan without water except for the drops that cling to the leaves.
Reduce the heat when the steam forms and cook 3 to 4 minutes more.
Cook the lasagna noodles in boiling unsalted water and drain.
Cook the mushrooms, carrots and onions in a saucepan in hot oil until tender, but not brown.
Stir in the tomato and spices.
Simmer for at least 20 minutes.
In a sprayed baking dish, layer as follows, noodles, cottage cheese, spinach, cheese and sauce mixture.
Repeat the layers, reserving several cheese slices for the top.
Then sprinkle the top with grated Parmesan. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let the lasagna cool for 10 minutes before serving.

title: martin's loaf
directions: Have butcher bone round steak and put through cuber.
Place meat on flat surface; sprinkle with half the salt, pepper and paprika.
Top with layer of mushrooms, onion (separated into rings) and olives, then sprinkle with crumbs.
Mix melted butter with egg; pour over stuffing.
Roll meat, jelly roll fashion.
Tie with string.
Put into shallow dish.
Pour wine over top.
Sprinkle with remaining salt, pepper and paprika.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, basting once or twice.
Slice and serve with pan juices.
Makes 6 servings.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
A dash of Worcestershire sauce or chopped green pepper may also be added.
Shape into cakes and fry in butter or margarine until brown.
Serve hot.

title: queen's favorite cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
In a mixing bowl mix milk, flour and sugar.
Add to melted margarine in baking dish. Add peaches but do not stir.
Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes or until brown.
Excellent served warm, topped with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: baked lasagna casserole
directions: Brown meat in pan; add garlic, tomato paste, water, onion, bay leaves, parsley, salt and pepper.
Mix.
Cover. Simmer 1 hour over low heat.
Remove bay leaves.
Cook noodles until tender.

title: blueberry crisp
directions: Layer in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in a 3-quart casserole, mixing well. Cover. Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until rice and chicken are tender.

title: chess pie
directions: Blend together and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Cook until a knife will come out clean when inserted in center.
Top with stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake until brown.

title: campbell's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except
for
soup and form into one loaf. Pour Campbell's French
onion
soup
over
top of loaf. Bake at 350° for approximately 2 hours or until well done.

title: seafood pepperpot
directions: Step 1:
In a large casserole, cook bacon over medium heat until translucent.
Add okra; continue cooking until okra is slightly brown and edges curl.
(If using canned okra, add in Step 3.)

title: crab soup
directions: Saute butter, both onions, parsley, garlic and celery flakes until tender.
Then add Pet milk, then whole milk and potato soup. Cook slowly and stir for 30 minutes.
Then add crab meat.
Cook very low for 2 hours.
You may have to add a little more milk.
Add Cajun seasoning.
Serve on toasted kaiser buns that have been toasted real hard.
Slice off top and scoop out the inside.
Fill with soup and replace top.

title: granny cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and sugar together in mixing bowl.
Add eggs and pineapple; mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: low-fat spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain; cool.
Mix all ingredients together with spaghetti; refrigerate.
Better if set overnight.

title: meringue
directions: Add water and salt to egg white and beat until stiff but not dry.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Beat until well mixed. Add baking powder and beat until smooth and fluffy.
Cover pie and brown lightly in a moderate oven.

title: millionaires pie
directions: Mix milk, egg yolks and lemon juice well.
Add pineapple, nuts and Cool Whip, blending until smooth.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill several hours.
Makes 2 pies.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add baking soda and flour.
Mix.
Add potato chips and morsels.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased, floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pam's homemade pizza
directions: Prepare crust as directed on package and set aside. Meanwhile, combine hamburger, onion, seasonings, salt and pepper. Brown in microwave or on stove.
Drain.
Grease large cookie sheet.
Spread pizza dough over cookie sheet.
Spread hamburger mixture over dough.
Spread sauce over hamburger.
Top with mushrooms, Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes in 400° oven or until crust is brown on bottom and cheese in melted on top.

title: mama's chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder and cocoa together.
Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs slowly.
Add milk and flour mixture alternately.
Add flavoring.
Fold in nuts.

title: pizza by the yard
directions: Brown beef.
Drain.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Simmer 8 to 10 minutes.
Prepare dough as directed.
Lightly oil a large baking sheet and roll dough into a 14 x 16-inch rectangle.
Place the meat filling lengthwise down the center.
Cover only the center third of the dough.
With a knife, cut into the dough every 2-inches on each side.
Cross the strips diagonally over the filling, creating a braided look.
Tuck in the ends.
Let rise 5 to 10 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with tomato, green pepper slices and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake 5 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: pumpkin cheesecake bars
directions: On low speed, combine cake mix, 1 egg, butter or margarine and 2 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice until crumbly.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with fork.
Beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk, then 2 eggs, pumpkin, 2 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice and salt.
Mix well.
Pour over crust and sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until set.
Cool and chill in refrigerator.
Cut into bars and serve cold, otherwise they are mushy.
tags: Betty Crocker golden pound cake mix

title: french fried eggplant(6 to 8 appetizers)
directions: Peel eggplant.
Cut lengthwise into 1/2-inch strips.
Dip strips in flour, then in milk, then roll in cracker meal.
Heat oil in deep fryer to 350°.
Fry sticks a few at a time, without crowding in oil, 8 to 10 minutes, until golden brown.
Be sure oil temperature stays at 350°.
Remove sticks from oil and drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and serve with cocktail sauce.

title: easy breakfast casserole
directions: Beat eggs, salt, mustard and milk.
Mix in cheese, bread and meat.
Pour into 9 x 11-inch baking dish.
Cover and let set overnight.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until set up.

title: sex in a pan
directions: Put cake mix, apricot nectar, oil and eggs in large mixing bowl.
Beat in medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Pour in pie crust.
Top with toasted coconut.

title: corn meal pie
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients; add egg yolks, vanilla, cream and corn meal.
Sprinkle 1 cup pecans or coconut.
Add lightly beaten egg whites and blend.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust and bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: fortune cookies
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add oil and egg white.
Stir until smooth.
Add water, mix well.
Make one cookie at a time by pouring 1 tablespoon of the batter on lightly greased skillet.
Spread to 3 1/2-inch circle.
Cook over low heat about 4 minutes or lightly browned.
Turn with wide spatula; cook 1 minute more.
Working quickly place cookie on pot holder.
Put paper strip printed with fortune in center; fold cookie in half and fold again over edge of bowl.
Place in muffin pan to cool.

title: shortening bread
directions: Mix
flour,
cinnamon and nutmeg together.
Put soda in buttermilk.
Bring	margarine and molasses to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add
the
molasses to the flour mixture, then add the milk,
then
add the egg.
Bake in a large skillet at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: all american hamburger
directions: Mix all ingredients together and saute hamburger in 2 tablespoons butter.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Sift the sugar and cocoa together.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Add 1 cup chopped nuts, if desired.
Bake in cookie sheet (10 1/2 x 15 1/2 x 1-inch) at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Heat the pineapple, sugar and flour.
Stir until this thickens; set aside and cool.
Slice bananas and dice apples directly into pineapple mixture.
Mix well.
Dice oranges, peaches and pears. Add all with the strawberries and chill.
Serves 8.

title: baked alaska(home ec special demonstration)
directions: Cut cake layer about 1-inch larger all around than the brick of ice cream block.
Place on wooden board and set aside.
Beat egg whites with electric mixer at high speed, until foam is fine, and add sugar gradually, beating after each addition, until the meringue stands in stiff peaks.
Beat in vanilla.

title: chocolate nugget cake
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Beat all ingredients for 2 minutes.
Pour into a 10 x 16-inch pan.
You will need 2 pans.
Sprinkle 6 ounces chocolate chips and 1 cup nuts over each cake.

title: miniature banana bran muffins
directions: Beat egg and sugar in a bowl.
When smooth, beat in bananas, walnuts, vanilla and oil.
Let stand for a few minutes.
Thoroughly mix all-purpose and wheat flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and bran in a large bowl.
Add banana mixture and fold in with a wooden spoon until dry ingredients are moistened. Spoon batter into muffin cups.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes. Center should be springy to the touch.
Makes 4 dozen miniature muffins.

title: chicken bake
directions: Lightly roll chicken breast in flour, salt, and pepper. Place chicken in 11x14 baking dish.
Mix stuffing according to pkg.
Put a Tbsp. dressing on each chicken breast.
Mix mushroom soup with one can water, and pour over dressing.
Bake at 375° for 30-35 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat.
Drain and add remaining ingredients except buns. Cover; simmer for 30 minutes.
Spoon onto hamburger buns.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: scalloped potato casserole
directions: You can put this together on Saturday and heat just before dinner Sunday.

title: herbed chicken
directions: Prepare rice according to package. Meanwhile, lightly season with salt and pepper the chicken breasts. Brown them in the butter in a large skillet.
Spoon rice into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Arrange chicken on the rice.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Saute onion and beef in salad oil until brown.
Add tomato sauce and mix.
Add spices from wine through pepper.
Simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Cook and drain spaghetti.
Add to sauce with 1/2 cheese.
Place in a 3-quart casserole dish and store in the refrigerator.
When ready for use, set oven at 375°. Put remaining cheese over dish and bake, covered, for 45 minutes. Reduce heat to 300° and bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: good grief
directions: Brown sausage and beef.
Add onion soup, parsley and bread crumbs.
Mix well.
Add the tomatoes and stir.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook until onions are tender.
Pour over cooked macaroni.
Serves 6.

title: surprise delight
directions: Mix and pat in pan the flour, butter and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: whiskey cookies or friendship cookies
directions: Fruits may be cut up or left whole.
Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate for a few hours or overnight.
Drop onto a greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yields 14 dozen.
Very good cookies!

title: burritos
directions: Brown beef and onion.

Add taco seasoning, pepper (if desired), oregano, parsley and sour cream. Add 1/2 the cheese and 1/2 of the taco sauce, mixing well. Place 2 or more tablespoons of mixture on tortilla shell and roll up.
Place, seam side down, in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with remaining cheese and taco sauce. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese melts and the burritos are heated through.
This freezes well.

title: spinach rolls
directions: Blanch spinach leaves carefully in boiling water (in and out quickly); drain well and spread out ready to use. Grate the Parmesan cheese and the Mozzarella cheese, then add them to the cottage cheese and mix together in a stainless steel bowl. Sweat the garlic lightly in some butter or oil; add the walnuts, bread crumbs and a little pepper to taste. Mix the garlic, bread crumbs and walnuts into the cheese mix, stirring just enough to blend them together. DO NOT OVERMIX. Take each spinach leaf in turn and lay it out flat on a board. With a tablespoon, place a spoonful of the cheese mix on to the spinach leaves. Fold the sides of the spinach leaf in toward the center first, then roll up the spinach leaf into a roll, keeping it reasonably taut. Place the 6 rolls of spinach and cheese into a shallow dish that has been greased with butter or oil; add about 1/2 cup of vegetable stock or enough to just cover the bottom of the dish. Cover with a tight fitting lid and shallow poach for a few minutes over a medium-high heat on the range until the stock is absorbed. Yield: 4 portions.

title: egg and cheese bake
directions: Lightly butter deep baking dish.
Using 3 slices of white bread, cutting one slice in two (butter as desired), place in baking dish so that all three slices fit tightly.
Top with cheese. Do the other three slices in the same order; top with cheese so that it is layered.
Beat eggs and milk with salt and pepper.
Pour mixture on top of layered bread and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until done as desired.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: open-face eggs benedict
directions: Lightly toast English muffins.
Top each English muffin half with scrambled eggs.
Place one slice of tomato on each muffin. Pour 2 tablespoons of Hollandaise Sauce on each muffin.
Microwave on High for 30 seconds to heat thoroughly.
Serves 2.

title: nannie's relish
directions: Chop all ingredients.
Mix in kettle and slow boil until thick.
You can eat right away, but tastes better after a week or better.
While at a slow boil, can and jar.

title: nannie henning's coffee bread
directions: Pour scalded milk over butter; let cool.
Dissolve yeast in measuring cup with 1 tablespoon sugar and lukewarm water.
Let rise to top of cup.
Add yeast mixture to milk mixture and flour to make a sponge.
Let rise 45 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, eggs, salt and flour.
Knead and let rise 2 hours.
Divide into 2 loaves and braid each loaf with 4 braids.
Put in two 9 x 7 x 1-inch pans. Brush with egg mixture and sprinkle with sugar and almonds.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: diet milk shake
directions: Put all ingredients into blender; blend until slushy.
Makes 1 serving.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in order.
Mix until well blended. Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle chow mein noodles over top.
Bake 10 minutes (uncovered) longer or until brown.
Serve on rice or noodles or by itself.
Can also add extra chow mein noodles on your plate.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Slice onion and separate into rings. Cover with buttermilk and allow to stand for 1 hour.
Put flour in a plastic or paper bag. Add onion rings.
Inflate bag and shake until rings are coated with flour. Fry in hot oil.
Drain on paper towels.

title: dried fruit cake
directions: Butter a 5 x 9-inch loaf pan lined with parchment or wax paper.
Combine dates, apricots, raisins, figs, 1 tablespoon minced fresh ginger and 1/2 cup sherry.
Mix well and let stand 30 minutes.
Then stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, almonds, pecans, pistachios and crystallized ginger.
Beat together eggs and almond extract.
Add egg and nut mixtures to fruit evenly. Bake in 300° oven until top is golden brown, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy chess pie
directions: Combine ingredients and cook over low heat until margarine is melted.
Do not boil.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°; bake 25 to 30 minutes or until firm.
Lemon juice may be used instead of vinegar for delicious lemon-chess pie or add about 3/4 cup coconut to plain chess recipe and have coconut-chess pie.
Yummy!

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients
except
potato
chips
and cheese. Put in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cover with chips and cheese mixture. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mint patties
directions: If too dry, add more cream cheese.
Shape into desired patty size.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream butter and 5 tablespoons of sugar. Work flour, vanilla and nuts into cream mixture. Roll into small balls. Bake on ungreased sheet at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar, right from oven.

title: 24 hour fruit salad
directions: Mix together all but the bananas and refrigerate. Before serving add 2 medium diced bananas. Stir and enjoy.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef and onion.
Add celery and soups.
Place in 2-quart buttered casserole and cover with as many Tater Tots as possible.
Bake for 30 minutes!

title: drop cookies
directions: Stir sugar into mix.
Combine milk, beaten egg and vanilla. Stir in Master Mix until well blended.
Drop by teaspoons on greased baking sheet at 375° for 20 minutes.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: cheese biscuits(like red lobster)
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Drop by spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.
As soon as biscuits come out of oven, brush with mixture of remaining ingredients.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: wafer delights
directions: Put it together like a sandwich.
Great for snacking.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Layer hamburger, green beans, soup and milk mixed together. Top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: irish colcannon
directions: Mash potatoes with milk, margarine, salt and pepper until fluffy.
Simmer leeks or onions in 1/4 cup water, broth or milk until tender. Add to cabbage. Add all to potatoes and mix well.

title: easy bean dip
directions: In deep 1-quart casserole bowl, combine soup, cheese, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, onion and hot pepper sauce. Cover.
Microwave at full power (High) for 4 to 5 minutes or until cheese melts, stirring twice.
Stir 1/2 cup bean mixture into sour cream.
Stir sour cream mixture into bean mixture in casserole bowl.
Cover.
Microwave at 30% (Medium-low) for 2 minutes or until heated through, stirring once.
Serve hot with vegetable dippers or chips.

title: prune cake
directions: Cook on low heat for 10 minutes.
Punch holes in warm cake and pour cooked syrup slowly over cake.
Cool to serve.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream crisco and sugar. Beat eggs in one at a time. Add 1/4 cup milk and 1 cup of flour. Mix well. Add the remaining milk and flour. Bake at 300 degrees for 1 hour.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Combine chocolate morsels, butterscotch morsels and peanut butter morsels in 2-quart casserole.
Put in microwave; heat on full power for 1 minute and 35 seconds.
Then stir and cook again for 1 minute and 45 seconds.
They should all be melted.
Then stir in peanuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Chill until firm. Store in a covered container in refrigerator.
Yields about 3 1/2 to 4 dozen.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Mix the sugar, coconut, margarine, raisins, walnuts or pecans, eggs, vanilla and vinegar together well. Pour into 2 (9-inch) pie shells. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes or until browned on top.

title: pineapple orange cake(good, moist cake)
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake according to directions on mix box in 9 x 13-inch size pan.

title: italian cheese log
directions: Roll cheese into a log shape.
Cover completely with dry dressing mix.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.

title: cheese tea biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients and roll out little pieces the size of thumb.
Press with a fork to the size of a quarter, then to the size of a silver dollar.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: huevos rancheros(nonfat)
directions: Cover tortilla with 1/2 cup nonfat refried beans (heated), 1/2 cup nonfat Cheddar cheese, 1 fried egg white, 2 tablespoons salsa, 1/4 cup nonfat sour cream and 1/2 cup nonfat Cheddar cheese.
Put in preheated oven at 350° until cheese melts.
Top with 2 tablespoons green pepper and 1 chopped green onion.
Serves one.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Blend mayonnaise, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce in bowl.
Then add rest of ingredients and toss lightly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish. Mix soup and sour cream; spread over chicken. Sprinkle with poppy seeds. Top with crumbled Ritz crackers. Drizzle with butter. Bake 20 - 25 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: iridescent soap bubbles
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Blow beautiful bubbles.

title: mingea's prize winning pepper relish
directions: Drain juice off ground peppers.
Add 1/2 cup salt to enough water to cover peppers.
Let sit 2 or 3 hours or overnight and drain.
Grind onions.
Mix with ground peppers.
Add vinegar, sugar, 1 teaspoon salt and mustard seed.
Cook over medium heat in heavy pot about 1 1/2 hours, until glazed looking.
If watery, dip some liquid off.
Seal in jars.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and cream cheese together. Fold in fruit, then Cool Whip.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix first 5 ingredients well and press into a deep 10-inch pie plate, as for a crust.
Bake 40 minutes. In the meantime, combine rice, water, onion and seasonings in a heavy saucepan with lid.
Let sit for 20 minutes without heat. After 20 minutes, bring to a boil; stir once.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, 20 minutes.
Stir in butter.
Remove meat from the oven and drain off any fat.
Top the meat with the rice, smoothing it to the edges of the pie plate.
Sprinkle with cheese and return to the oven for a few minutes until cheese melts.
Let sit 10 minutes before cutting into wedges.
Serves 6.

title: nut crescents
directions: Mix butter, cream cheese and flour together.
Roll into a ball and cut ball in half.
Roll out flat and cut into squares, approximately 2 x 2-inch.
Mix walnut meats, sugar and melted butter together. This makes the filling.
Put 1 tablespoon filling in each square and fold diagonally making sure all nutmeats are covered.
Shape into crescents.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Soak beans overnight in water.
Drain and cover with water. Cook until tender, 30 to 40 minutes.
Rinse under hot water.
Put in casserole.
Add butter.
Mix in dry ingredients and stir in molasses and sour cream.
Mix gently.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until thick.

title: ham and potato au gratin
directions: In a saucepan melt margarine.
Stir in flour.
Add 1 3/4 cups milk all at once.
Cook to make sauce.
Remove from heat.
Stir 1 cup of the mixture into the beaten eggs.
Stir in Cheddar cheese, 1/4 cup milk and pepper.
Set aside.

title: ashley's spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Combine eggs and Parmesan.
Stir into spaghetti.
Layer 1/2 spaghetti and 1/2 Mozzarella twice in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Brown ground beef; drain well.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Heat while spaghetti is baking. Pour sauce over baked spaghetti.
Let set 10 minutes before serving.

title: mucho nacho omelette(makes six 3 egg omelettes)
directions: Mix all ingredients, putting equal amounts into 6 omelettes.

title: potatoes deluxe
directions: Mix potatoes, onions, soup, cheese and butter.
Add salt and pepper.
Place potato mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: crawfish impossible pie
directions: In a small skillet, saute onion, garlic and celery until clear.
Add crawfish, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 5 minutes. Grease pie plate.
Add crawfish mixture.
Beat eggs and milk for 1 minute.
Add biscuit mix; mix well.
Sprinkle cheese on top of crawfish.
Pour biscuit mixture into pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Serve warm.
Serves 6.

title: pizza burgers
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef.
Drain.
Stir in pizza sauce and oregano.
Chop fine onion, green pepper and pepperoni.
Add to beef mixture.
Simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Spoon mixture on buns. Top with Mozzarella cheese.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots. Add other ingredients and cool.
Cool, covered, for several hours.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Gently beat eggs and sugar.
Add oil,
water
and pumpkin. Add remaining ingredients.
Divide into
greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: best-ever meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Cover with chili sauce on top of meat loaf.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tostados soup
directions: Cook meat with onions; drain.
Add chopped tomatoes to meat along with other ingredients.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes or until blended.
Top with chips and cheese.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fudgy brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease an 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
In large bowl, stir together the cocoa and water; let stand for 5 minutes.
Stir in oil, granulated sugar, brown sugar, egg whites and vanilla.
Add the baking powder, salt and flour and stir for 2 minutes.
Fold in nuts, then pour the mixture into the pan.
Bake for 20 minutes or until set and a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool.
Cut into 2-inch squares. Makes 16 brownies.

title: elsie rolls
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Pour 1/2 full in greased muffin tins. Bake 10 minutes at 450°.

title: scallop casserole
directions: Mix crumbs and butter.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Alternate layers of crumbs and scallops in buttered casserole.
Drizzle cream over the casserole.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: pasta primavera casserole
directions: Cook pasta.
Put in casserole dish.
Saute zucchini, red peppers, mushrooms and scallions in butter.
Add tomato.
Spoon over pasta.
Add 1/2 flour to drippings in pan.
Blend in milk. Add broth, nutmeg and pepper.
Cook until thick.
Add spinach and cheese.
Pour over pasta and vegetables.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Combine flour, pecans, butter and brown sugar in 8-inch square baking pan.
Stir well.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool.
Combine strawberries, sugar, lemon juice and egg whites in large mixing bowl.
Beat at high speed for 10 to 12 minutes or until stiff peaks form.
Fold in whipped cream.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Put yeast in bowl.
Add water.
Let stand 4 minutes.
Add butter, milk, eggs, salt, sugar and 2 cups flour.
Beat 3 minutes. Add rest of flour.
Mix well.
Cover and let stand until double in bulk.
Turn out on floured board and work dough.
Take rolling pan and roll them.
Have a mixture of 1 cup sugar, 1 stick of softened butter, 1 tablespoon cinnamon and 1 1/2 cups softened raisins. Spread on dough.
Roll up dough.
Cut and lay on greased sheet. Bake in 350° oven when double in bulk.
Mix powdered sugar and milk.
Put on rolls when done.

title: green jacket salad
directions: Pita croutons:
Bake pita bread for 4 hours at 200° or until crisp.
Break into small pieces.
Do not brown pita bread.

title: teriyaki-glazed turkey burgers
directions: In small bowl, combine honey, ginger, soy sauce and garlic until well blended.
In separate bowl, mix together turkey, celery and green onion.
Blend in 3 tablespoons honey mixture.
Divide mixture into 4 to 6 patties.
Place patties on a well-oiled grill. Grill, turning 2 to 3 times, brushing with honey glaze until patties are well-browned and cooked through.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Cream together the oleo, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla, flour, baking powder and salt.
Spread 2/3 batter into greased 12 x 18-inch pan.
Spread with pie filling.
Drop remainder of batter onto filling by spoonfuls.
Swirl with knife.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Spread lightly with a cream cheese icing.
Also very good with raisin, apricot or cherry pie filling.

title: texas beans
directions: Put bacon, meat, onion and ham in bottom of crock-pot.
Mix vinegar, mustard, catsup and brown sugar and add to crock-pot. Then add the five cans of beans.
Cook on high for four hours. Delicious with salad and (Mexican) Corn Bread.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Place all ingredients in food processor or blender.
Blend until mixed well.
Good with vegetables.

title: coffee
directions: For 30 cups of coffee, enough to feed small family, scoop 1 tablespoon for every 2 cups of fresh cold water.
Add a pinch of salt after all the coffee has been added.
Place crushed egg shells on top of ground coffee.
Plug in and allow 20 to 30 to perk.

title: rosemary potatoes
directions: Leave peel on potatoes and slice round.
Layer potatoes in baking dish; sprinkle each ingredient over.
Repeat.
Use more salt, if desired.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: veggie quiche
directions: In large bowl, mix together broccoli and cauliflower mix, cheese, egg substitute, evaporated skimmed milk, green onion and Italian seasoning.
Pour into frozen pie crust.
Sprinkle with salt and ground black pepper, if desired.
Bake in a 375° oven on a preheated baking sheet for 45 to 50 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: linda's tuna ball
directions: Add a small amount of nuts to mixture as you mix ingredients together.
Roll or shape into a ball.
Roll in nuts and parsley flakes.
Chill and serve with party crackers.

title: chicken nuggets(microwave)
directions: Combine Parmesan cheese, Cheddar cheese, crumbs, garlic powder, salt, oregano and pepper.
Blend well.
Dip chicken pieces into melted margarine.
Roll in crumb mixture.
Arrange chicken in single layer in an 8 x 10-inch microwavable dish.
Cover with plastic wrap, poking several holes in plastic wrap.
Cook chicken for 10 minutes at normal setting or until cooked.
Serve hot or cold as appetizer or as a meat dish.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: spaghetti corn
directions: Melt the butter in a casserole dish.
Stir the rest of the ingredients together in the casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered, and 30 minutes uncovered.
Serve hot.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray Pam into a glass or oblong pan. Dump pineapple.
Dump cherry pie filling on top of pineapple. Dump cake mix on top of cherry pie filling.
Dump walnuts on top of cake.
Mix and cut butter into pats on top of walnuts.
Bake about 45 minutes.

title: caramel fluff pie
