directions: Melt caramels in milk in double boiler, stirring constantly. Add salt to gelatin and soften in cold water.
Add to caramels. Stir to dissolve.
Chill until quite thick.
Fold in whipped cream and nuts.
Pour into a prepared pie crust of your choice. Refrigerate until firm.

title: champagne salad
directions: Soften cream cheese and blend with sugar.
Blend in whipped topping. In another bowl mix pineapple, strawberries with juice, bananas and nuts.
Blend fruits with cream cheese mixture, pour into 9 x 13 pan and freeze.
To serve, remove from freezer 20 minutes before serving and cut into squares.
Can be refrozen.

title: apple crisp
directions: Pour apple filling in 9x13 pan.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over apples.
Pour dry cake mix over apples.
Melt 1 1/2 sticks margarine and pour over cake mix.

title: cutlets
directions: Wash and boil the potatoes with 1 teaspoon salt until about half cooked.
Drain; cool, then peel.
In a large bowl, grate the onion and potatoes.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly until a uniform texture is reached.

title: chicken spaghetti "norma"
directions: In heavy 4-quart pot, saute garlic in oil for 3 minutes.
Add drumsticks.
Simmer until brown, turning frequently.
After 10 minutes, add tomato paste, sofrito, cilantro and water.
Bring to a boil; cover tightly and cook on low for 40 minutes.
Add cooked spaghetti, mix and serve.

title: hot and sour soup
directions: Soak black Chinese mushrooms and lily buds for 30 minutes; drain.
Cut mushrooms in thin strips; cut off and discard hard tips from lily buds.
Tie each bud onto itself to make a knot in the middle.
Cut bamboo shoots into matchstick pieces.
Cut chicken into thin slices; sprinkle with sherry and let stand 15 minutes.

title: bumbleberry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Place 2nd crust on top.
Trim 1/2 inch larger than pan. Tuck top crust under; crimp edges.
Cut slits in top crust.
Place on baking sheet and bake 25 minutes.
Reduce to 350° and bake 30 minutes.

title: frosting for sugar cookies
directions: Cream Parkay margarine until fluffy.
Add sugar, 1/2 cup at a time.
Mix well; add vanilla and milk.

title: crumb cake
directions: Pour pie filling in a long Pyrex cake plate.
Add sugar.
Add dry cake mix (don't mix it up).
Pour melted margarine over top of dry cake mix.
You can add coconut and pecans if you choose.
Bake in 350° oven until brown on top.

title: bagged caramel corn
directions: Cook in microwave: margarine, brown sugar, syrup and salt. Boil 2 minutes.
Put popcorn in brown grocery bag.
Pour syrup over top.
Fold shut; shake.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes; shake. Microwave 1 1/2 minutes; shake.
Repeat one more time!
Cut open bag and let mixture cool on bag or cookie sheet.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Cook rice as directed.
Drain broccoli.
Mix broccoli, rice, Cheez Whiz and soup in a casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: german skillet dinner
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Rinse sauerkraut and drain.
Add all ingredients together in skillet and mix well.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes over low heat or put in casserole, cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: jean's boiled custard
directions: Beat eggs.
While stirring, add remaining ingredients.
Cook in top of double boiler over hot, not boiling, water.
Stir with wooden spoon until mixture coats spoon.
Be careful not to overcook.
Remove from heat and cool.
Can be frozen in an ice cream freezer.

title: bean and corn chili over puffed tortillas
directions: Bake tortillas at 450° for 4 to 5 minutes.
Saute onion and garlic in oil 3 to 4 minutes.
Add tomatoes, cumin, black pepper, red pepper, kidney beans and liquid and 1/2 of green chilies. Simmer for 5 minutes, stirring often.
Add corn and cook 1 minute longer.
Place 3/4 cup of chili over each tortilla.
Sprinkle each with 1/4 of cheese.

title: apple brownies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Sift dry ingredients into butter mixture and mix well.
Add chopped apples.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35-40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in microwave oven just long enough to make it tender. Mix all remaining ingredients together. Place mixture in a shallow baking dish. Cook at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups flour, yeast, sugar and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Add hot water and mix until dry ingredients are moistened.
Beat 2 minutes or until smooth.
Blend in oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each addition.
Add remaining flour (or enough to make a stiff batter) and beat well for 1 minute or until smooth and elastic.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until light and bubbly, about 1 hour.
Stir batter down and turn into 2 greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans, which have been dusted with cornmeal.
Cover and let rise until doubled (about 30 minutes).
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Allow bread to cool completely, then invert and shake gently to remove. To serve, cut 1/2-inch slices and toast.

title: bly's sport pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a 3-quart bowl.
Stir in flour, oil, garlic and salt.
Mix until dough; let stand 15 minutes.
Heat oven to 425°.
Pat dough to shape of cookie sheet (12 x 15 1/2-inch).
Place dough on lightly greased cookie sheet.

title: low calorie orange pie
directions: Heat pineapple and add orange jello. Stir until dissolved. Let cool. Add cream cheese and beat well. Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in pie crusts.
Chill overnight. Enjoy!

title: crab imperial
directions: Combine green pepper, pimento (both finely chopped), dry mustard, salt, pepper, eggs and 1 cup mayonnaise.
Add crab meat and blend all the ingredients together gently with the fingers so as to not break meat too much.

title: chicken-broccoli with alfredo sauce(low-carb)
directions: Spray skillet with Pam spray. Cut chicken into strips; cook in skillet until slightly browned. Add broccoli and cover.
Cook on medium heat while making sauce.

title: nannie's butter pie
directions: Put oleo in mixing bowl. Soften. Add sugar and egg. Beat together. Add flour. Blend together. Add Milnot and water. Add vanilla. Mix well. Pour into pie crust and bake at 400° to set (approximately 8 minutes). Turn down to 350° and bake until done. (Filling will move a little in center.) Baking time: About 30 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients; let stand for 1 hour and add the remaining ingredients.
Beat until fluffy.
Take hands and form a ball.
Slice.

title: lynn's barbecue brisket
directions: Place brisket in roasting pan with half bottle of ketchup evenly distributed.
Sprinkle half box brown sugar over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn brisket over and pour rest of ketchup over top.
Sprinkle rest of brown sugar on top.
Bake 1 hour and remove.
Slice thinly with electric knife and place into pan with the sauce.
Add 1 cup water and bake 2 to 3 more hours until tender, basting meat periodically.

title: almond eggnog pound cake
directions: Grease a 10-inch fluted tube pan with 2 tablespoons butter. Press almonds onto the bottom and sides of pan. Set aside. Melt remaining butter. In a large mixing bowl, beat the cake mix, eggnog, eggs, rum extract, nutmeg and melted butter on low speed for 30 seconds or just until moistened. Beat on medium for 2 minutes. Pour into prepared pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes, until inserted toothpick comes out clean. Cool for 15 minutes; put on wire rack.

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and potato chips.
Top with grated cheese, then crushed potato chips.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 400°.
Serves 6.

title: spinach quiche appetizer
directions: Mix together flour, salt and baking powder.
In a separate bowl, mix together eggs, milk and margarine.
Combine with dry ingredients.
Add cheese, onion and spinach.
Mix well and pour into 10 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into squares and serve.
The quiche will not be very thick, about 1/2 to 3/4-inch.

title: no bake cherry cheesecake
directions: Use mixer to blend softened cream cheese with sugar and vanilla.
Add Cool Whip and blend.
Mix graham cracker crumbs with melted margarine and press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread cream cheese mixture on top of crust and spread.
Cover with cherry pie filling and refrigerate.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over 1 1/2 cups V-8 juice in a bowl.
Let set while heating (do not boil) the remaining 1 1/2 cups V-8.
Combine the two mixtures.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased mold.
Congeal.
Unmold on serving tray.

title: pepper steak
directions: Partially frozen meat will be easier to cut.

title: lauren's spaghetti soup
directions: Brown ground beef, chopped onion, salt and pepper in a soup pot.
In another pot, cook spaghetti according to directions on package.
Drain.
Rinse and set aside for later use.
Add can of pork and beans, tomato sauce and tomato soup to ground beef mixture.
Add a can of water for each of these 3 cans.
Add cooked Spaghetti Soup.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: world war #2 cake
directions: In a saucepan, mix brown sugar, 1 1/2 cups water, shortening, raisins, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Bring to a boil and boil 3 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Dissolve salt and baking soda in 2 teaspoons of water.
Add salt and soda mixture to raisins and spice mixture.
Blend in flour and baking powder.
Turn batter into a lightly greased and floured 8-inch square pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: one dish chicken bake
directions: Mix stuffing mix as directed.
Place chicken in 13 x 9 pan. Mix soup and sour cream.
Spoon stuffing over chicken; add soup mixture.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: apple bread
directions: Bake at 350° until it tests clean.

title: ri's pork 'n bean with dog casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, covered.
Add bacon slices on top of beans.
Bake 8 more minutes, uncovered. Serves 4.

title: jambalaya mix
directions: Combine all ingredients; store in airtight container. Yield: 1 1/2 cups.

title: snow balls
directions: Mix and roll into balls.

title: orange cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl and beat for 3 minutes.
Pour into 3 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Cool before frosting.

title: baked chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese, salt and herbs.
Mix well.
Dip chicken pieces in butter. Coat with bread crumb mixture.
Place on baking sheet in a single layer.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: n. y. style cheesecake
directions: Mix crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Line bottom of 8-inch or 9-inch spring pan.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with crackers.
Mix prepared vanilla pudding and Cool Whip together and put on crackers.
Put another layer of crackers.
Top this layer of crackers with Chocolate Icing.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and 1 egg.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread over first layer. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marshmallow delights
directions: Open crescent rolls and separate triangles.
Dip each marshmallow in melted butter, then in mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Place a marshmallow in the center of each triangle and pinch corners of dough together.
Dip tops of dough in remaining butter and sugar mixture.
Bake in greased muffin pan at 375° for 13 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm; centers will be gooey.

title: crock-pot nachos
directions: Brown ground beef and drain well.
Put ground beef, cheese and salsa in crock-pot.
Stir occasionally until cheese is melted. Pour cheese/meat mixture over chips and enjoy plain, or add any of your favorite toppings, such as jalapenos, sour cream, guacamole, etc.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients then add onion with enough water to be able to mix.
Drop into hot grease until brown.

title: beef parmigiana
directions: Pound steak to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut into 6 serving size pieces. Combine bread crumbs with Parmesan cheese.
Dip steak in egg and coat with crumb mixture. Brown steak in hot oil in skillet. Remove and place in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside.

title: green bean vinaigrette
directions: Cook green beans according to package directions; drain. Plunge into ice water to stop the cooking process.
Drain and set aside.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix together flour, margarine and powdered sugar; spread in a pizza pan and bake at 325° for 12 minutes.
Let cool.
Blend cream cheese and sugar and spread over top of crust.
Pour pie filling on top and chill for 1 hour.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Cook apples and water for 15 minutes; mash.
Pour in crock-pot (low heat).
Stir in all ingredients.
Cover; cook 12 hours.
Stir well.
Turn heat on high until extra juices evaporates, about 45 minutes.
Leave lid off while cooking down.
Pour into sterile jars and seal.
Makes 7 or 8 pints.

title: easy browned rice
directions: Melt butter or margarine in skillet.
Saute rice in skillet until lightly browned (approximately 10 minutes).
Put rice into casserole dish.
Add can of soup to rice and mix.
Add bouillon cube/water and mix.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and oleo; cook over medium heat until soft ball shape (approximately 15 minutes after it starts to boil). Remove from heat and add vanilla, peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Stir until all ingredients are combined.
Pour into greased cake pan.

title: striped delight
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter. Press firmly into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese with 1 tablespoon sugar and 2 tablespoons milk until smooth.
Fold into the whipped topping, reserving 1/2 cup for top layer.
Spread over crust.
Mix pudding according to package directions.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Chill several hours or overnight. Spread remaining whipped topping over pudding.
Garnish with grated chocolate or chopped nuts if desired.

title: bran muffins
directions: Soak:
100% bran in water and cool.
Cream:
shortening, sugar and eggs.
Mix together:
flour, soda and salt and alternately with buttermilk.
Put in muffin tins.
Make indentation, put in raisins, dates, chunk pineapple or jelly (optional).
Bake at 375° for 23 minutes.
Makes 60.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in pineapple.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cheese cake muffins
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla. Mix but do not overmix.
Fill muffin liners 3/4 full.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes.

title: orange date muffins
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add oil, 1/4 cup juice and milk.
Mix in dry ingredients just until moistened; batter will be lumpy.
Fold in dates and nuts.
Bake at 350° in lined muffin cups 25 to 30 minutes.
Take remaining 1/4 cup juice and brush on.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Makes 6 large or 10 small muffins.

title: glazed strawberry pie
directions: Combine water, sugar and cornstarch.
Cook on low heat, stirring occasionally until mixture is thick and clear.
Add one box of gelatin.
Cool to lukewarm before combining with strawberries and placing in baked and cooled pie shell.

title: onion dip - fast and easy
directions: Mix ingredients in a bowl.
Cover.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Great with potato chips or raw vegetables.

title: sheet coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Blend in vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and blend well.
Spread 2/3 of dough in greased jelly roll pan.
Cover with fruit filling.
Spoon remaining batter on top and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cover with Glaze soon after it comes out of oven.

title: fresh green peas with or without snaps
directions: Fry 2 slices of bacon in a heavy, 4-quart pot.
Add the fresh peas.
Cook, covered, on medium heat, stirring often.
They will "steam fry" for about 20 minutes.
Stir frequently, do not let them burn.
Add salt (to taste) and enough water to cover the peas (or to make the amount of pea "juice" that you want).
When they begin to look cooked, turn the heat down more and cook until tender.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and soda. In a saucepan, bring margarine, shortening, Coca-Cola and cocoa to a boil. Remove from heat; stir in marshmallows until almost dissolved. Add to dry ingredients. Add beaten eggs and buttermilk. Do not overbeat. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. When cool, top with icing.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Press zucchini with paper towel to get out moisture.
Mix with onion, eggs, flour, salt and enough bread crumbs to make a fairly stiff batter.
Fry.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: In a medium saucepan melt margarine and brown sugar over low heat and bring to bubble stage.
Continue cooking for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add eggs (all at one time), stirring rapidly. If lumps occur, return to heat and continue to beat.
Add dry ingredients and stir.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: onion cheese casserole
directions: Saute thinly sliced onion rings in margarine.
Place in flat greased casserole (8 x 8-inches).
Sprinkle with cheese and pour chicken soup over all.

title: oriental cabbage salad
directions: Cut cabbage in thin strips.
Slice green onion.
Add crushed noodles, seed and almonds.
Mix with diced, cooked chicken.
Add dressing.
Toss.
Let stand overnight.
The longer it sets, the better it will be.

title: layered walnut pumpkin pie
directions: Chop walnuts fine; set aside.
Soften gelatin in water in a 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in pumpkin, 1/2 cup of the sugar, milk, lightly beaten egg yolks, spice and salt.
Heat just to boiling, stirring constantly.
Turn heat very low.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and Cool Whip.
Chill until mixture thickens slightly.

title: swordfish steaks with orange
directions: Thaw fish, if frozen.
Cut into 4 serving size portions. Rinse and pat dry with paper towels.

title: vegetable salad ala houston
directions: Line salad bowl with lettuce.
Cut string beans very fine, lengthwise, French-style.
Mix all vegetables.
Add seasonings, oil and vinegar.
Mix well.
Place on lettuce and serve.
(Peas may be added, if desired.)

title: fruit salad pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour in saucepan with fruit.
Heat until thick. Remove from heat.
Add the cherry Jell-O (no water).
Let cool. When cool, add the bananas that have been mashed and 1 cup broken pecans.
Refrigerate overnight.
When ready to serve, top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Real good and fast.

title: saucy pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops over medium heat.
Combine soup, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Place browned pork chops in baking dish; cover with soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes covered.
Remove lid and bake an additional 10 minutes.
Serve in sauce.

title: hidden valley ranch baked chicken
directions: Dredge 2 to 3 pounds of chicken pieces in Hidden Valley dressing mix, then bake skin side up at 375° for 45 minutes until brown and crispy.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hot bean dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat on Medium-high in microwave until cheese melts.
Stir 2 to 3 times while heating.
Serve warm with corn chips.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef and onions, salt and pepper to taste.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes, until noodles are tender.

title: orange glazed carrots
directions: Boil sliced carrots in water until tender; drain well.
Place in casserole dish.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Mix sugar and cornstarch well.
Add orange juice, mix well, then add nutmeg. Pour in pan with butter.
Cook sauce slowly until it thickens, then pour over the carrots and serve.

title: green tomato preserves
directions: Blend tomatoes (any ripeness).
Add sugar and boil 10 minutes on medium heat.
Remove from heat and add jello.
May be canned, froze or kept in refrigerator.
Use strawberry or blackberry jello for taste.

title: camper's baked potatoes
directions: Use baking potatoes, scrub and chop into pieces.
Do not peel. Use heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Use about 6 to 8 pieces, one for each serving.
Place equal portions of the ingredients on each foil square.
Fold the foil and seal ends.
Place on barbecue grill for about 45 to 55 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings.
Carbohydrate 14 g, protein 2 g, fat 1.6 g, calories 74.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Layer corn tortillas, chopped chilies, onion and cheese in electric skillet.
Add 2 cans of milk to cans of soup and heat. As you are layering ingredients, pour soup over each layer.
Top your casserole with shredded cheese and pour balance of soup over all.
Keep skillet turned on low before and during serving.
If it becomes dry, add small amount of milk.

title: pizza by the yard
directions: In a bowl, combine the uncooked beef, olives, onion, Parmesan cheese, tomato paste, oregano, salt and pepper.
Spread to the edges of the cut surface of the bread.
Broil 6-inches from the heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until the meat is fully cooked.
Top with tomatoes and the mozzarella cheese.
Broil 2 to 3 minutes more or until cheese is melted.
Serve immediately.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Peel and slice carrots.
Cover with boiling water and cook 15 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Slice onion.
Cut green pepper in strips.
Combine sugar, soup, vinegar, oil, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Pour over carrots and mix well.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown ground beef and add taco mix.
Set aside.
Spread refried beans on bottom of baking dish.
Pour nacho soup on top. Add sour cream.
Pour meat mixture on top of sour cream.
Top with salsa, then cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Spread	popcorn in a large, shallow roasting pan.
Stir sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt.
Cook over medium heat until mixture
boils.
Continue
cooking, without stirring, 5 minutes. Stir
in
vanilla
and baking soda.
Pour corn syrup mixture over popcorn.
Bake at 250°, uncovered, 1 hour.	Break apart and cool.

title: vegetarian spaghetti sauce
directions: Good recipe for a slow cooker to simmer all day.
Serve over pasta or rice.

title: stove top beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a pot.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover.
Cook gently for 30 minutes.
Uncover pot and continue cooking for 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: (latkes) potato cakes
directions: Grate potatoes into a bowl;
mix with eggs.
Add salt and flour.
Set aside to rest while heating just enough oil to cover the bottom of a heavy pan.
When oil is hot, add potato mixture to it in tablespoons.
Fry quickly until brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels; serve warm with sour cream.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over bran in separate bowl; stir and let stand to cool.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and soaked bran.
Add buttermilk.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Mix well. Fold in All-Bran until mixed.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400° in greased muffin tin or use cupcake papers.
Makes 30 muffins.
Keep extra batter or baked muffins in refrigerator.

title: biscotti
directions: Place the beaten eggs in a large mixing bowl and while the eggs are still beating, add melted butter, oil, anise flavor and last the sugar. Mix until well blended. Use your hands to add the flour and baking powder until well blended.

Add sliced almonds and mix until you have a good firm ball. Place on greased cookie sheet in two loaves. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Remove cookie from sheet and slice on the diagonal. Place back on cookie sheet and toast in oven until golden brown. Once cooled, you may dip in chocolate.

title: vanilla carob cake(sugar-free)
directions: Beat together eggs, mashed banana, butter and milk until creamy.
Add vanilla, flour, carob powder, baking powder and baking soda.
Beat well.
Stir in flaked coconut.
Spoon batter evenly into an oiled and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cut potatoes into thin slices, but not all the way through.
Lay knife handle by potato and slice.
Place in baking dish and fan slightly.
Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with herbs.
Bake at 425° for 50 minutes. Remove from oven.
Sprinkle cheeses.
Bake another 10 to 15 minutes until lightly brown, cheeses are melted and potatoes are soft again.

title: snow peas and carrots
directions: String peas, if necessary.
Peel carrots and cut in sticks, about 1/2-inch thick.
Cook carrots in boiling water for 5 minutes or until barely tender.
Drain.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter in a skillet.
Add carrots and toss until well coated.
Heat through and season to taste.
Arrange in the center of a platter.
Keep warm.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter in another skillet.
Saute peas quickly until well coated with butter.
Cover pan and cook 2 minutes.
Serve peas around carrots.
Makes 6 servings.

title: eat it up spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti. Beat eggs.
Mix spaghetti, margarine, eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Spread mixture into oblong glass pan or 2 glass deep dish pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Take out and spread Ricotta cheese on top, then layer on hamburger, spaghetti sauce and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: baked chicken parmesan
directions: Combine crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper.
Brush chicken with salad dressing.
Coat with crumb mixture.
Place in 13 x 9-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter, brown sugar and 2 tablespoons pineapple syrup in a 10-inch round cake pan.
Remove from heat.
Arrange pineapple and cherries in mixture.
Prepare batter as directed on cake package.
Pour over mixture in the pan.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Allow 2 to 3 minutes before removing pan.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: green tom pie
directions: Wash and slice thinly the tomatoes.
Mix all other ingredients. Arrange tomatoes in layers, sprinkling each layer with mixture in an ungreased pie shell. Add top crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: our family's favorite chili
directions: Brown ground round; drain and rinse with hot tap water.
In large pan or crock-pot, combine ground round and the rest of the ingredients.
Simmer on stove top for 3 hours, covered, or cook in crock-pot on low for 10 to 12 hours, or on high for 5 to 6 hours.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Measure into a bowl, the boiling water and oats.
Cool until warm and add the shortening, sugars, eggs, cinnamon and vanilla. Mix thoroughly and add, flour, soda and salt.
Bake in oblong greased pan 30-35 minutes at 350°. While still hot, spread with frosting.

title: drunk wieners
directions: Mix brown sugar, chili sauce and bourbon together in a large skillet.
Cook until simmering.
Add sausages and cook until hot through and through.
Serve in a chafing dish to keep hot.

title: fatush - arabic salad
directions: Toast Arabic bread until hard; break into bite size pieces. Smash garlic with salt.
Mix all ingredients in large salad bowl. Enjoy!

title: jim's herbed bread
directions: Stir yeast into warm water.
Combine sour cream mix with brown sugar, margarine and spices.
Blend yeast mixture and sour cream mixture without allowing to cool.
Add 1/2 cup corn meal and one cup of the flour and blend together well.
Add remaining flour 1/2 cup at a time until well blended.
Knead dough vigorously for 5 minutes.
Roll the dough around in a lightly greased bowl; cover and let stand, away from drafts, until double in bulk.
Punch down and allow dough to relax for a couple minutes.
Shape into a round loaf and place into a greased round glass pie tin.
Cover with an inverted bowl and allow to double in bulk.
Place in a preheated 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add salt and pepper, drained beans and soup.
Pour into greased dish.
Mash potatoes while hot, add milk and egg.
Season with salt and pepper.
Spoon over hamburger. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Alternately layer tortillas, chicken, onions, chilies, soup mixture and cheese until all ingredients are used.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: escalloped chicken
directions: Melt butter, then toss cubed bread in butter. Add the soups, boned chicken and beaten eggs. Put in baking dish and top with cracker crumbs mixed in melted butter. Bake in 350° oven 1 hour. May be cut in half.

title: crab spaghetti
directions: Combine half and half, Velveeta and one stick of butter in pan over
very	low
heat, stir occasionally.
In the meantime, melt other
stick
of
butter
in
frypan and add sliced mushrooms. Saute
over
low
heat covered until mushrooms are cooked.	Cook spaghetti
in
large
pot
in salted water until tender.
Drain and
return
to
same
pot.
Add
cheese sauce, mushrooms, pimentos
and
raw onions.	Mix thoroughly and then fold crabmeat into
mixture.
Place
in one large or two small casserole dishes. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: crock-pot chicken and dressing
directions: Saute onion and celery in 1/2 of melted butter. Crumble corn bread and mix all ingredients together, adding chicken last. Cook in crock-pot on high for 3 1/2 hours.

title: alabama chocolate-candy jumbo christmas cheesecake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; press mixture evenly onto bottom and 1 1/2-inches up sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Sprinkle chopped nougat bars evenly over bottom; set aside.
Beat cream cheese at high speed with mixer until light and fluffy.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Stir in chocolate morsels and vanilla; beat until blended. Spoon over candy layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and run knife around edges of pan to release sides.
Let cool to room temperature.
Cover and chill at least 8 hours.
To serve, remove from pan and pipe whipped cream on top.

title: pesto
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients well.
Pour in slowly the olive oil. Add cheese, salt and pepper.
This freezes well.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: potato casserole
directions: In skillet melt 1/2 stick butter.
Add hash browns and green onions.
Saute until softened.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add sour cream and Velveeta.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add to top 1/2 stick melted butter and cornflakes.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together hamburger, onion, ketchup, oatmeal, egg and crackers.
Then shape your loaf.
Peel potatoes and carrots; put beside meat loaf then pour 3/4 cup of tomato juice and 1 cup water around meat loaf.
Then cover with aluminum foil and bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: rotel - fondue dip
directions: Place all ingredients in fondue pot.
Let melt completely. Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: country-style vegetable soup(health conscious)
directions: In large saucepan, combine onion, carrots, potatoes, celery, zucchini, salt, pepper, bay leaves and parsley.
Cover with stock; bring to a boil and simmer, covered, for 45 to 60 minutes.
Remove bay leaves and serve.

title: christmas tree salad
directions: Dissolve Jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Let cool.
Add Philadelphia cream cheese, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Mix with beater.
Add nuts.
For tree effect pour salad mixture in coffee cup liners.
Gel.
Dip in hot water to loosen.
Turn upside down on leaf of lettuce.
Top with Cool Whip.
Place a Maraschino cherry on top of tree for effect, or pour into small square pan.

title: ham barbecue
directions: In electric roaster combine all the ingredients except ham over high heat, then turn to simmer for 1 hour.
Add chipped ham. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Serves 65 to 75.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook bacon until done.
Brown diced onion.
Add to other ingredients.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: roulards (rinderrouladen)
directions: Cut eye of round into thin slices and beat slices with tenderizer on both sides to thin out. Spread mustard onto the beef slices. Place bacon, pickle slice and onion slice onto the beef slices. Roll up and tie with string or carpet thread. Put oil in pan and heat (enough oil to brown meat). Brown meat thoroughly. Drain oil out and add enough water to cover. Cover pot and let boil. After it begins boiling, simmer, covered, about 1 1/2 hours. Mix flour and water with salt and pepper. Add to meat and sauce when at a boil and continue boiling until thick. Serves 4 to 6.

title: coconut balls
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients 10 minutes. Add vanilla, pecans and Rice Krispies.
Let cool. Shape into balls and roll in coconut.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine hash browns, 1/2 cup oleo, soup, cheese and onions. Spread evenly into 10 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Top with crushed corn flakes.
Spoon remaining oleo over top . Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sou]per oniony meat loaf for two
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 5 ingredients.
In shallow baking pan, shape into loaf; bake 40 minutes or until done.
Top with Quick Tomato Sauce during last 5 minutes (optional) of baking.

title: kentucky rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 6 x 10-inch glass baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour or more, until center is set.
Do not overcook.
Serves 8. Very moist and flavorful.

title: moon river clam dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, Bleu cheese, chives, salt and Tabasco sauce.
Add drained clams.
Mix (add some milk to obtain smooth consistency.)
Chill.
Serve with crackers.
May substitute with crab meat or shrimp.

title: monkey bread
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon.
Quarter biscuits and roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place biscuit quarters in a greased bundt pan.
In a small saucepan, bring oleo, brown sugar and water to a boil.
Continue to boil for 2 minutes. Remove mixture from heat and pour over biscuits.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350 degrees.
Remove bundt pan from oven and turn upside-down on a platter while still hot.
Allow to cool and remove monkey bread from bundt pan.

title: sweet potatoes with pecan topping
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in a saucepan.
In a separate pan, mix the brown sugar, pecans, flour and 3/4 stick butter and heat.
Put sweet potato mixture in casserole dish.
Pour second mixture over them.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fig preserves cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl; add oil, beating well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add buttermilk and vanilla, mixing thoroughly.
Stir in preserves and pecans.
Pour batter into a greased and floured (do not use nonstick spray) 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Pour warm Buttermilk Glaze over warm cake.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Let margarine soften and eggs get to near room temperature. Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream Crisco, margarine and flavoring together.
Add sugar and eggs alternately.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Start in a cold oven.
Bake in 9 or 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 80 minutes (1 hour and 20 minutes).
Turn out and upright on a cooling rack or towel to cool. Do not cut until completely cool; flavor seems to evaporate otherwise.

title: dill dip in cabbage
directions: Rinse cabbage well and remove any damaged outer leaves.
Slice off top of cabbage, then remove inner leaves to form a bowl.
Chill until serving time.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into pie crust.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° to 400° for about 30 minutes or until light brown.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix salad dressing, preserves and onion soup mix.
Pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serve with rice.

title: grandma's never fail kringle
directions: Dissolve yeast cake in warm water.
In a large bowl, put flour, shortening, salt and sugar.
Beat egg yolks.
Add the warm milk and yeast mixture.
Pour all in the flour bowl and mix well. Cover and place in refrigerator for 3 to 4 hours.
Roll out and spread with beaten egg whites, brown sugar, raisins, dates, nuts or whatever you want.
Let rise about 1 hour and bake on cookie sheet for about 1/2 hour in a 350° oven.
Yields 3 kringles.

title: chicken broccoli divan
directions: In 9-inch pie plate or 2-quart oblong baking dish, arrange broccoli and chicken.
In small bowl, combine soup and milk.
Pour over broccoli and chicken. Sprinkle cheese over soup mixture.
In cup, combine bread crumbs and margarine.
Sprinkle over cheese. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches into glass baking dish (8 x 12-inch).
Trim crust from bread and cut into 1/2-inch strips.
Cover peaches with bread strips.
Mix sugar and flour.
Add egg and oleo.
Mix well and pour over peaches and bread.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: sloppy joe's
directions: Fry hamburger, onion, salt, pepper and garlic.
Drain off fat. Add sauce and simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: maryland fried chicken from the chesapeake
directions: Dredge chicken in mixture of flour, salt and pepper. Heat oil in 12-inch iron skillet until almost smoking; add parsley (it will sputter) and fry 5 to 8 seconds; drain on paper towels. Brown chicken in 2 batches, 8 minutes per side; drain on paper towels. Discard drippings, but reserve 3 tablespoons for gravy. Return all chicken to skillet; add water. Cover and cook over low heat 10 minutes; arrange chicken on a large platter and keep warm. (Fried parsley in it sweetens the flavor.)

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Blend together first 3 ingredients.
Add pineapple.
In separate bowl, cube bread.
Add enough milk to moisten bread, then add to other mixture.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: squash souffle
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender; drain well.
Mash.
Add salt, pepper, cheese, butter, egg yolks, milk and crackers.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° until brown and firm (about 35 to 40 minutes).
Serve hot.

title: best ever  cream cheese fruit dip
directions: Mix with mixer until creamy.
Drain pineapple and then it can be made into a roll.

title: scallop casserole
directions: Combine scallops and soup in a greased casserole dish; let stand.
Melt butter and add bread crumbs to make topping.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: tiger butter
directions: Combine white chocolate and peanut butter in microwave-safe bowl; melt until liquid.
Pour into greased cookie sheet.
Melt semi-sweet chocolate chips until liquid; pour on top of peanut butter mixture.
Use a fork and swirl until marbled effect. Refrigerate 2 hours.
Turn upside down and break into small pieces (or cut).

title: oven fried chicken (potato flakes)
directions: In a plastic bag combine potato flakes and seasonings.
In shallow bowl combine egg and lemon juice.
Dip chicken pieces in egg mixture.
Shake in plastic bag.
Place chicken, skin side up, in ungreased 15 x 10-inch jellyroll pan.
Bake uncovered for 60 to 75 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Gives 6 servings.

title: sunshine punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Sprite.
Freeze solid; thaw until the punch base is a thick slush (at least 1/2 still frozen).
Mix with chilled Sprite at a ratio of 2 to 1 (Sprite and punch base).

title: gooey bars
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and oleo.
Press into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: vegetable rice bake
directions: In a saucepan, combine bouillon granules and 1 1/2 cups water. Bring to boil; add rice.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes or until tender.

title: german cole slaw
directions: Put shredded cabbage into bowl.
Cook bacon; remove from pan and add to cabbage.
Then add pickle relish and bacon grease.
Mix thoroughly and serve immediately.

title: lo-cal dill dip
directions: Blend cottage cheese until smooth in blender.
Add remaining ingredients and blend to mix.
Chill.
Serve with fresh vegetables.
Yield: About 1 cup.

title: zucchini bread(makes two 9 x 5-inch loaves)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with electric mixer.
Mix in flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
Add shredded zucchini and then nuts.

title: amaretto punch
directions: Make the orange juice according to the package directions. One half hour before serving, pour in the orange juice.
Drop the ice cream in. Add the Amaretto, more if you like.
Add the ice cubes or ice ring.

title: asparagus cheese casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Blend in flour.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly and cook until mixture thickens.
Add salt, pepper and cheese and mix well.
Alternate layers of asparagus with egg slices in a buttered casserole.
Cover with cheese sauce.
Top with buttered crumbs or Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: simple corn souffle
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix dressing, egg yolks, flour, sugar and pepper in large bowl until smooth.
Stir in corn, cheese and onions.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; fold into corn mixture.
Pour batter into greased 4-cup souffle dish or 9-inch square baking dish.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings.

title: roast squirrels
directions: Dress and clean squirrels.
Wash in several waters.
Cover with cooking oil mixed with lemon juice; let stand for 1 hour.
Combine crumbs with enough milk to moisten mushrooms, salt, pepper and onion juice.
Stuff squirrels with mixture; sew and truss.
Place in roaster; baste with olive oil or bacon fat.
Roast, uncovered, at 325° until tender for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.
Baste every 15 minutes with fat.
Serves 6.

title: apricot-raspberry torte
directions: Combine cake mix, nectar and egg whites.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Pour into 2 (8-inch) pans, sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until done.
Cool 15 minutes.
Turn out onto wire racks.
Cool.
Slice each cake in half horizontally to make 4 layers.
Spread jam between layers.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch round baking pans.
Combine all ingredients, except walnuts, in large bowl, mixing at low speed for 30 seconds and scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until wooden pick inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Spread cake layer with Butterscotch Filling and sprinkle with walnuts.
Top with second cake layer and pour Chocolate Chip Glaze over top of cake.
Garnish with additional walnuts.

title: margaret's mom's karmel korn
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil, without stirring, for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soda and vanilla.
Gradually pour over popped corn, mixing well.

title: caramel fudge
directions: Put 4 cups sugar, the cream and butter on slow fire.
While this is cooking, put the remaining cup of sugar in a skillet and caramelize over a slow fire.
When the mixture comes to a boil, add the burnt sugar and milk to it.
Cook until it reaches a soft ball when tested in cold water.
(Cook long enough.)
Let cool, then add vanilla.
Beat until thick, add nuts and marshmallows.
Pour into a buttered dish.
Cut when cool into about 3 dozen pieces.
I use the small marshmallows.

title: chili con queso
directions: In double boiler melt Velveeta and American cheese (a few cubes at a time).
Brown onions in a separate pan, add chili and tomatoes and keep warm.
When cheese has melted, add the chili, etc.
Mix gradually.
This freezes well so make a big batch.
Dip for use with nachos.

title: light spinach dip(low-fat recipe)
directions: Process cottage cheese in food processor or blender until smooth.
Place in medium bowl and set aside.
Press spinach between paper towels until barely moist.
Add spinach and remaining ingredients to cheese mixture; stir well.
Cover and refrigerate about 3 hours.
Serve with nonfat crackers or fresh raw vegetables. Makes 3 cups (twelve 1/4 cup servings).

title: boiled turkey
directions: Use a large stewing pot.
Fill it with enough water to cover turkey.
Put whole turkey in pot, turn on burner high enough to boil water.
When water boils, turn timer on for 1 hour, depending on if turkey is frozen or unfrozen.
Boil until meat on wings is done.
It comes off bone slightly when done.
The turkey remains soft and tastes like turkey out of the oven.
It saves time to cook and does not have the fat content involved.
If stuffing is necessary, make it separate in the oven.
This cooking is for plain unstuffed turkey.

title: instant pudding delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and walnuts together for crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup of Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Beat pudding with milk and vanilla until thick.
Spread over 2nd layer.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with additional nuts.
Chill.
Keeps several days in refrigerator.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until they are light and foamy.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients, sifted together.
Pour into 3 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Test for doneness with a toothpick.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix butter, 1 cup sugar, egg, vanilla, soda, tartar and half of the flour.
Slowly add the other half of the flour.
Either chill the dough and roll it into balls after it is well chilled and firm and roll the balls into the sugar and cinnamon.
Or spoon the cookies onto the cookie sheet and dust them with the cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack. Makes about 34 cookies.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Place in layers in casserole with fish sticks first.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cover with grated cheese and crushed potato chips.
Bake until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: snap peas with ham and pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Meanwhile, heat oil in skillet.
Add garlic and snap peas and saute, stirring over high heat until peas are slightly browned, about 2 minutes. Add ham and heat through.
Remove from heat and discard garlic. Add cooked pasta to skillet.
Stir in thyme and mustard and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serve hot or at room temperature. Serves 2.

title: rapid roast
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Make sure roast is at room temperature. Rub roast with garlic and salt.
Place, uncovered, in heated oven for 37 to 40 minutes. Turn off oven. Do not open door for exactly 2 hours.

title: marinated carrots
directions: In a large saucepan over medium heat, cook carrots in a small amount of water until crisp-tender.
Drain and cool.
Place in a 3-quart serving bowl.
Add green pepper and onion; set aside.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in ice cream freezer.
Crank until firm.
Use chocolate supplement and leave out fruit, if desired.

title: marie's meat loaf
directions: Add milk and bread crumbs to egg. Let set 5 minutes. Add meat, onion, salt, sage, and pepper. Form into loaf. Place in greased loaf pan. Mix together brown sugar, catsup, nutmeg, and mustard. Pour over meat loaf and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken tetrazzini(low-fat)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend liquid Butter Buds, flour and seasonings over low heat in a saucepan; stir and cook until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in broth and skim milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in wine, spaghetti, chicken and mushrooms.
Pour into a 9 1/2 x 11-inch casserole dish that has been sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray.
Sprinkle with both cheeses.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes, or until bubbly.
To brown, place briefly under broiler. Serves 6.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into baking dish. Top with buttered Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix powdered sugar, 2 cups flour and butter; press into pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot chicken salad in stuffing crust
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, combine stuffing mix and margarine; reserve 1/2 cup.
To remaining stuffing, add eggs; mix well.
Spoon into greased 9-inch pie pan plate.
Press on bottom and up sides of rim to form crust.
In a large bowl, combine remaining ingredients except reserved stuffing.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until hot.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add rest of ingredients.
Put in greased loaf pan.
Start in cold oven and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: cheesy macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Drain.
Stir in butter and 1 1/2 cups Cheddar cheese and 1/2 cup Velveeta cheese cubes. Combine eggs and milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over macaroni mixture, stirring to combine.
Pour macaroni mixture into a greased or ungreased 2-quart casserole or bowl.
Top with remaining Cheddar and Velveeta cheese.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: jean's applesauce cake
directions: Gradually add brown sugar to shortening, creaming until fluffy.
Add egg.
Beat hard. Stir in applesauce. Sift flour with salt, soda and spices.
Add to first mixture and beat smooth.
Add nuts.
Bake in well-greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan at 350° moderate oven for 45 to 55 minutes or in two round 8 or 9-inch layer pans, 35 to 40 minutes until done.
Cool on rack.
Frost as you wish. Stays fresh and moist to the last bite.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer cooked, deboned chicken in large baking dish.
Retain 1/2 can of chicken broth in a bowl and set aside.
Mix all soups and the remaining 1/2 can of chicken broth, stirring well.
Spread stuffing evenly over chicken.
Pour the set aside portion of chicken broth over the stuffing.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: zesty bread sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Unroll dough. Cut into 32 strips. Combine eggs, butter, flour, onion salt, garlic powder and parsley flakes in bowl.
Mix well. Dip each dough strip in mixture to coat. Roll in crushed onions.
Place on baking sheet. Bake 10 minutes.
May twist each strip before baking.
Serves 10 to 15.

title: knee patches
directions: Mix flour, milk, egg and salt.
Flatten dough and cut into squares (more flour or milk may be needed, you decide).
Deep-fry in at least 2 1/2 inches of cooking oil until golden brown.
Stack on plate and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: salmon chowder
directions: Saute onion in 1/2 stick butter. Add potatoes and garlic and cook 5 to 10 minutes, covered. Add broth, carrots, corn, peppers, corn and tomatoes to the pot and cook until potatoes are done. Add salmon and cook until done. Add heavy cream and cheese and heat until cheese is melted.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix together and pour in ungreased pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix the green beans and mushroom soup together and place in baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle onion straws on top.
Bake for another 5 minutes or until onion straws are golden brown.
This is delicious as a side dish and is very low in carbs!!!

title: bits 'o brickle dessert
directions: Roll cookies into crumbs.
Mix with margarine.
Spread into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix 2 boxes pudding with 2 cups milk.
Add ice cream and blend together. Pour into cooled crust.
Let chill.
Cover with prepared Dream Whip.
Top with Bits 'O Brickle.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt the butter and brown sugar together.
Cool slightly;
add egg
and
vanilla.
Sift
together the flour, baking powder
and salt;
stir
into
the butter mixture.
Add nuts. Turn
into
a greased 9 x 9-inch baking pan and bake about 30 minutes in a moderate oven (350°).

title: dressing
directions: Serve over fruit or jello salad.

title: glaze for duck
directions: Mix all together.
Pour over duck.
Roast at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 325° until done.

title: apple crisp
directions: Fill bottom of an 8 x 8-inch baking dish with apples.
Cover with water and cinnamon.
Combine sugar, flour and margarine until crumbly.
Top apples with flour mixture and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Serve hot with milk or lite Cool Whip.
This recipe can also be used with sliced peaches.
Yields 9 servings.

title: rice meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
With wet hands, shape meat into balls and place in skillet.

title: stuffed avocado
directions: Cut avocados in half and carefully remove meat.
Sprinkle skins inside with lemon juice.
Mash avocado meat in bowl and add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pile back into shells and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot with rice.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Sift 1 cup sugar and flour together; add to milk.
Beat egg yolks; add.
Cook until mixture begins to thicken.
Add margarine, 1 teaspoon vanilla and coconut.
Reserve enough coconut to sprinkle on top.
Cook until thick.
Pour into pie crust.
Beat egg whites until thick; add remaining sugar and vanilla.
Beat until stiff.
Put on pie; sprinkle with reserved coconut.
Put in oven and brown.

title: sweet cream-style potato salad
directions: Cook and mash potatoes as for mashed potatoes.
Don't put much milk.
Add 1 tablespoon butter, salt and pepper to taste.
Chop eggs, onion, pickle and add pimento.
Add to mashed potatoes.
Add vinegar a little at a time.
Add sugar a little at a time.
Let set overnight.

title: dill crackers
directions: Pour oil over crackers and add all the rest over the crackers, dry.
Mix well with hands.
Chill at least 30 minutes.

title: tomato cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° in 13 x 9 greased pan for 40 minutes.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Add enough milk to make a stiff dough.
Mash 1 medium size baked sweet potato.
Add to dough with 1 teaspoon baking powder. Knead well and make into biscuits.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies (we use a Ziploc bag and a rolling pin; can also use a blender).
Cream together the cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar.
In second bowl, mix pudding and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add cream cheese mixture to pudding mixture.

title: ranch beans
directions: Brown onions and hamburger.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Mix with remaining ingredients and place in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: butterscotch nut fudge
directions: Melt butter in a heavy saucepan.
Add brown sugar and heat to boiling.
Add the granulated sugar and sour cream.
Cook over low heat, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Cook to soft ball stage (238° on candy thermometer).
Remove from heat and let cool to lukewarm (119°) without stirring.
When cooled, beat mixture until it is thick enough to hold its shape.
Add the vanilla and nuts and quickly spread into a greased pan.
Cool and cut into squares. Makes about 2 1/2 dozen pieces.

title: lemon bread
directions: Grease dish and line with wax paper on bottom.
Blend oleo and sugar, then eggs.
Alternate dry ingredients with milk.
Add rind of lemon and chopped nuts.
About 5 minutes after cooling, turn out onto rack.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: potato candy
directions: Peel potato.
Cook in small amount of water.
When tender, smash or beat until smooth.
Add powdered sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Work in until able to roll out on powdered area to thickness of 1/4-inch to 1/3-inch.
Spread enough peanut butter to cover area.
Roll like jellyroll, starting with long area.
Roll may be cut into 2 or 3 pieces.
Roll in bar in wax paper. Refrigerate.
Slice when ready to eat.
Put back in refrigerator.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Combine noodles and next 3 ingredients with Miracle Whip.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in the bottom pie crust.
Put top crust on; pinch edges together.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon and sugar.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Then add rice and soups; simmer low until bubbles start. Then mix in thawed broccoli. Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour melted margarine and milk into a bowl and mix.
Pour over mixture; spread shredded cheese over and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Pour evenly 1/2 cup melted butter over top and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: crystal pickles
directions: Cut pickles in very thin slices.
Weigh pickles.
Place in large jar or crock.
Add equal weight of sugar.
Let stand 3 days. Pickles will be crisp and clear.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Make crust of shortening, water and enough self-rising flour to make stiff dough.
Roll dough out thick.
Spread with chopped apples.
Roll up as for jelly roll and with sharp knife slice and drop into melted margarine.
Place in oven and cook at 350°
until lightly brown.

title: delicious cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg, nuts and flour with baking powder.
Add chocolate and vanilla.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 9 minutes.

title: college special
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain peas and tuna.
Drain macaroni.
Combine macaroni, cheese, margarine and milk.
Mix well.
Add tuna and peas.
Mix again.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until completely warmed.

title: herring salad(sildesalat)
directions: Toss all ingredients together.
Refrigerate for 3 hours. Mound on a platter.
Garnish with hard-boiled egg and parsley.

title: crawfish pie
directions: Melt butter.
Saute onions and parsley in butter. Add flour and blend well.
Add soup as in the can.
Add no water to it. Simmer 5 minutes. Add crawfish tails (drained). Simmer 10 more minutes on very low heat.
Prebake small pie shells at 350° for about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Fill with crawfish filling.
Bake filled shells for 10 minutes.
These are absolutely delicious!

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Stir in sifted dry ingredients. Chill dough several hours. Roll out small portions on lightly floured board to 1/8-inch. Cut with floured cookie cutters. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes until light browned. Cool on racks. Makes 5 to 6 dozen cookies.

title: ginger's egg rolls
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Add alternately (in small amounts) with brown sugar and soy sauce.
Cook until just tender.
Put small amount of ground chuck mixture in center of wrap.
Moisten edges with baking powder and water mixture.
Fold sides to center and moisten edges, then starting at the top, roll firmly and seal with water and baking powder mixture.
Drop in hot oil until brown. Drain on paper towels.

title: chicken paprekash(pawp-pre-kash)
directions: Brown the chicken in butter and paprika.
Dump browned chicken and remaining butter into large stewing pan.
Add the vegetables which have been cleaned and cut into chunks (small things may be left whole).
Add spices and water.
Stew over low fire for several hours in covered pan.
Additional water may be added, if needed.
(More vegetables may be added, if desired; however, those quantities given are minimum for this dish.)

title: vegetable-curry casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to package directions; drain. Combine vegetables and next 4 ingredients; spoon into a lightly greased 1-quart casserole.
Combine breadcrumbs and butter; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly and lightly browned.
Yields 4 servings.

title: green beans of the sea salad
directions: Put first 5 ingredients into large bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Pour mixture of remaining ingredients on and toss.
Sprinkle on:

title: bohemian cake
directions: Beat sugars and Crisco.
Add one egg at a time.
Beat well. Add other ingredients.
Fold in nuts and coconut.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: martha jean's strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup of boiling water; let cool.
Add 1/2 cup cold water or pineapple juice, crushed pineapple, mashed bananas and frozen strawberries.
Place half of the mixture in a mold and let jell.
Spread with 1 pint of sour cream.
Pour rest of mixture on top of sour cream and chill 4 or more hours.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift onto wax paper, flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Beat in 3-quart bowl, brown sugar, egg and shortening until light and fluffy.
Mix in dry ingredients alternately with applesauce.
Stir in raisins.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Serve warm or cool.
Sift powdered sugar lightly over top before serving.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Sift brown sugar and white sugar together if brown sugar is lumpy.
Cream together sugar, shortening and margarine until fluffy.
Cream together with eggs and fluff again.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Alternately add it and milk to creamed mixture. Add nuts and maple flavoring.
Bake in Bundt pan at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients. Combine egg, milk and oil. Add to dry ingredients.
Stir until moistened.
Bake on hot griddle.

title: pancakes
directions: Beat egg in a bowl. Add rest of ingredients to egg. Using mixer, beat until smooth. For variation, add blueberries or raisins after turning on griddle.

title: rice and sausage
directions: Saute the sausage, onion, pepper and garlic, breaking the sausage into small pieces.
Add all other ingredients; mix well and pour into a 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake at 300° for about 1 hour. Serves 8.

title: japanese noodles
directions: Heat oil in wok or frypan.
Stir-fry chicken 3 to 5 minutes. Meanwhile, cook noodles in boiling salted water until just tender. Drain and rinse under hot water.
Leave in colander to dry.
Add cabbage and onions to chicken along with soy sauce, pepper and sesame oil.
Cook 1 minute and toss in noodles.
Toss.

title: quick potato chocolate fudge
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over hot water.
Add mashed potatoes, salt and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Blend in sugar. Knead until smooth.
Press into buttered 8-inch square pan. Cool. Cut into squares.

title: hot dogs on a stick
directions: Mix all the ingredients well to coat hot dogs.
Then deep fry until golden brown.
These are very good.
Kids love them.

title: party potatoes
directions: Peel, cook and drain potatoes.
Beat sour cream and cream cheese until well blended.
Add gradually to hot potatoes, beating constantly, until light and fluffy.
Add seasonings to taste.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: On a 12-inch glass plate layer ingredients in order given. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Serve with corn chips. This is a good Mexican-flavored dip for a crowd!

title: sweet potato angel biscuit
directions: Combine yeast and warm water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and sugar in a large bowl. Cut in shortening with pastry blender or fork until crumbly.
Add yeast mixture and potatoes, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead 5 minutes.
Place dough in a lightly greased bowl.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight.
Roll dough 1/2-inch thick. Cut with a 2-inch round cutter and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Let rise in a warm place for 20 to 25 minutes.
Bake at 400° until lightly brown.

title: easy microwave divinity
directions: Combine sugar, water and salt in a 2-quart glass dish. Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir.
Attach a microwave-safe candy thermometer to bowl.
Microwave on High to a temperature of 265° or hard-ball stage.
Place Marshmallow Creme in a large mixing bowl.
Pour hot syrup in, a bit at a time, beating with an electric mixer until candy will hold a fairly stiff peak.
Stir in nuts, vanilla and food coloring if desired.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: pecan roll
directions: Roll or crush vanilla wafers until powder.
Add pecans and milk.
Roll into long log with Reynolds Wrap.
Store in freezer.

title: diet soup
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Season as desired.
Cook for about 1 hour or until done.

title: cherry nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs. Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Add alternately with liquid. Mix in other ingredients and pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oven apple pancakes
directions: Combine eggs, milk, flour and salt; beat with whisk or rotary beater until smooth.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; toss with apples to coat.
Grease two 9-inch pie plates with butter.
Put half of the apples in each pie plate.
Pour half of the batter over apples in each plate.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until light brown.
Serve hot, cut in wedges.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.
(Can be successfully cut in half.)

title: cream of broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add water and bouillon.
Heat to boil; stir until cubes dissolve gradually.
Add noodles and salt. Cook 3 minutes.
Cook and drain broccoli.
Add to broth and noodles.
Add garlic powder; cook 4 minutes.

title: iced almonds
directions: Heat almonds in heavy skillet along with sugar and butter. Stir until almonds are toasted and sugar is brown, about 15 minutes. Stir in vanilla. Drop in clusters. Sprinkle with a little salt. Cool.

title: settlers beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350°, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple bread and topping
directions: Mix in the order given.
Place in greased pans.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan; bring to boil.
Pour over patties.
Bake in 350° oven for about 15 minutes.

title: giblet stuffing for roast turkey
directions: Boil giblet and neck bone in lightly salted water until tender.
(Pressure	cook for about 15 minutes is better.) Cool and remove
meat
from neck bone, cut it and the giblets into very small pieces and set aside.
Break up sausage roll(s) in a	large heated
skillet.
Drain
fat; add onions and celery. Saute lightly.
Add giblets, apples, walnuts, raisins, stuffing
mix and
chicken
broth.
Mix
well, heating it through. Allow to cool before stuffing.
Do not stuff turkey until just before
putting turkey
in	oven.
Rub
salt
inside cavities before stuffing.

title: old fashioned chocolate cake
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients and pour into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Pour warm water over all and mix.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in ungreased pan.

title: best brownies
directions: Melt and cool the shortening.
Blend cocoa, sugar and eggs. Add combined dry ingredients (flour, baking powder and salt). Stir in the chopped nuts and vanilla.
Bake in a 9-inch square pan for 25 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with floured fork.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Cookies brown around edge. Makes about 7 dozen.

title: blueberry pancake syrup
directions: In a saucepan, combine blueberries, honey and enough water to just cover the berries.
Bring to a boil and boil 5 minutes.
In a separate bowl, mix flour with the 1 cup water until smooth.
Stir mixture into hot berries; cook until slightly thickened.
Stir in lemon juice.
Serve either hot or cold.
Also makes good ice cream topping.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip muffins
directions: Combine oats and milk; allow to stand 15 minutes.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Stir egg, oil, 1/2 cup brown sugar, chocolate chips and 1/2 cup pecans into oat mixture.
In a large bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add oat mixture to flour mixture, stirring just until all dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill each cup of
a lightly greased 12-cup muffin tin 2/3 full with batter. Sprinkle tops with remaining brown sugar and pecans.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until the top of a muffin springs back when lightly touched.
Serves 12.

title: squash relish
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook for 20 minutes.
Slowly pour into hot sterile jars and seal.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces and parboil.
Cut up broccoli and parboil.

title: dad's favorite chicken and sausage gumbo
directions: Cook eggs and put the soup in.

title: nachos
directions: Cook hamburger and drain.
Combine pinto beans, taco sauce, Chili-O and tomato paste.
Add water to desired thickness and bring to a boil.
Pour chili mixture over nachos.
Add onions, cheese, tomatoes and sour cream.

title: pasties
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except the mushroom soup.

title: cherry pie
directions: Bring frozen cherries, sugar, flour and extract to boil.
Cook one minute, cool.
Pour filling in crust.
Place pie in 425° oven and bake for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Make jello with hot water and drained pineapple juice.
Add all but sour cream.
Put 1/2 of mix in a 7 x 9-inch pan (about 2 1/2 cups).
Refrigerate.
Keep other 1/2 at room temperature. When set, spread sour cream on top and put remaining mix on top. Refrigerate until serving time.
Keep unserved part in refrigerator.

title: pul kogee(fire meat)
directions: You can use pork or chicken or even ground beef.
The chicken does not have to be paper thin.

title: rosamarina
directions: Boil the first 6 ingredients until thick, then cool.
Add the rosamarina.
Mix together with the Cool Whip.

title: good salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Stir in sherbet and drained fruit.
Chill until congealed.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 35 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with oleo.
Sprinkle rice in pan evenly.
Place chicken pieces on rice.
Mix soup and water; pour over chicken and rice.
Sprinkle onion soup mix on top.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Bring first 6 ingredients to boil and let cool slightly.
Pour over vegetables.

title: crescent cream squares
directions: Line bottom of dish with one can of rolls.
Mix together cheese, vanilla, sugar and eggs (minus 1 egg white).
Spread over rolls.
Put other rolls on top.
Brush with egg white.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Melt oleomargarine.
Work
in
peanut butter and sugar. Chill overnight.	Melt
chocolate
chips and paraffin together in double boiler or
microwave.
Dip
chilled	peanut	butter mixture in chocolate and
place
on
wax paper.
Peanut butter mixture may be shaped as desired or cut into squares.

title: lemonade ice tea
directions: Brew tea using water and tea bags.
Mix tea, sugar and lemonade.
Just before serving, stir in ginger ale and pour over crushed ice.
Garnish with sprig of mint.
Makes 10 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Tear chicken breasts into pieces and put into a baking dish. Combine soup, milk and pour over chicken; add butter dotted around the top.
Add prepared stuffing on the top and bake at 350° until brown.

title: carnival cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening with both sugars; add eggs, one at a time, and blend well.
Stir in oatmeal and Raisin Bran.
Sift flour with baking powder and soda.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and peanuts.
Roll into small balls; place on greased baking sheet and press with the tines of a fork to flatten.
Bake in moderately hot oven (375°) for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 7 dozen small cookies.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Mix together slightly beaten eggs, milk, salt, mustard, cheese and bread.
Add sausage.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May store in refrigerator overnight and bake in the morning. Serves 6 to 8.

title: a dish of christmas cheer
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water for 20 minutes.
Drain.
Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain off excess fat.
Combine ground beef, soups, sour cream and Italian seasoning into large saucepan and simmer for 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Serve immediately.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cube steak dinner
directions: Dip cube steak in milk, then in flour to coat.
Place in hot oil in electric skillet.
Brown on both sides.
Add cubed potatoes, soup and water.
Cook on low until potatoes are tender. Serve with salad or vegetable for a quick meal.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix together; pour into crust and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and sugars.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and make patties. Brown in a little fat. Remove browned patties. To the grease, add the flour. Stir until browned. Add the water and gravy.
Return patties to baking dish. Add gravy.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine soup, milk, cheese and pepper. Add noodles and chicken.
Over low heat, heat through, stirring occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: party punch
directions: Combine water with concentrates; stir.
Add pineapple juice, sugar and lime juice; chill.
When ready to serve, pour over ice and add ginger ale and carbonated water.

title: three bean salad
directions: Combine drained beans, green pepper, celery, onion and pimiento in large bowl.
Combine the vinegar, sugar, oil, salt and pepper.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour mixture over vegetables and mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight, stirring occasionally.
Drain before serving.
Makes 10 generous servings.

title: white bread macaroons
directions: Trim crust from bread; cut into strips.
Dip into Eagle Brand milk.
Roll in coconut.
Lay on well-buttered cookie sheet and bake at about 350° until golden brown.
These are delicious.

title: hot corn
directions: Mix and bake at 350 degrees till hot and bubbly, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: turkey burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into quarter pound patties.
Best if grilled over charcoal, medium heat, for approximately 10 minutes each side.

title: shoe peg corn
directions: Cook Shoe Peg corn until almost done.
Add cream cheese and green chiles.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook corn until done. If mixture becomes too thick, add a little milk.
Serve hot.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Slowly add milk, blending in mixture.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Freeze until firm, then wrap after pie is frozen.
To serve: while frozen cut into small pieces.
Return to freezer.
Let cut pieces stand 5 to 8 minutes before serving.
Pie stays "creamy-smooth" even when kept frozen for a week.

title: wassail
directions: Combine ingredients in large Dutch oven and simmer over low heat approximately 2 hours before serving.

title: cherry coconut bars
directions: Pastry:
Combine flour, butter and powdered sugar.
Mix until smooth.
Spread into square pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream oleo, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour (just a little at a time) and beat well after each addition. Add vanilla.
Pour in heated and greased Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix pie filling and condensed milk.
Add pineapple, Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Mix well.
This also freezes well.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Makes 2 large pies, 9-inch.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, then turn to 350° and continue baking until done (total baking approximately 1 hour).

title: banana split brown pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare brownie mix in batter bowl according to package directions.
Place parchment paper on 15-inch pizza pan.
Pour brownie mixture on paper and spread into a 15-inch circle.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until set.
Cool to room temperature.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Peel carrots, slice and cook until barely tender.
Drain. Heat oil, soup, vinegar, soup and spices until blended.
Combine carrots, peppers and onion.
Pour heated vinegar mixture over all. Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown beef, onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Drain.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Simmer uncovered 20 minutes.
Cook spaghetti as directed.
Drain.
Toss with butter.
Serve sauce over spaghetti. Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: mom's pizzelles
directions: Beat eggs and add all other ingredients, then add flour. Press with Italian pizzelle iron until golden brown.

title: chocolate pie(microwave filling)
directions: Microwave on High about 13 to 14 minutes, stirring every 3 to 4 minutes.
Put in baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well; add milk and egg.
Place in 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan or deep pie plate.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° or until lightly browned.
Cut and top with sweetened strawberries.
Add whipped cream, milk or both.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Drain clams, save liquid, and chop the clams.
(I cook my clams about five minutes and then put them into a blender to chop with the liquid.)
Fry bacon until brown.
Remove.
Add onion and celery to bacon fat; cook until tender.
Add clams and liquid, potatoes and seasonings; cook for 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add milk and heat.
Garnish with chopped parsley.
Serves 6.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems and clean with mushroom brush any debris from mushroom caps.
Chop stems into small pieces.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry out bacon, adding onion and green pepper.
Add beans, mustard, brown sugar, ketchup and cubes.
Heat all in pan and serve.
Break bacon up after frying and put in baked beans.

title: dave's rich and meat chili
directions: Cook beans in water for 30 minutes; drain.
Add chicken broth and cook for 1 hour.
Finely dice the onion, celery and carrots (I do this in a food processor).
Saute the vegetables in margarine for about 5 minutes.
Add to the beans, along with the salt, basil and garlic powder.
Simmer, uncovered, for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger and chopped onion together in skillet.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over hamburger.
Simmer together for 10 to 30 minutes.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix and serve with chips or fresh vegetables.
Preparation time:
5 minutes.

title: grilled salmon
