directions: Catch a 40 pound king salmon fillet and put 3/4 in the freezer for the future.
Grill over charcoal.
Before putting on grill, season with garlic and onion salt and liberally coat top side with Parmesan.
Serve with sauteed fiddlehead ferns, sour dock salad, herring eggs on kelp and rhubarb pie.

title: tyl's stew
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain grease.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Cook on low heat for 40 minutes or longer.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Chill to serve.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: caramel cookies
directions: Melt butter and 1/3 cup evaporated milk together.
Beat into cake mix.
Add nuts.
Pour 1/2 cake mixture in bottom of greased 7 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Melt caramels with the remaining 1/3 cup evaporated milk in double boiler.
Pour over chocolate chips.
Place rest of cake mixture on top of caramels.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool; cut in squares.

title: mexican cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients; shape in ball.
Sprinkle or roll in taco shredded cheese.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix together butter and sugar until creamy.
Add egg and vanilla.
In a separate bowl mix together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Slowly mix dry mixture into sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Using 1 teaspoon of batter, roll in a ball.
Put on greased cookie sheet and press down slightly.
Sprinkle with colored sugar.
Bake at 325° for approximately 10 minutes until golden.

title: strawberry chocolate delight
directions: Mix Jell-O.
Pour in dessert cups and chill for two hours or until fully firm.
Grate the chocolate and set aside.
Top Jell-O cups with Cool Whip and then sprinkle on grated chocolate.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: lucille's lemon pie
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Cut Crisco in well.
Then add ice water. Mix well with a fork until the mixture holds together.

title: mexicali taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and add onion and beans.
Season hamburger with taco sauce.
Add other ingredients and mix in a large bowl just before serving.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: In baking dish, layer cracker crumbs, asparagus, salt and pepper and grated cheese.
Pour milk over it to make soggy.
Bake for about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into small flowerets.
Cook bacon until crisp, cut up.
Add all ingredients in bowl.
Add mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over the ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill before serving.

title: tantalizing taco pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 400°.
Thaw pie crust 10 minutes.
Prick bottom and sides thoroughly with fork.
Bake crust on cookie sheet for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and reduce oven temperature to 350°.

title: ghoul-ade
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and sugar in large pitcher.
Just before serving, add the ginger ale.
Serve over ice.

title: beef logs
directions: Mix cheese, almonds, garlic salt and milk to spreading consistency.
Spread each meat slice with cheese mixture.
Roll up log fashion.
Chill.
Slice into bite size pieces.

title: cheese struedel
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and egg yolk. Spread 1 package crescent rolls in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Pinch at perforations to keep from separating.
Pour cream cheese mixture evenly to cover dough. Spread second stretched crescent dough over top. Brush with egg white over top.
Bake in glass pan at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes. Bake in metal pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: old fashion pie
directions: Mix
all
ingredients; just keep adding flour until the dough gets
hard.
Put dough in ice box overnight.
Roll dough thin; add filling.
Bake at 350°.

title: farm fried potatoes
directions: Parboil potatoes and slice thin.
Peel and slice onions, chop green pepper, broil bacon and dice.
Add the rest to large skillet. Melt butter in skillet.
Stir all gently.
Cook at medium temperature until brown and bubbly.

title: "philly" cream cheese salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Let set until thick.
Add softened cream cheese; mix well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill until set.

title: zucchini lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in a skillet until crumbly; drain well.
Add tomato sauce, salt, oregano, basil and pepper.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Slice zucchini lengthwise 1/4-inch thick.
Blend cottage cheese and egg in bowl.
Alternate layers of zucchini sprinkled with flour, cottage cheese mixture and sauce in a rectangular baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch until all ingredients are used.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes. Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting.
Makes 8 servings.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Cut beef into tiny bite size pieces, trimming away all fat. Season to taste with Accent, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Roll in flour.
Saute, until browned, in a small amount of cooking oil. After meat is browned, drain off oil.
Add 1 envelope Lipton dry onion soup mix.
Add 2 cups cold water.
Cover.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes, stirring to keep from sticking.
Just before removing from heat, add sour cream and stir.
Serve over egg noodles which have been prepared according to directions.

title: home made pancake syrup
directions: Put both sugars in a sauce pan.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Let cool and add maple flavoring.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Combine all 6 ingredients in top of a double boiler.
Cook over simmering water, stirring occasionally.
When thickened, pour into serving bowl.

title: ham hocks and red beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain.
Place beans in large pot. Cover with water.
Bring to a boil.
Add hocks, onion, red pepper and garlic.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 2 hours or until tender.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Do not peel zucchini, but clean and slice thin.
Add just enough water to cook crisp-tender; drain.
Saute onion in 1 tablespoon margarine, add to zucchini.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Crush tortilla chips in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan to make "crust" for casserole.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix in all canned ingredients and cook on low heat for 4 to 6 minutes, blending all together.
Pour over bed of chips, top with cheese and bake for 12 to 18 minutes or until cheese has melted.
Serves 5 to 7.

title: chocolate eclair cake #4
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with graham crackers.
Mix pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Put 1/2 of this mixture over graham crackers. Place second layer of crackers and remainder of pudding on top. Place third layer of crackers.
Microwave chocolate frosting until melted; pour over crackers.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: swedish mundel korka
directions: Beat eggs very well (5 to 10 minutes).
Add 1 cup sugar and melted shortening.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder and add to egg mixture.
Add almond flavoring.
Beat.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in oil until soft.
Add remaining ingredients except shrimp.
Add water and simmer 1 hour or until okra is soft.
Add shrimp and cook 3 to 5 minutes until pink. Serve hot over rice.
Serves 4.

title: upside-down apple pie(opp-ned eple pie)
directions: Mix together in a bowl.
Sprinkle mixture over apples.
Roll out the other pastry and place on top of the apple mixture.
Punch holes for steam to escape.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes and at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and jello.
Then fold in Cool Whip. Add fruit and chill.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Stir together first 4 ingredients.
Add apples and cherries. Chill two hours.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Then add nuts.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix together and heat until jello is dissolved and cool.
Add 2 cups buttermilk.
Put in the refrigerator for 40 minutes.
Add 8 ounces Cool Whip.

title: haupia(coconut pudding)
directions: Mix cornstarch	and sugar together.
Add enough coconut milk to make
a smooth paste.
Heat the remaining coconut milk to boiling; slowly add the cornstarch paste.
Lower heat; cook until mixture
thickens, stirring to prevent lumps.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan and chill.
Cut into squares.
Serves 9.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer and bake in a greased and floured cake pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook noodles whole as directed on package; drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Place noodles in large bowl and add all ingredients. Mix together by hand and refrigerate.
(I like it better if it refrigerates overnight.)

title: beef barbecue
directions: Chop onion, celery and green pepper.
Place in a frying pan and saute.
Add ground beef and brown.
Add rest of ingredients. Cover and simmer about 1 hour, stirring often.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Melt butter.
Mix with sugar and eggs; beat well.
Fold in bread pieces and pineapple with juice.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: ho-ho cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions and bake.
Beat sugar, butter, Crisco, salt, vanilla and evaporated milk.
Beat 10 minutes.
Spread on cooled cake.

title: hog killing cake
directions: Bake cake.
Bake in 3 layers.
Mix all other ingredients and spread over cake top and sides.

title: blackberry juice cake
directions: Mix well;
pour
in greased cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: buttermilk roast
directions: Cut garlic and rub meat well, pressing some of the garlic into the meat.
Add salt and pepper and dredge with flour.
Brown on all sides in a small amount of fat.
Add buttermilk and cook slowly until tender, about 3 to 4 hours.
The liquid is a delicious gravy.

title: spinach-tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini according to package directions.
Drain in large strainer; rinse with cold water and drain again.

title: spicy sloppy joes
directions: Cook ground beef and sausage in a skillet over medium heat until brown.
Remove from heat and drain as much grease from meat as possible.
Mix meat, Manwich, salt and pepper in saucepan and heat.
Best served the second day.

title: cajun catfish with fried rice
directions: Rub catfish with the 1 tablespoon blackened seasoning (I use a lot more), then coat with cornmeal and flour. Set aside.
Cook bacon, if desired, and set aside (I leave it out!). Saut mushrooms and onions.
Add corn and beans to saut; cook 1 minute. Add rice and stir-fry 1 minute. Stir in chicken broth and the rest of blackened seasoning.
Reduce heat and cook 10 minutes. Stir to prevent sticking.

title: mustard kabob marinade
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil and simmer 5 minutes. I marinate chicken kabobs with this sauce, but if you put it in the fridge, it turns solid again. I usually pour it over while it's hot and let it sit at least 30 minutes before grilling. Put aside what you don't use over the chicken for an excellent dipping sauce.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In a large casserole or baking dish, combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake in the oven for 30 to 45 minutes at 350° to 400° or microwave on High for 10 minutes or until casserole bubbles.

title: pot a'scallops newberg
directions: Put butter in a 2-cup measure and melt on 70% power for 30 seconds.
Mix in the flour and cook on High for 30 seconds.
Stir again and slowly add milk.
Mix in seasonings and cook on 70% for 1 minute; stir.
Cook 30 seconds.
Stir.
Cook for 30 seconds; stir. Set aside.

title: old-fashioned cheese potatoes
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter.
Add the flour, salt and pepper. Cook and stir until a thick paste forms.
Gradually add milk. Cook and stir until mixture begins to thicken.
Place potatoes in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over potatoes. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender. Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain. Preheat oven to 350°.
In
a medium saucepan, melt margarine; stir in milk, cornstarch and salt.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add macaroni.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Heat water to boiling.
Add potatoes and onions.
Boil until potatoes are tender.
Drain off water.
Put 1/2 of vegetables into blender.
Add 1/4 to 1/2 cup of milk.
Blend until smooth.
Return all vegetables to cooking pot.
Stir in remaining ingredients using measurements listed first and then adding salt and pepper to your taste.
Heat, stirring occasionally, until hot.
Add more milk while heating for a thinner soup.

title: water chestnut wraps
directions: Drain water chestnuts and soak in soy sauce to cover, 2 to 3 hours.
Broil bacon until almost done.
Cool.
Wrap bacon slices around water chestnuts and secure with toothpicks.
Broil until bacon is brown and serve.

title: broccoli puff cornbread
directions: Pour in a greased round casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: black-eyed susans
directions: Combine butter and sugars, creaming until light and fluffy; add egg, warm water, vanilla, and peanut butter; beat mixture well.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix water and sugar thoroughly.
Add orange juice, lemonade and pineapple juice with water.
Dilute orange juice and lemonade with water. This can be mixed ahead.
Before serving, add bananas (mashed with a little of the mix), then add to all and add ginger ale.
A ring can be frozen out of mixture.

title: macaroni shrimp salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: pastitsio
directions: Brown beef and onion together in a large frying pan.
Drain off any fat.
Add undrained tomatoes, tomato paste and thyme.
Add 1 teaspoon salt, if desired.
Simmer, covered, 30 minutes.

title: frito pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef.
Add chili and mix well.
In casserole dish, add layer of Fritos (enough to cover the bottom), a layer of meat and 2 slices of cheese.
Repeat these layers 3 times.
Crumble some Fritos chips on top.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes until cheese melts.

title: quick and easy sausage balls
directions: Crumble sausage, brown and drain. Cool slightly and mix with cheese and Bisquick mix, blending well. Shape into small balls. Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheeses and drain pineapple.
Add other ingredients except
chopped
pecans.
Mix
well
and
chill slightly. Roll in chopped
nuts.
Wrap
in plastic wrap, then return to refrigerator until ready to serve with crackers.

title: buster bar torte
directions: Mix Oreos with 1/3 cup melted butter.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread softened ice cream over cookie layer and sprinkle with peanuts.
Freeze a few hours.
Combine remaining ingredients and bring to boil over low heat.
Boil 8 minutes.
Cool before spreading over ice cream.
Return to freezer.

title: parmesan fish fillets
directions: Dip fillets into butter mixture (butter and lemon juice) and arrange in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour remaining butter over fish.
Mix seasonings in bowl, along with cheese and crumbs.
Sprinkle over fish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until fish flakes. Garnish with parsley and lemon wedges.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugars, butter, Crisco, eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients and stir into sugar mixture.
Add oatmeal, chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful onto a cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes.
Yield: approximately 8 to 9 dozen.

title: sunday fried chicken
directions: Combine ingredients.
Coat chicken pieces with mixture. Place in shallow baking pan and bake uncovered for 1 hour or until done at 350°F.
This makes enough coating for several chickens. Store unused mixture in an airtight container.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill. Make into a ball.
Roll the ball
in 1 cup chopped pecans.

title: signature crabcakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together gently so as not to break up lumps. Scoop out onto greased baking pan with ice cream scoop. Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: key lime cheesecake(low in cholesterol and sugar)
directions: Combine crumbs, margarine and sugar substitute (several). Stir well.
Press into bottom of spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Stir yogurt and drain through cheesecloth. Sprinkle gelatin over lime juice.
Let stand 1 minute.
Add 1/2 cup sugar.
Cook until dissolved.
Remove and let cool.
In food processor, blend
cottage cheese, cream cheese and gelatin. Process until smooth.
Add yogurt and process until smooth.
Stir in rind.
Pour over crust.
Cover and chill.

title: oriental cauliflower
directions: Stir soy sauce, water and cornstarch together and set aside. Separate cauliflower into flowerets.
Cut flowerets into 1/4-inch slices.
Cut any large slices in 1/2 to make bite size.
Heat the oil and saute the scallions and mushrooms about 5 minutes.
If the dish is not to be served immediately, stop at this point and continue just before serving.
Add the cauliflower and saute 1 to 2 minutes.
Add the broth and salt.
Bring to a boil and simmer, covered, about 3 minutes or just until the cauliflower can be pricked with a fork.
This step is the key to the entire dish.
The cauliflower must not be overcooked.
Stir in the cornstarch mixture and cook until the sauce thickens, just 1 to 2 minutes.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil for one minute, then add peanut butter.
Stir well until blended, then add oatmeal and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper until set.

title: lemon-pineapple-cream cheese salad
directions: Bring pineapple to boil.
Add lemon Jell-O.
Add cream cheese. Cool.
Add Cool Whip, nuts (chopped) and cherries.
Put in bowl or mold.

title: brownie kiss cups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place 25 foil liners in muffin pan or on cookie sheet.
Combine brownie mix, egg, water and oil in large bowl; stir with spoon until well blended.
Fill each liner with 2 tablespoons batter.
Bake at 350° for 17 to 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Place 1 chocolate candy kiss on each cupcake.
Bake 1 minute longer.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes in pans.
Remove to cooling racks.
Cool completely.
Yields 25 brownie cups.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Put Crisco and 2 cups water in boiler and heat until 120° to 130°.
In mixer, mix together sugar, salt, yeast and 2 cups flour. Add eggs and warm liquids until moistened.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Gradually add 2 cups flour and beat until blended. Remove mixture from mixer and add remaining 2 cups flour by hand and blend well.
Put in greased bowl; cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Remove amount needed and knead with little flour as possible.
Roll out and dip in oleo.
Place on cookie sheet.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake in preheated 425° oven approximately 20 minutes.

title: oven potatoes
directions: Arrange slices of potatoes in flat casserole.
No need to butter dish.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour cream over potatoes, so they are completely covered.
Cover casserole with foil and bake in moderate oven 45 minutes.
Uncover and continue baking for 15 minutes or until potatoes are slightly brown and tender.

title: super moist zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all dry ingredients together (if you are using self-rising flour, eliminate salt, baking soda, and baking powder).
Grease and flour pans.
Mix all wet ingredients together and combine with dry ingredients.
Bake for about 50 minutes for loaf pans and 30-40 minutes for muffins.

title: ella davis' chicken pot pie
directions: Cut Crisco into flour and salt until it resembles coarse corn meal.
Add water and mix altogether.
Roll on floured board until dough stops stretching, then cut into squares.
Drop into boiling chicken broth; cover and cook about 20 minutes.
Dough is done if it goes down under broth after lid is removed and mixture is stirred.

title: tuna croquettes
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour, salt, pepper and dry mustard. Slowly add milk and cook, stirring until thick.
Add tuna, onion, celery, parsley and lemon juice.
Mix well; chill until very cold. Shape into cone shape croquettes; roll in crumbs, then egg which has been mixed with water, then roll in crumbs again.
Fry in deep fat which has been heated, until golden brown.
Serve with Creamy Cheese Sauce.
(See recipe for Creamy Cheese Sauce.)

title: strawberry delight
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Crumble wafers in bottom of dish for crust.
Pour mixture over crumbs.
Put strawberries on top of mixture.
Cover with whipped topping and refrigerate.

title: sugar-free strawberry pie
directions: Mix cornstarch with small amount of "red pop."
Mix all ingredients, except berries.
Microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes. Stir mixture and repeat this step twice.
Add berries to cooked mixture.
Cool until set and pour into baked pie shell.

title: beat and eat frosting
directions: Place egg white, sugar, cream of tartar and vanilla in a deep small bowl.
Mix well, add boiling water; beat at high speed until stiff peaks form.
After 4 to 5 minutes, frost 2 layer cake. Sprinkle with coconut.

title: whip cream frosting
directions: Cook milk and flour slowly until thickened.
Cool.
Cream sugar, crisco, oleo, salt and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.	Add white sauce to sugar mixture.
Beat until fluffy.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk together first, then add remaining ingredients.
Chill for dessert.

title: beef barley soup
directions: In Dutch oven, bring beef and water to a boil.
Skim off foam.
Cover; simmer 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stirring occasionally, simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour or until meat and barley are tender.
Serve immediately.
Refrigerate up to 3 days or freeze up to 3 months.
Serves 12.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until golden brown and a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: broccoli with cheese sauce
directions: Prepare and cook broccoli.
Heat remaining ingredients over medium heat, stirring frequently until cheese is melted and mixture is smooth (6 to 8 minutes).
Pour cheese sauce over broccoli.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheese come to room temperature, then mix all ingredients together by hand.
(Do not use blender or mixer.)
Chill for 1 hour.
Roll into a ball and roll in chopped pecans.
You can also add a few of the chopped pecans to the cheese mix with the other ingredients.

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Blend the sugar and shortening. Add the eggs, one at a time, blending well after each one. Add the flour, sifted with the salt, alternating with the milk.
Add the vanilla flavoring and the food coloring. Blend until color is even.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done in a large tube pan.

title: nicole's chocolate popcorn
directions: Put M&M's in bottom of a bowl.
Pop popcorn and put it in the same bowl.
Mix.
Chocolate will partially melt.

title: italian wedding soup
directions: Combine meat, garlic, egg, and bread crumbs.
Form into very small (1/2 inch) meatballs.
Cook through in skillet or bake. While meat is cooking bring broth to simmer in a large sauce pan. Add noodles and cook according to package directions.
Add meatballs and spinach.
Allow spinach to thaw.
Remove from heat and serve.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant in 1/2-inch crosswise slices.
Saute in oil until brown on both sides and soft.
Season with salt and pepper. Arrange eggplant on platter.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix corn oil and sugar together with spoon until sugar is dissolved. Combine dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture alternating with eggs. Beat after each addition. Add vanilla, chopped apples, and nuts. Batter will be very thick. Put into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours. Cool in pan.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Layer 1/2 can chicken soup in bottom of casserole dish.
Add chicken breasts.
Add remaining soup.
Layer cheese.
Melt butter; mix in stuffing.
Put on top of cheese.
Pour evaporated milk over stuffing.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Cover for first 30 minutes.

title: strawberry rhubarb sauce
directions: Slice rhubarb in small slices.
Combine in large pot with frozen strawberries.
Add a little water and poach over medium heat.
As rhubarb begins to get tender, add sugar.
Simmer until done (about 15 minutes after adding sugar).
Use like applesauce or as topping for cake, pudding, ice cream.

title: kolackies
directions: Mix ingredients until it reaches a smooth dough-like form. With a rolling pin, roll dough on a floured surface.
Cut dough in circles or squares.
Fill with Solo fruit filling.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or lightly browned.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender, 15 minutes. Drain and mash lightly. Beat the eggs with the butter, sugar and salt.
Mix with the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into 8-inch pie plate; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes, until bubbly.
Serve with crackers.

title: creamsicle cake
directions: Bake the orange cake (Duncan Hines makes this flavor!) as directed on package.
Use a 9x13-inch pan.
Allow to cool.
When cooled, use a straw to poke holes in the surface of the cake, the more the better.
(I usually do about 4-5 rows with 8-10 holes per row.)

title: hot wing dip
directions: Mix together. Heat in small crock pot until cheese in melted. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Wash and core bell peppers; boil in water for about 5 minutes, drain.
Mix ground beef, rice, and onion together, salt and pepper to taste.
Add tomato sauce and mix well.
Stuff into peppers.
Bake in oven at 325 degrees for about 30 minutes.

title: strawberry dessert bread
directions: Stir flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and sugar into a large bowl. Make a well in the center. Mix frozen strawberries, eggs, oil or melted margarine and chopped pecans. Pour into dry ingredients (I beat the eggs, then beat in the oil and stir in the strawberries. I also put the pecans in the dry ingredients.) Stir just enough to dampen all ingredients. Pour into two greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. I use 7 small pans and bake about 35 minutes or until tested done!

title: raspberry salad
directions: Bring crushed pineapple and 1/2 cup sugar to a full boil.
Add raspberry jello.
Mix well with cream cheese.
Remove from fire and stir in cream cheese until completely dissolved.
Add ice water and let cool.
Add chopped nuts and diced celery.
Let set in refrigerator until mixture starts to jell.
Add whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Fold into cooled jello.
Let stand 24 hours.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan or mold.
Serves 15.

title: jicama slaw
directions: Heat a dry heavy skillet, preferably cast iron over medium heat.
Add garlic cloves and roast, turning occasionally with tongs until blackened in spots and soft (about 10 minutes).
Peel, removing tough ends.
In blender or food processor, combine garlic, apple cider, oil, vinegar and mustard.
Process until smooth.
Season with salt and pepper.
In salad bowl, combine jicama, carrots and apples.
Add dressing and toss to coat.

title: swiss cheese chicken
directions: Place chicken in a greased baking dish.
Cover with cheese. Spread the soup over the cheese.
Spread the dressing over the top; cover completely.
Pour melted butter over the top.
Bake at 375° for approximately 25 to 30 minutes or until the chicken is completely covered.

title: jenny's company chili
directions: Combine first three ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Cook until brown.
Drain pinto beans; reserve liquid.
Add liquid.
Stir in remaining ingredients (except pinto beans) and simmer 45 minutes. Stir in pinto beans and cook for 15 minutes longer.
Yields three quarts.

title: italian sausage soup
directions: Cook sausage links and cut into bite-size pieces.
Add the remaining ingredients and cook together with the sausage.

title: stuffed summer squash
directions: Simmer squash in salted water until tender.
Slice in half lengthwise and scoop out inside, leaving shells intact.
Drain and mash squash meat with remaining ingredients and stuff into shells. Sprinkle with additional cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Melt butter and cream cheese, add soup mix and seasoning; fold into spinach.
Put in casserole dish and top with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Freezes well.
Serves 10.
Quadruple recipe for 50 people.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in round microwave dish.
Top with chili. Top with cheese.
Microwave 5 minutes.
Mix.
Serve hot with taco chips or Doritos.

title: broccoli, tomato and basil frittata
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Oil 7 to 8-inch baking dish.
In large bowl, combine first 4 ingredients.
Saute in oil for 5 minutes. Add tomato and basil and saute 10 minutes, stirring frequently. Add broccoli and mushrooms and cook 5 minutes more.
Add this mixture to eggs and pour into prepared dish.
Bake 15 to 17 minutes, until just set.
Do not overbake.
Serve immediately.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, soda and cinnamon.
In saucepan, mix oleo, cocoa and water.
Bring to boil; pour over dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into greased sheet cake pan.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: ham croquettes
directions: Cook together the milk, butter, onion, flour, salt and pepper to make a creamy sauce, then add the wine and ham, cook slowly. Afterwards, put it in the refrigerator for 2 hours.
Then, form the croquettes, using eggs and cracker crumbs and fry them.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Heat all ingredients together in saucepan and put in casserole dish; cook in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: spicy pickles
directions: Drain juice (save). Cut whole pickles in 1/4 pieces. Return juice to jar with sugar, garlic juice and Tabasco sauce. Stir until sugar is dissolved. Add pickles. Turn jar every day for about 4 days. Ready to eat!

title: ham potato scallop
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, layer half of the ham, half of the onion and half of the potatoes.
Repeat layers.
Mix soup, milk, and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven about one hour or until potatoes are almost tender.

title: stollen
directions: Soften yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Melt butter (margarine or half and half) in milk.
In large mixer bowl, put sifted flour with salt.
Make a well in center and add the milk/butter mixture (slightly cooled) and eggs.
Stir with a wooden spoon to blend along with the yeast.
Add the fruit and sugar mixture.
Knead or use dough hooks and work until smooth, elastic and cleans the bowl.
Cover with towel and set in warm (not hot) place for 12 hours.

title: country fair brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, then walnuts.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until firm in center.
Be careful not to overbake.

title: old fashioned cooked dressing
directions: Beat egg yolk lightly in a small saucepan. Mix together in 1 cup milk, flour and cornstarch. Mix this will the egg yolk. Add sugar and mix; add 1/3 cup milk and mix. Add vinegar and mix. Bring all to a boil, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add salt and margarine. Mix and let cool, then refrigerate. This is a good dressing for Waldorf salad, fruit salad or slaw. For slaw, add 1/4 teaspoon dry mustard to the dressing. Makes 1 cup.

title: trick or treat caramel corn
directions: In large pan, mix popcorn and pretzels; set aside.

Over medium heat, cook brown sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt, stirring until mixture comes to a full boil (12 to 14 minutes). Continue cooking and stirring, until small amount of mixture dropped in ice water forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat and stir in baking soda.
Pour over popcorn and pretzels.
Sprinkle peanuts over caramel mixture and stir until all popcorn is coated.
Bake 20 minutes in oven at 200°.
Stir.
Continue baking for 20 minutes.
Stir in M&M's and candy corn; continue baking for 5 minutes.
Immediately spread on waxed paper to cool.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 26 cups.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix ingredients in order as listed.
Freeze in a 9 x 13-inch dish or 2 smaller dishes.
After freezing, may be cut in squares and stored in Ziploc bags in freezer.
Easy to remove from bag as a snack.

title: nordstrom's nordy bars
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter over medium heat. Add butterscotch chips and brown sugar, stirring until melted.
Remove pan.
Add eggs, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix thoroughly. Stir in vanilla. Cool. When cool, stir in chocolate chips, marshmallows and pecans.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove and cool thoroughly.
Cut into squares.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by spoonfuls into a deep fryer. Cook until golden brown.

title: yogurt parfait
directions: In a parfait glass or large glass mug, layer one-third of the yogurt, half of the granola and then half of the fruit.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining yogurt.
Yields 1 serving.

title: honey date cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place the honey, sugar, raisins, water, shortening, cinnamon and salt in a saucepan and boil for 3 minutes.
Cool about 30 minutes.
Add the flour and the baking soda which have been mixed together.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into 10 x 16-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: ice cream
directions: Pour into an ice cream maker.

title: orange velvet cake(this cake will melt in your mouth.)
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder into a large bowl.
In separate dish, cream shortening, sugar and rind thoroughly.
Beat in egg.
Add dry ingredients and milk, alternately.
Place in lightly greased 8-inch pan and bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Cook ground beef; drain.
Add all ingredients.
Simmer 2 hours or cook all day in crock-pot.

title: homemade mayonnaise(luscious and versatile and ready in minutes)
directions: Combine egg yolks, whole egg, mustard, salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste and half of the lemon juice in the bowl of a food processor fitted with a steel blade.
Process for 1 minute.

title: janet's chicken breasts in sour cream
directions: Marinate chicken for 6 hours or overnight in sour cream, mixed with next 3 ingredients. (I use a Baggie.) Shape like veal birds and roll in dressing mix. Let sit for an hour in the refrigerator to hold shape. Drizzle with a stick of melted butter. Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven. Baste once. These freeze beautifully at the ready-to-bake stage.

title: stir-fried steak
directions: Partially freeze steak; slice across grain into 3 x 1/4-inch strips.
Set aside.
Combine soy sauce, sherry and garlic; mix well.
Add steak and marinate 30 minutes.
Trim off large outer leaves of broccoli and remove tough ends of stalks.
Wash broccoli thoroughly; cut stalks diagonally into 1-inch pieces.
If stalks are more than 1 inch in diameter, cut in halves lengthwise. Separate flowerets into small pieces.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salted water until tender.
Drain and mash. Combine with other ingredients and pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes (or until browned). You may sprinkle extra cheese on top if desired.
You may also add 1 large onion, chopped, and cooked with squash, if desired. Serves 4.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar, then cream both.
Add eggs and beat.
Add sifted dry ingredients, then milk and vanilla.
Beat well.

title: barbecued ground beef
directions: In oil, saute onion, celery and green pepper.
Add ground beef and cook until beef is gray color.
Add salt, pepper, tomato soup and barbecue sauce.
Mix well.
Simmer about 1 hour.
Serve on buns or rolls.

title: apple dip
directions: In food processor, grind peanuts. Add sugar, then cream cheese and vanilla. Serve with sliced green and red apples.

title: potato cakes
directions: Add beaten egg to mashed potatoes.
Stir in 1/2 cup flour gradually.
May have to use more or less flour.
Mixture should be similar to cookie dough.
Preheat oil in skillet.
Drop potato mixture by tablespoon.
Let brown on first side.
Turn, mash with spatula and let brown on second side.
Great way to use left over mashed potatoes.

title: oatmeal fruit cookies(sugar-free)
directions: Sift flour and soda together; set aside.
Over medium-high heat, bring water, dates, apples and raisins to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; simmer 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; add margarine. Stir until melted.
Pour into large bowl; cool slightly.
Stir in dry ingredients, oatmeal, beaten eggs, vanilla and chopped walnuts until well blended.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter; add broccoli.
Simmer, covered, for 10 mintues.
Add cubes and boiling water and simmer another 15 minutes.

title: val's cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and soda; stir in pineapple and eggs.
Mix by hand.
Bake at 350° until done; watch closely.

title: low-fat vegetable meat soup
directions: *May use frozen stew vegetables.

title: skillet corn
directions: Cut kernels from corn, scraping the cob.
Melt margarine in a heavy skillet and saute corn lightly (about 10 minutes).
Combine a little of the milk with flour and stir into the corn.
Add other ingredients and remaining milk; simmer, covered, over low heat for 20 minutes.
Stir often to keep from scorching.

title: corn casserole
directions: Take a frying pan; put in 1/2 stick margarine, pepper, onion and jalapeno peppers.
Cook peppers and onion together.
Open 2 cans of creamed corn.
Mix in bowl with peppers and rice.
Top with shredded cheese.
Put in oven and grease casserole dish. Cook about 30 minutes.
Bake at 325°.

title: fruity icies
directions: Put crushed ice and 7-Up in a blender.
Add any kind of canned fruit and blend.
Our favorite is cling peaches.

title: diced apple salad
directions: Combine apples, nuts, and raisins in a salad bowl.
In a small bowl, stir mayonnaise and sugar together; beat until creamy. If needed, stir in a teaspoon of milk to thin.
Pour dressing over salad and stir to coat.

title: olive bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine orange juice, oil, salt and flour; knead well until smooth and satiny.
In a separate bowl, combine olives, onions and mint.
Roll dough to 1/8-inch thickness.
You may roll individual 5-inch circles or roll out larger portion and use round cookie cutter.
Place 1 teaspoon olive filling along edge and roll dough.
Pinch center to close and form into crescent shape.
Place on cookie sheet and bake approximately 30 minutes or until light golden.
Makes approximately 80 pieces.

title: pink salad
directions: In a saucepan mix drained juice from pineapple and add marshmallows.
Heat slowly until marshmallows dissolve.
Stir in jello; set aside.
In a bowl mix crushed pineapple, cottage cheese, pecans and whipping cream.
Add mixture from saucepan to ingredients in bowl.
Stir and mix well.
Pour into square container and refrigerate for several hours.
Cut into squares and serve.
Very easy and takes about 5 minutes to mix.

title: avocado cocktail
directions: Cook until it thickens; stir.
Serve hot in avocados.
Leave shell on avocados, serve 1/2 avocado on lettuce leaf.

title: ranchero roll-ups
directions: In large skillet, cook onion in 1 tablespoon oil until tender-crisp.
Drain tomatoes, reserving liquid.
Add liquid and oregano to skillet; cook over high heat 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in meat and chiles; remove from heat.
Spoon chicken mixture into each tortilla; roll up.
Add remaining tablespoon oil to skillet and lightly brown roll-ups.
Chop tomatoes; stir in vinegar.
Pour over roll-ups; cover and cook over low heat for 3 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Slightly crush 1/2 box of wafers in dish.
Sweeten and crush berries.
Put half on top of wafers.
Mix pudding according to directions
on box or use a homemade recipe.
Put half of pudding mixture on berries.
Repeat layers.
Put Cool Whip on top.
Can use peaches too.

title: portuguese clam stew with garlic croutons
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In a saut pan, heat the olive oil. When the pan is smoking hot, add the chorizo.

Brown the sausage for 2 to 3 minutes. Add the onions, cilantro, garlic, shallots, potatoes, salt, crushed red pepper, black pepper and shrimp stock. Bring to a boil. Add the clams, tomatoes, green onions and Essence.
Cover the saut pan and cook over high heat until all the clams are open, about 5 minutes. Remove from the heat.

title: linda's chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with garlic salt.
Cook in small amount of oil in electric skillet.
Take out and saute onions, green pepper and mushrooms.
Place chicken in baking pan.
Spoon vegetables over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Place under broiler until cheese melts and is lightly browned.

title: chicken over rice
directions: Mix rice, water, 1/2 envelope of onion soup mix and soup; pour into well-greased baking pan.
Place chicken breasts over rice mixture and sprinkle with the rest of the onion soup mix over chicken and bake for 2 hours at 350° covered.
Uncover last 15 minutes to brown.

title: frosted chews
directions: Place sugar and corn syrup in medium-size saucepan and stir to combine.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter.
Mix well. Add Special K cereal.
Stir until evenly coated.
Press mixture evenly and firmly into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Cool.

title: oatmeal jumbles
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar.
Blend in eggs, vanilla and orange peel.
Beat well.
Sift together flour and baking powder. Add to creamed mixture.
Blend well.
Blend in milk.
Stir in rolled oats, nutmeats, raisins and coconut.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch square pieces.
Cut broccoli flowerets into bite-size pieces and peeled stalks into thin slices.
Heat oil in large skillet over high heat.
Add chicken; stir-fry 1 minute.
Add broccoli and onion; stir-fry 1 minute.
Add 2 tablespoons water; cover and cook 2 minutes, stirring once.
Add bell peppers and mushrooms; stir-fry 3 minutes.
Add stir-fry sauce and crushed red pepper.
Cook, stirring, until chicken and vegetables are coated with sauce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
